The Little White Bird is a British novel by J. M. Barrie , ranging in tone from fantasy and whimsy to social comedy with dark , aggressive undertones .
A Little History of the World ( originally in German , Eine kurze Weltgeschichte für junge Leser ) is a history book by Ernst Gombrich .
Caesar 's Women is the fourth historical novel in Colleen McCullough 's Masters of Rome series , published in 1996 .
Paris 1850 ( 2004 ) , is the second novel in the Vampire Plagues series by Sebastian Rook , the pseudonym for Ben Jeapes .
Romeo Brown was a British comic strip written by Peter O'Donnell and drawn by Alfred Mazure ( 1954 - -1957 ) and Jim Holdaway ( 1957 - -1963 ) .
Military Cross T./2nd Lt . Wilfred Beaver , Gen. List , and R.F.C. For conspicuous gallantry and devotion to duty .
Captain Arthur J. Jackson ( born October 18 , 1924 ) is a United States Marine who received the Medal of Honor for his actions on Peleliu during World War II . PFC Jackson single - handedly destroyed 12 enemy pillboxes and killed 50 enemy soldiers .
In January 2010 , King Juan Carlos I appointed Javier Solana the 1,194th Knight of the Order of the Golden Fleece for his career in diplomacy .
Joe Isgro ( born c. 1948 ) is an American Academy Award - nominated producer and Purple Heart veteran .
Gerhard Simons ( born 5 February 1921 ) is an officer who served in the German army during World War II . He was a recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross with Oak Leaves ( medals recognising extreme battlefield bravery or successful military leadership ) .
Sympathy for Delicious is a 2010 drama film , and the directorial debut of Mark Ruffalo .
Jump Tomorrow is a 2001 independent film and romantic comedy written and directed by Joel Hopkins , starring Tunde Adebimpe , Hippolyte Girardot , and Natalia Verbeke .
H.M.S. Defiant ( released as Damn the Defiant ! in the United States ) is a British adventure CinemaScope and Technicolor film from 1962 starring Alec Guinness and Dirk Bogarde .
The Lost Bridegroom a 1916 silent comedy film produced by Adolph Zukor starring John Barrymore .
The Scotland Yard Mystery is a 1934 British crime film directed by Thomas Bentley and starring Gerald du Maurier , George Curzon , Grete Natzler , Belle Chrystall and Wally Patch .
Her Nameless Child is a 1915 British silent drama film directed by A.V. Bramble , Fred Groves and M. Gray Murray .
Duane Hopwood is a 2005 film featured in the Sundance Film Festival starring David Schwimmer and Janeane Garofalo , with a supporting cast featuring Judah Friedlander , Dick Cavett , Susan Lynch , John Krasinski , Rachel Covey , and Mia Dillon .
Shockproof is a 1949 American film noir directed by Douglas Sirk , and starring Cornel Wilde and Patricia Knight .
This Is the Army is a 1943 American wartime musical comedy film produced by Hal B. Wallis and Jack L. Warner , and directed by Michael Curtiz , adapted from a wartime stage musical with the same name , designed to boost morale in the U.S. during World War II , directed by Ezra Stone .
Johnny Concho is a 1956 film starring Frank Sinatra , Phyllis Kirk and Keenan Wynn and directed by Don McGuire .
El estudiante ( English : The Student ) is a 2009 Mexican film written and directed by Roberto Girault , and starring Jorge Lavat , Norma Lazareno , José Carlos Ruiz , Jeannine Derbez , Siouzana Melikián and Cristina Obregón .
Pattakkathi Bhairavan ( Tamil : பட்டாக்கத்தி பைரவன் ) is a 1979 Tamil - language Indian feature film starring Sivaji Ganesan , Jaiganesh , Sridevi and Jayasudha in the lead roles .
The Understanding Heart is a 1927 American silent adventure drama film directed by Jack Conway and stars Joan Crawford in an early leading role .
Sontha Ooru ( English : Native village ) is a 2009 Telugu film starring Raja , Thirtha , L.B. Sriram in main roles .

A Strange Kind of Colonel ( French : Un drôle de colonel ) is a 1968 French comedy film directed by Jean Girault and starring Jean Lefebvre , Jean Yanne and Pascale Roberts .

Kallukkul Eeram ( Tamil : கல்லுக்குள் ஈரம் English : Moisture inside stone ) is a 1980 Kollywood film directed by P. S. Nivas , starring P. Bharathiraja , Sudhakar , Aruna and Vijayashanti . Aruna and Vijayashanti was debut movie in Tamil language .
Tin Hats is a 1926 comedy film directed by Edward Sedgwick ( his first for MGM ) , starring Claire Windsor and Conrad Nagel .

Film Portrait ( 1972 ) is a full - length autobiographical movie directed by , and about , the life of Minnesotan film - maker and artist , Jerome Hill .
Hercules and the Masked Rider ( Italian : Golia e il cavaliere mascherato , also known as Goliath and the Masked Rider ) is a 1963 Italian peplum film written and directed by Piero Pierotti and starring Alan Steel and Mimmo Palmara .

One More Spring is a 1935 film about three people ( Janet Gaynor , Warner Baxter , and Walter Woolf King ) living together in the maintenance shed at Central Park as an alternative to living on the streets .

Stowaway on Board ( Spanish : Polizón a bordo ) is a 1941 Spanish comedy film directed by Florián Rey , co - starring Guadalupe Muñoz Sampedro and Ismael Merlo .

A Chilling Cosplay is a 2013 Chinese - Hong Kong crime thriller film directed by Wang Guangli and starring Simon Yam , Vivian Hsu , Ying Er and Yuan Hong .
The Kiss in the Tunnel is a 1899 film British short silent comedy film , produced and directed by George Albert Smith , showing a couple sharing a brief kiss as their train passes through a tunnel , which is said to mark the beginnings of narrative editing .
Oh , Mabel Behave is a 1922 American silent comedy film starring Mabel Normand , Mack Sennett and Ford Sterling .
The Pope Must Die stars Robbie Coltrane as a low ranking priest who is mistakenly elected Pope , then has to avoid being assassinated by the Mafia .

Dancing Lady is a 1933 American Pre - Code musical film starring Joan Crawford and Clark Gable , and featuring Franchot Tone , Fred Astaire , Robert Benchley , and the Three Stooges .
Thomas Boyle ( 29 June 1775 -- 12 October 1825 ) was one of the most successful Baltimore privateer captains during the War of 1812 .
Captain John Herbert Hedley ( 19 July 1887 -- 1 April 1977 ) was a World War I British flying ace credited with eleven aerial victories .
Vladimir Efimovich Gorev ( 1900 - 20 June 1938 ) , known as Vladimir Gorev , was a military Belarusian known to have participated in the defense of Madrid as a Soviet military advisor during the Spanish Civil War .
Major Rajesh Singh Adhikari , MVC ( December 25 , 1970 -- May 30 , 1999 ) , was an Indian Army officer who died during the Kargil War .
Lieutenant Colonel John McCrae , MD ( November 30 , 1872 -- January 28 , 1918 ) was a Canadian poet , physician , author , artist and soldier during World War I , and a surgeon during the Second Battle of Ypres , in Belgium .
Frederick S. Neilon ( June 22 , 1846 -- September 13 , 1916 ) , also called Frank Singleton , was an American soldier in the U.S. Army who served with the 6th U.S. Cavalry during the Red River War .
Milan Kalabić ( Serbian Cyrillic : Милан Калабић ; 1886 -- 3 October 1942 ) was a Serbian military officer who fought in the Balkan Wars and the First World War and was involved with the Chetniks during the Second World War .
Thomas Cavanaugh ( born May 10 , 1869 ) was an American sailor serving in the United States Navy during the Spanish-- American War who received the Medal of Honor for bravery .
Newton Henry Mason ( 24 December 1918 -- May 1942 ) was a decorated United States Navy fighter pilot of World War II who was killed in action at the Battle of the Coral Sea .
Luís Vaz Pereira Pinto Guedes , 2nd Viscount of Montalegre , was a Portuguese soldier , born 1770 , who served on the absolutist side in Portugal 's Liberal Wars .
Gerhard Schacht ( 6 April 1916 -- 7 February 1972 ) was a highly decorated Major i . G. in the Fallschirmjäger during World War II and an Oberst in the Bundeswehr .
Orland Smith ( May 2 , 1825 -- October 3 , 1903 ) was a railroad executive and a brigade commander in the Union Army during the American Civil War .
Neboulos ( Greek : Νέβουλος ) was a South Slavic or Bulgar military commander in the service of the Byzantine emperor Justinian II ( r. 685 - -695 and 705 - -711 ) , who defected with many of his men to the Arabs during the crucial Battle of Sebastopolis .
Captain Jameel Sayhood was an Iraqi pilot in the Gulf War who it is claimed managed to attain one of the few aerial victories by the Iraqi Air Force in his MiG-29B , before being shot down by USAF Captain Craig Underhill and Captain Cesar Rodriguez with their F-15Cs mere minutes after his air - air victory .
The M1 carbine ( formally the United States Carbine , Caliber .30 , M1 ) is a lightweight .30 caliber semi - automatic carbine that became a standard firearm for the U.S. military during World War II , the Korean War and the Vietnam War , and was produced in several variants .
Karl Kessel ( 1 June 1912 -- 24 August 1997 ) was a highly decorated Oberstleutnant i m Generalstab in the Luftwaffe during World War II and a Generalmajor in the Bundeswehr .
Thomas Cruse ( December 29 , 1857 -- June 8 , 1943 ) was a United States Army Brigadier General who was a recipient of the Medal of Honor for valor in action on July 17 , 1882 , at the Battle of Big Dry Wash , Arizona .
Werner Dobberstein ( 4 April 1911 -- 25 February 1993 ) was a Korvettenkapitän with the Kriegsmarine during World War II and a recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross .
David Gregg McIntosh ( March 16 , 1836 -- October 16 , 1916 ) was a Confederate artillery officer during the American Civil War from the state of South Carolina .
On 26 February 1940 Ronald Symond enlisted again ( in World War II ) .
Robert Heriot Barclay ( 18 September 1786 -- 8 May 1837 ) was a British naval officer who was engaged in the Napoleonic Wars , and its North American counterpart , the War of 1812 .
Ernst Nobis ( 18 October 1901 -- 7 March 1963 ) was a highly decorated Oberst in the Wehrmacht during World War II who later served in the Austrian Bundesheer .
Otto Kissenberth ( 26 February 1893 -- 2 August 1919 ) was a German flying ace of World War I credited with 20 aerial victories .
Oberstleutnant Anton Mader ( born 7 January 1913 in Kaštel Novi -- died 19 February 1984 in Vienna ) was German World War II Luftwaffe 86 victories Flying ace and recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross .
The Battle of Arica , also known as Assault and Capture of Cape Arica , was a battle in the War of the Pacific .
Leutnant Hans - Georg von der Osten began his career as a World War I flying ace credited with five aerial victories .
Col . Herbert T. Levack ( March 14 , 1916 -- January 27 , 2010 ) was a command pilot in the U.S. Air Force flying B-24s in World War II , and C-124s in Korea and Vietnam .
USS Sallie Wood ( 1860 ) was a 256-ton steamer captured by the Union Navy during the early years of the American Civil War .
USS Stonewall ( 1863 ) was a small 30-ton blockade - running schooner captured by the Union Navy during the Union blockade of the American Civil War .
Josef Swientek ( 1 February 1912 -- 29 June 1991 ) was a Standartenführer ( Colonel ) in the Waffen SS during World War II who was awarded the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross , which was awarded to recognize extreme battlefield bravery or successful military leadership by Nazi Germany during World War II .
Alfred B. Hilton ( 1842 -- October 21 , 1864 ) was a Union Army soldier during the American Civil War and a recipient of America 's highest military decoration -- the Medal of Honor -- for his actions at the Battle of Chaffin 's Farm .
Lothar Kmitta ( 19 January 1921 -- 13 May 2009 ) was a highly decorated Leutnant in the Luftwaffe during World War II , and a recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross .
Julio Mangada Rosenörn ( June 30 , 1877 Sancti Spíritus , Cuba -- April 14 , 1946 , Mexico City ) was a prominent Spanish Republican Army officer during the Second Spanish Republic and the Spanish Civil War .
Major Thomas Sinclair Harrison DFC * ( born 8 January 1898 in South Africa ) was a World War I fighter ace credited with 22 aerial victories .
Klaus Häberlen ( 14 April 1916 -- 7 April 2002 ) was a German Luftwaffe bomber pilot during World War II and recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross which was awarded to recognise extreme battlefield bravery or successful military leadership .
Quincy Adams Gillmore ( February 25 , 1825 -- April 11 , 1888 ) was an American civil engineer , author , and a general in the Union Army during the American Civil War .
Matthäus Hetzenauer ( 23 December 1924 in Tyrol , Austria -- 3 October 2004 ) was an Austrian sniper in the 3rd Mountain Division on the Eastern Front of the World War II , who was credited with 345 kills .
Mustafa Şekip Birgöl ( 1903 -- November 11 , 2008 ) , a retired Turkish colonel , was the last veteran of the Turkish War of Independence ( 1919 - -1923 ) .
David Bullock Harris ( September 28 , 1814 -- October 10 , 1864 ) was a Colonel in the Confederate States Army during the American Civil War ( Civil War ) .
Charles - Théodore Millot ( 28 June 1829 -- 17 May 1889 ) was a French general who distinguished himself in the Franco - Prussian War ( 1870 - -71 ) and the Tonkin campaign ( 1883 - -86 ) .
Major Arthur Chin ( Chinese : 陳瑞鈿 ; pinyin : Chén Ruìdiàn ; Cantonese : Chan Sui - Tin ; October 23 , 1913 -- September 3 , 1997 ) was a pilot from the United States who participated in the Second Sino - Japanese War .
George Henry Thomas ( July 31 , 1816 -- March 28 , 1870 ) was a United States Army officer and a Union general during the American Civil War , one of the principal commanders in the Western Theater .
Clack Stone ( fl . 1827 - -1839 ) was a captain in the 27th Regiment Illinois Militia during the 1832 Black Hawk War .
John Pope Cook ( June 12 , 1825 -- October 13 , 1910 ) was an Illinois politician and a general in the Union Army during the American Civil War .
Franco Lucchini , MOVM , ( 24 December 1917 -- 5 July 1943 ) was an Italian World War II fighter pilot in the Aviazione Legionaria and in the Regia Aeronautica .
Major Archibald H. Gillespie ( 14 August 1810 -- 16 August 1873 ) was an officer in the United States Marine Corps during the Mexican - American War .
Heinz - Otto Fabian ( 1 March 1918 -- 16 September 1990 ) was a highly decorated Major in the Wehrmacht during World War II and later a Brigadegeneral of the Bundeswehr .
Colonel Ambrosio José Gonzales ( October 3 , 1818 -- July 31 , 1893 ) was a Cuban revolutionary who became a Colonel in the Confederate States Army during the American Civil War .
Mitros Petrovas or Mitropetrovas ( Greek : Μήτρος Πέτροβας , Μητροπέτροβας , 1745 -- 12 March 1838 ) was a military leader of the Greek War of Independence from Messenia and one of the leaders of the anti - government riots during the Bavarian regency of Greece .
Joseph L. Epps ( May 16 , 1870 - -June 20 , 1952 ) was a United States Army private received the Medal of Honor for his actions on December 4 , 1899 during the Philippine - American War .
Jacob Fick ( 17 January 1912 -- 22 April 2004 ) was an Obersturmbannführer ( Lieutenant Colonel ) , in the Waffen SS during World War II who was awarded the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross .
Colonel Ernst Ludwig Wilhelm von Bismarck ( 7 April 1772 in Magdeburg -- 20 June 1815 in Namur ) was a Prussian officer during the Napoleonic Wars .
Paul Langkopf ( 7 July 1915 -- 6 November 1961 ) was a highly decorated Oberleutnant in the Luftwaffe during World War II , and a recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross .
Joel Abbot ( January 18 , 1793 -- December 14 , 1855 ) was a U.S. naval officer who served notably in the War of 1812 , and commanded a squadron during Commodore Perry 's 1852 visit to Japan .
Major Reinhard Seiler ( 30 August 1909 -- 6 October 1989 ) was German Spanish Civil War and World War II Luftwaffe Ace , commander of Jagdgeschwader 104 and a winner of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross with Oak Leaves ( German : Ritterkreuz des Eisernen Kreuzes mit Eichenlaub ) .
Prince Alexei Grigorievich Scherbatov ( Russian : Алексей Григорьевич Щербатов ; 1776 - 1848 ) was a Russian imperial general during the Napoleonic Wars and November Uprising .
James Kelsey Cogswell ( September 27 , 1847 -- August 12 , 1908 ) was an admiral in the United States Navy who served in Spanish-- American War .
Anthimos Gazis ( or Gazes ; Ἄνθιμος Γαζῆς ; 1758 , Milies -- 1828 , Ermoupoli , Syros ) was a Greek scholar , philosopher during the Greek Enlightenment , cartographer and one of the heroes of the Greek War of Independence against the Ottoman Empire .
Pomeroy Parker ( March 17 , 1874 -- December 30 , 1946 ) was a private serving in the United States Marine Corps during the Spanish-- American War who received the Medal of Honor for bravery .
David McMurtrie Gregg ( April 10 , 1833 -- August 7 , 1916 ) was a farmer , diplomat , and a Union cavalry general in the American Civil War .
Nikitaras ( Greek : Νικηταράς ) was the nom de guerre of Nikitas Stamatelopoulos ( Greek : Νικήτας Σταματελόπουλος ) ( 1784 -- 1849 ) , a Greek revolutionary in the Greek War of Independence .
Alfred Siegling ( 15 March 1918 -- 6 September 1984 ) was a Untersturmführer ( Second Lieutenant ) , in the Waffen SS during World War II who was awarded the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross .
The Ordnance QF 6-pounder 6 cwt Hotchkiss Mk I and Mk II was a shortened version of the original QF 6 pounder Hotchkiss naval gun , and was developed specifically for use in the sponsons of the later Marks of British tanks in World War I , from Mark IV onwards .
General Stanisław Maczek ( ( staˈɲiswav ˈmat͡ʂɛk ) ; 31 March 1892 -- 11 December 1994 ) was a Polish tank commander of World War II , whose division was instrumental in the Allied liberation of France , closing the Falaise pocket , resulting in the destruction of 14 German Wehrmacht and SS divisions .
Edward B. Young ( 1835 -- February 24 , 1867 ) was a Union Navy sailor in the American Civil War and a recipient of the U.S. military 's highest decoration , the Medal of Honor , for his actions at the Battle of Mobile Bay .
Jean François Graindorge ( 1 July 1770 -- 1 October 1810 ) became a brigade commander during the Napoleonic Wars and was mortally wounded while leading his troops against the British at the Battle of Bussaco in Portugal .
Jürgen Stroop ( born Josef Stroop , 26 September 1895 in Detmold , Germany -- 6 March 1952 in Warsaw , Poland ) was an SS General during World War II . He was in command against the Warsaw Ghetto Uprising and wrote the Stroop Report , a book - length account of the operation .
Hormuzan ( Middle Persian : Hormazdān , New Persian : هرمزان ) was an Iranian aristocrat who served as the governor of Khuzestan , and was one of the Sasanian military officers at the Battle of al - Qādisiyyah .
Messier 28 ( also known as M28 or NGC 6626 ) is a globular cluster in the constellation Sagittarius .

HAT - P-6b is a transiting extrasolar planet located approximately 650 light - years away in the constellation of Andromeda , orbiting the star HAT - P-6 .

HD 115337 is a cool supergiant star in the constellation Camelopardalis .
Lacaille 9352 ( Lac 9352 ) is a star in the southern constellation of Piscis Austrinus .
HD 33636 is a binary system located approximately 94 light - years away in Orion constellation .
The Glover Rocks ( 67 ° 46′S 68 ° 54′W ) are a group of rocks lying northwest of Avian Island , off the south end of Adelaide Island , Antarctica .
Hiyoko Island is an island lying 1.1 kilometres ( 0.6 nmi ) southwest of Nesøya in the northeastern part of Lützow - Holm Bay , Antarctica .
Mount McDonald ( 72 ° 30′S 166 ° 36′E ) is a peak rising to 2,470 metres ( 8,100 ft ) on the north side of Trafalgar Glacier , 4 nautical miles ( 7 km ) northwest of Mount Burton , in the Victory Mountains of Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Krakra Bluff ( Rid Krakra \'rid ' kra - kra\ ) is a rocky bluff of elevation 140 m surmounting Memorable Beach ( 62 ° 38′35``S 60 ° 33′19''W ) on the northwest coast of South Bay , Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Jacobs Island is a narrow island 560 m ( 0.3 nmi ) long between the Hellerman Rocks and Laggard Island , off the southwest coast of Anvers Island , Antarctica .
Nižná Voľa ( Ukrainian : Нижня Воля , Nyzhnia Volia ) is a village and municipality in Bardejov District in the Prešov Region of north - east Slovakia .

John Conrad Jaeger , FRS ( 30 July 1907 -- 15 May 1979 ) was an Australian mathematical physicist .
Jean Dondelinger ( 4 July 1931 -- 21 October 2004 ) was a Luxembourgian diplomat and civil servant .
Forbes Johnston ( 3 August 1971 -- 12 July 2007 ) was a Scottish professional footballer playing primarily in defence , but also spending some time in the midfield .
William Denis Kendall , generally known as Denis Kendall , ( 27 May 1903 Halifax , West Yorkshire , England -- 19 July 1995 Los Angeles , California ) , was a controversial , British , Independent , Member of Parliament .
Hallvard Gunnarssøn ( c.1550 -- 1608 ) was a Norwegian educator and non - fiction writer .
Tom Mackie ( 30 March 1918 -- 1989 ) was a Scottish professional footballer who played as a left back .
Hugh Goodacre ( died 1553 ) was an English Protestant clergyman , who was briefly Church of Ireland Archbishop of Armagh and Primate of Ireland .
Selim Aga ( born around 1826 in Taqali area of Sudan , died December 1875 in Liberia ) , a native of Sudan who was abducted by slave traders when he was eight years of age , was brought to Scotland in 1836 , and raised and educated as a free man .
Baldwin Nkumbula ( died 27 August 1995 ) was a Zambian politician and a son of veteran politician Harry Nkumbula .
Richard Buchta ( 19 January 1845 -- 29 July 1894 ) was an Austrian explorer , born in Radlow , Galicia .
Paulus Barbus ( Paul Soncinas ) ( b. at Soncino , Lombardy , from where comes the name of Soncinas which appears at the head of his books ; d. at Cremona , 4 August 1494 ) was an Italian Dominican philosopher and theologian .
Charles Zinzan ( died 1714 ) was the English Acting Governor of Bombay in the late 17th century .
Charles Frank Byers , Baron Byers , OBE , PC , DL ( 24 July 1915 -- 6 February 1984 ) was a British Liberal Party politician .
Edwin Lankester FRS , FRMS , MRCS ( 23 April 1814 -- 30 October 1874 ) was an English surgeon and naturalist who made a major contribution to the control of cholera in London : he was the first public analyst in England .
Tamaz Nadareishvili ( Georgian : თამაზ ნადარეიშვილი ) ( 19 July 1954 -- 31 August 2004 ) was a Georgian politician who served as head of the Council of Ministers of Abkhazia , a government - in - exile for the breakaway province .
Jon Pyong - ho ( March 1926 -- 7 July 2014 ; also written Chŏn Pyŏng - ho ) was the Chief Secretary of the Korean Workers Party ( KWP ) Committee of the North Korean Cabinet , and director of the DPRK Cabinet Political Bureau before his retirement in 2010 .
Herbert Ditty ( died 1998 ) was a lifelong Ulster Unionist politician , representing the Shankill Road , Belfast , Northern Ireland .
Esther Roper ( 4 August 1868 -- 28 April 1938 ) was an English suffragist and social justice campaigner who fought for equal employment and voting rights for working - class women .
Nicholas Merbury ( died 1421 ) was an English administrator , Member of Parliament and first Master of the Ordnance .
Pleasant Moorman Miller , ( unknown birth - 1849 ) was an American politician who represented Tennessee in the United States House of Representatives .
Paul Lester Wiener ( 1895 - -1967 ) was an American architect and urban planner .
Samuel Hale Parker ( 1781 - -1864 ) was a publisher and bookseller in 19th - century Boston , Massachusetts , United States .
Lennart Rönnback ( 21 May 1905 -- 4 November 2007 ) was a Finnish White Guard veteran of the Finnish Civil War of 1918 .
K. Srinivasan ( 1899 - -1975 ) , also known as Stalin Srinivasan , was an Indian journalist and Indian independence activist who founded the journal Manikodi in 1932 .
Ashok Kumar ( 13 October 1911 -- 10 December 2001 ) , born Kumudlal Ganguly and also fondly called Dadamoni , was an Indian film actor who attained iconic status in Indian cinema .
Elsie Hill ( 1883 - -1970 ) was an American suffragist , as were her sisters Clara and Helena Hill .
August Weenaas ( 1835 - -1924 ) was a Norwegian American Lutheran minister and educator .
Harry Frederick Dietz ( 8 December 1890 , Indianapolis -4 September 1954 , Kennett Square PA ) was an American economic entomologist .
Peter Quesnel ( or Quesuel ) ( d. 1299 ? ) , Franciscan , was warden of the Franciscan house at Norwich , and died about 1299 .
Arthur Stuart - Menteth Hutchinson ( 2 June 1879 -- 14 March 1971 ) , commonly known by his initials A. S. M. Hutchinson , was a British novelist .
Michael Louis Hearn ( 1866 -- 1 May 1931 ) was an Irish Nationalist Member of the Parliament of the United Kingdom for South County Dublin , 1917 - 18 .
Gabrielle Daye ( 2 October 1911 in Manchester , Lancashire -- 5 January 2005 in Essex ) was an English television actress , notable for her role as Mrs. Pring on Bless Me Father .
William Pennefather ( 1816 - 1873 ) was an Irish Anglican cleric who spent most of his adult life in England , and was celebrated for his hymns and sermons .
Congal Cennmagair ( died 710 ) was High King of Ireland .
Margaret Mittelheuser ( 1931 - -2013 ) was an Australian stockbroker .
Bishop Festo Kivengere ( 1919 - -1988 ) was a Ugandan Anglican - Christian leader referred to by many as `` the Billy Graham of Africa '' .
Alexander Egorovich Varlamov ( or Aleksandr Yegorovich Varlamov ; Russian : Александр Егорович Варламов ; 27 November 1801 -- 27 October 1848 ) was one of the founding fathers of the Russian art song .
Kenneth H. Wood , Jr. ( 5 November 1917 -- 25 May 2008 ) was a Seventh - day Adventist minister , author , editor , and administrator .
Paul Panhuysen ( 21 August 1934 - -29 January 2015 ) was a Dutch composer , visual and sound artist .
Abd Allah ibn Abd al - Latif Al ash - Sheikh ( 1848 - -1921 ) was an Islamic scholar from Saudi Arabia and was the grandfather of King Faisal of Saudi Arabia .
Hallvard Rieber - Mohn ( 2 October 1922 , Molde - 4 August 1982 ) was a Norwegian writer and Dominican priest .
Mary Annette Anderson ( July 27 , 1874 -- 1922 ) was an American professor and the first African American woman elected to Phi Beta Kappa .
Balangoda Ananda Maitreya Thero ( Sinhalese : අග්ග මහා පණ්ඩිත බලංගොඩ ආනන්ද මෛත්‍රෙය මහනාහිමි;23 August 1896 -- 18 July 1998 ) was a Sri Lankan scholar Buddhist monk .
Christian Brod , ( Oranienburg , 1917 -- Berlin , 2012 ) was a German painter whose work was discovered by his cousin Otto Brod in 2012 .
Carron Giovanni ( before 1619 -- 1649 ) was the First Duke of Buttigliera Alta .
Adalbold II of Utrecht ( died 27 November 1026 ) was a bishop of Utrecht ( 1010 - -1026 ) .
Syed Abu Bakar bin Taha Alsagoff ( Arabic : سيد أبو بكر بن طه السقاف‎ Saiyid Abū Bakr bin Ṭāhā al - saqqāf ) ( 1882 , in Hadramaut , Yemen -- 22 January 1956 ) was a well - known Islamic educator in Singapore .
Trevor Keelor , VrC , ( 8 December 1934 -- 27 April 2002 ) was a hero of the Indo - Pakistani war .
Shmuel Ehrenfeld ( Yiddish : שמואל עהרענפעלד‎ , 1891 - -1980 ) , known as the Mattersdorfer Rav , was a pre - eminent Orthodox Jewish rabbi in pre - war Austria and a respected Torah leader and community builder in post - war America .
Hugh Robert Mill ( 28 May 1861 -- 5 April 1950 ) was a Scottish geographer and meteorologist who was influential in the reform of geography teaching , and in the development of meteorology as a science .
Audley Archdall ( 6 June 1826 -- 27 February 1893 ) was an Irish cricketer .
Daniel Jacob Danielsen ( also known as Dollin , born 15 June 1871 in Copenhagen , grew up in Tórshavn , Faroe Islands , died 16 October 1916 ) was a Faroese missionary and humanitarian worker .
Walter Shanly ( 11 October 1817 -- 17 December 1899 ) was a Canadian civil engineer , author , businessman , and politician .
Thorold Charles Reep ( 22 September 1904 -- 3 February 2002 ) was an analyst credited with creating the long ball game which has characterized English football .
Arthur Edward Waite ( 2 October 1857 -- 19 May 1942 ) , commonly known as A. E. Waite , was an American - born British poet and scholarly mystic who wrote extensively on occult and esoteric matters , and was the co - creator of the Rider - Waite Tarot deck .
Abu Mansur Sabuktigin ( Persian : ابو منصور سبکتگین‎‎ ) ( ca 942 -- August 997 ) , also spelled as Sabuktagin , Sabuktakin , Sebüktegin and Sebük Tigin , was the founder of the Ghaznavid dynasty , ruling from 977 to 997 .
Earl Carlson ( c. 1925 -- c. 1970 ) is a former ice hockey player who played for the Durham Wasps .
Diederik Sonoy or Snoey ( Kalkar ( Duchy of Cleves ) , 1529 - Pieterburen , 2 June 1597 ) was a leader of the Geuzen during the Eighty Years ' War .
David Leslie , 1st Lord Newark ( c. 1600 - -1682 ) was a cavalry officer and General in the English Civil War and Scottish Civil Wars .
I. M. Rașcu ( most common rendition of Ion Rașcu ; March 31 ( O.S. March 19 ) 1890 -- 1971 ) was a Romanian poet of Symbolist verse , cultural promoter , comparatist , and schoolteacher .
Sir William Goring , 1st Baronet ( died 1658 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1628 to 1629 .
Lady Auriel Rosemary Malet Vaughan ( 20 January 1923 -- 14 October 2014 ) was an author of literary fiction and biographies who wrote under the name of Oriel Malet .
George Clancy , also known as Seoirse Mac Fhlannchadha and Seoirse Clancy , ( 1881 -- 7 March 1921 ) , was an Irish nationalist politician and Mayor of Limerick .
Sri Swami Anandpuri ji Maharaj ( 1782 - -1872 ) is known as the founder of the Advait Mat tradition .
Xu Enzeng ( Chinese : 徐恩曾 ) ( 1896 - 1985 ) was a Republic of China politician .
John Paget Figg - Hoblyn died in a nursing home on 12 June 2011 at the age of 85 .
Joseph Jane ( died 1660 ) was an English royalist politician and controversialist .
Sir Nathaniel Creswick K.C.B. ( 31 July 1831 -- 20 October 1917 ) was an English footballer who co - founded Sheffield FC , the oldest football club in the world , in 1857 .
Kadaru Nagabhushanam or K. B. Nagabhushanam ( Telugu : కడారు నాగభూషణం ) ( 1902 -- 18 October 1976 ) was a Telugu and Tamil film director and producer in the 1940s to 1960s .
Johann Adam Breunig ( 1660 in Mainz -- 1727 ) was a German Baroque architect .
William Faithorne , often `` the Elder '' , ( 1616 -- 13 May 1691 ) , English painter and engraver .
Doris Collins ( 1918 - 2003 ) was a British spiritualist and psychic medium .
Walter Thomas James Morgan CBE FRS ( 5 October 1900 -- 10 February 2003 ) was a British biochemist noted for his work on the immunochemistry of Antigens and described as ' one of the pioneers of immunochemistry ' .
Debala Mitra ( 14 December 1925 -- 2 December 2003 ) was an Indian archaeologist who served as Director General of the Archaeological Survey of India ( ASI ) from 1981 to 1983 .
Rod Watt ( 2 January 1895 -- 29 May 1967 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Ioannis Sofianopoulos ( Greek : Ιωάννης Σοφιανόπουλος ; 1887 - -1951 ) was a Greek politician and leader of the Agrarian Party .
Sir George Aitken Clark Hutchison ( 6 July 1873 -- 22 December 1928 ) was a Scottish Unionist who served as the Member of Parliament for Midlothian and Peebles Northern from 1922 to 1923 , and from 1924 until his death .
Gaius Rubellius Blandus ( ? died 38 ) was a suffect consul of ancient Rome , a grandson of Rubellius Blandus of Tibur ( see Tivoli , Italy ) .
Khaled Yashruti ( 1937 in Akko , Palestine -- 1970 in Beirut , Lebanon ) was a Palestinian political activist and a leading member of the PLO .
Bathanarius ( died 408 ) was a politician of the Western Roman Empire , comes Africae and brother - in - law of Stilicho .
Maria Eleonora of Brandenburg ( 11 November 1599 -- 28 March 1655 ) was a German princess and queen consort of Sweden .
Mohamed El Gourch ( Arabic : محمد الكورش‎‎ ; 11 January 1936 -- 21 February 2015 ) was a Moroccan road racing cyclist who won the Tour du Maroc , a record three times , in 1960 , 1964 and 1965 .
Dr. Anna Wessels Williams ( 1863 - -1954 ) worked as a bacteriologist at the first municipal diagnostic laboratory in the United States , helped develop the diphtheria antitoxin and was the first woman to be elected chair of the laboratory section of the American Public Health Association .
Okeke Nelson Malachy ( d 26 January 2007 , Changi Prison , Singapore ) was found guilty of drug offences and subsequently executed by the government of Singapore .
Gordon Brewster ( 26 September 1889 -- 16 June 1946 ) was an editorial cartoonist for the Irish Independent group of newspapers .
Charlotte Haldane ( née Franken , first married name Burghes ; 27 April 1894 -- 16 March 1969 ) was a British feminist author .
Gonzalo Martínez Ortega ( 27 April 1934 -- 2 June 1998 ) was a Mexican actor , director , screenwriter & producer .
Samuel Kemper ( died 1814 ) was an American adventurer and filibuster .
S. Siddalingaiah ( 1936 -- 12 March 2015 ) was an Indian film director and writer in the Kannada film industry .
Thomas H. O'Shea ( 1898 - -1962 ) was an Irish revolutionary and one of the founders of the Transport Workers Union of America ( TWU ) , subway workers in New York City that expanded to represent members in other forms of transit nationwide .
Vijaya Narasimha ( Kannada : ವಿಜಯ ನರಸಿಂಹ ) ( 1927 -- 31 October 2001 ) was an Indian lyricist who worked in Kannada cinema .
Mary Ann DeWeese ( 1913 - -1993 ) was an American sportswear designer .
Ellen Maude Carey I.S.O. ( 1888 - 8 August 1950 ) was the Colonial Postmaster of the Falkland Islands from 1 January 1934 .
William II , Marquis of Namur ( 22 January 1355 -- 10 January 1418 ) inherited the Marquisate of Namur from his father William I in 1391 and held it until his own death .
Joseph Connellan , known as Joe Connellan ( died 11 April 1967 ) was a nationalist politician and newspaper editor in Ireland .
Shri Tridandi Swami ( 22 April 1905 -- 2 December 1999 ) was a renowned Sri Vaishnava saint and one of the foremost preachers of the Sri Sampradaya in North India .
Gertrude Blanch ( ca . 1897 - 1996 ) was an American mathematician who did pioneering work in numerical analysis and computation .
Howell Evans ( 3 March 1928 -- 9 September 2014 ) was a Welsh actor , comedian , and singer who worked extensively in television and theatre roles in a career spanning over 60 years .
George Meikle Kemp ( 25 May 1795 -- 6 March 1844 ) was a Scottish carpenter / joiner , draughtsman , and self - taught architect .
John Ward Knowles ( 1838 - -1931 ) was a prominent British York - based stained - glass manufacturer , and commentator on local art and music .
Leonardo Morales y Pedroso ( 1887 - -1965 ) was one of the most prominent Cuban architects from early 20th century .
Meir Argov ( Hebrew : מאיר ארגוב‎ , Meyer Grabovsky ; 1905 -- 24 November 1963 ) was a Zionist activist , Israeli politician and a signatory of the Israeli declaration of independence .
Thomas la Warr , 5th Baron De La Warr ( c. 1352 -- 7 May 1427 ) was an English nobleman , the second son of Roger la Warr , 3rd Baron De La Warr and Elizabeth de Welle , daughter of Adam , 3rd Baron Welles .
Dr August Ferdinand Carl Schwartz ( 1817 - -1870 ) was a leading Hebrew Christian clergyman and minister of the Free Church of Scotland in Amsterdam , then Free Church minister in London .
Chanakya ( IAST : Cāṇakya ; pronunciation ; 350 -- 275 BCE ) was an Indian teacher , philosopher , economist , jurist and royal advisor .
Sophus Thalbitzer ( 1871 - -1941 ) was a Danish psychiatrist and medical doctor specializing in manic depressive psychoses .
Ben - Hur Baz ( 1906 - -2003 ) was a painter of pin - up art . Born in Mexico in 1906 , Baz was a pin - up and glamour artist who became known in the late 1940s and 1950s for his association with Esquire magazine .
Samuel Courtauld ( 1793 - 1881 ) Catherine Courtauld ( 1795- ) George Courtauld ( 1802 - 1861 ) He died on 13 August 1823 in Pittsburgh , Allegheny County , Pennsylvania .
Edward L. Allen ( 1830 - 1914 ) or E.L. Allen was a photographer in 19th - century United States .
Henry M. Brinckerhoff ( 1868 - -1949 ) was a pioneering highway engineer who in 1906 partnered with William Barclay Parsons to found what would eventually be known as Parsons Brinckerhoff , one of the largest transportation , planning and engineering companies in the United States .
Andrew Keir ( 3 April 1926 -- 5 October 1997 ) was a Scottish actor , who rose to prominence in a number of films made by Hammer Film Productions in the 1960s .
Blessed Teresa Manganiello ( 1 January 1849 -- 4 November 1876 ) was an Italian who became a member of the Secular Franciscan Order .
Giano II di Campofregoso ( 1455 - -1525 ) was the 43rd Doge of Genoa , ruling from 29 June 1512 to 25 May 1513 .
Johann Jakob Erhardt , or John James Erhardt , ( 17 April 1823 -- 14 August 1901 ) was a German missionary and explorer who worked in East Africa and India .
Paolo Constabile ( died 1582 ) was the Master of the Order of Preachers from 1580 to 1582 .
Isador Goodman AM ( 27 May 1909 -- 2 December 1982 ) was a South African - Australian Jewish pianist , composer and conductor .
Thomas Wotton , 2nd Baron Wotton ( 1587 -- 2 April 1630 ) was an English peer .
Alexander Nairne D.D. ( d. 1936 ) was a Canon of Windsor from 1921 to 1936 and Regius Professor of Divinity at Cambridge .
Bumin Qaghan ( Old Turkic : , Bumïn qaγan , a.k.a . Bumın Kagan ) or Illig Qaghan ( Chinese : 伊利可汗 , Pinyin : yīlì kěhàn , Wade -- Giles : i - li k'o - han , died 552 AD ) was the founder of the Turkic Khaganate .
Alfredo Gargiullo ( Genoa , 3 April 1906 - Milan , 9 March 1928 ) was an Italian sprinter ( 400 m ) .
Shalva Amiranashvili ( Georgian : შალვა ამირანაშვილი ; 26 March 1899 -- 9 February 1975 ) was a Georgian art historian , one of the first to have engaged in systematic scholarly treatment of the art of Georgia .
Sir George Onesiphorus Paul , 2nd Baronet ( 1746 - -1820 ) was an English prison reformer and philanthropist .
Israel Goldstein ( June 18 , 1896 -- 1986 ) was an American - born Israeli rabbi , author and Zionist leader .
Amelia of Masovia ( pl : Amelia mazowiecka ; 1397/98 - after 17 May 1434 ) , was a Polish princess member of the House of Piast in the Masovian branch .
Sultan Mahmud Mirza ( c. 1453 - January 1495 ) was a prince Timurid branch of Transoxiana , son of Abu Sa'id Mirza .
Hubert Detremmerie ( 26 March 1930 ; Deerlijk--9 November 2008 ; Ronse ) was a Belgian businessman and banker .
Ebenezer Brown ( ca 1824 -- June 5 , 1883)was an English - born wholesale merchant and political figure in British Columbia .
Admiral Radhakrishna Hariram Tahiliani ( Hindi : राधाकृष्ण हरिराम तहिलियानी , 12 May 1930 -- 14 October 2015 ) also known as R. H. Tahiliani , was a Four - Star Admiral in the Indian Navy .
Samuel Cummings , ( 7 February 1927 -- 29 April 1998 ) was an American small arms dealer .
Pedro Pompilio ( 11 November 1949 -- 30 October 2008 in Bernal , Buenos Aires ) was a football businessman and chairman of Boca Juniors .
Zhu Xuzhi ( simplified Chinese : 朱虚之 ; traditional Chinese : 朱虛之 ; pinyin : Zhū Xūzhī ; 1912 - 8 November 2000 ) was a general in the People 's Liberation Army of China .
Gwen Foster ( 1903 - -1954 ) was an old - time / country harmonica player who was known for work in The Carolina Tar Heels and the Blue Ridge Mountain Entertainers .
Jonathan Stevens ( died 27 December 2013 ) , known as `` Dr. Jonny '' , was a British medical researcher and campaigner for people with Parkinson 's Disease .
David Urquhart ( 1 July 1805 -- 16 May 1877 ) was a Scottish diplomat , writer and politician , serving as a Member of Parliament from 1847 to 1852 .
Humphry William Woolrych ( 1795 - -1871 ) was an English lawyer , known as a legal writer and biographer .
Thomas Hobbes Scott ( 17 April 1783 -- 1 January 1860 ) was an English - born clergyman , active in Australia .
Dulcie Howes ( 31 December 1908 -- 19 March 1993 ) was a South African ballet dancer , teacher , choreographer , and company director .
Jovan Tomić ( 9 May 1869 in Nova Varoš -- 22 July 1932 in Belgrade ) was Serbian historian and member of Serbian Academy of Science and Arts .
Hector Morison ( 1850 -- 4 June 1939 ) was a British stockbroker and Liberal Party politician .
Sir Thomas Kitson ( 1485 -- 11 September 1540 ) was a wealthy English merchant , Sheriff of London , and builder of Hengrave Hall in Suffolk .
Gerald Sharp ( 27 October 1865 -- 30 August 1933 ) was an English - born Anglican clergyman , Archbishop of Brisbane 1921 - -1933 .
Ernest de Sélincourt ( 1870 - -1943 ) was a British literary scholar and critic .
Elizabeth Cobbold or Carolina Petty Pasty born Elizabeth Knipe ( 1765 - -1824 ) was a British writer and poet .
Lazare de Baïf ( 1496 - -1547 ) was a French diplomat and humanist .
Empress Yang Zhi ( 楊芷 ) ( 259 - -292 ) , courtesy name Jilan ( 季蘭 ) , nickname Nanyin ( 男胤 ) , formally Empress Wudao ( 武悼皇后 , literally `` the martial and fearful empress '' ) was an empress of Jin Dynasty ( 265 - -420 ) .
Lionel Bradley Pett ( November 12 , 1909- 2003 ) was a Canadian biochemist and nutritionist .
Anne - François - Charles Trelliard or Treillard or Treilhard , born 7 February 1764 -- died 14 May 1832 , joined the cavalry of the French Royal Army as a cadet gentleman in 1780 .
Angharad Llwyd ( 15 April 1780 -- 16 October 1866 ) was a Welsh antiquary and a prizewinner at the National Eisteddfod of Wales .
Henry Smith Leiper ( 17 September 1891 -- 22 January 1975 ) was a missionary .
Robert Wellbeloved Scott , born Robert Wellbeloved ( 15 July 1803 -- 21 February 1856 ) was the Liberal Member of Parliament ( MP ) for Walsall , England from 1841 to 1847 .
Gerard Legh ( died 1563 ) was an English lawyer , known as a writer on heraldry .
Lewis Greifer ( 19 December 1915 in London , England -- 18 March 2003 ) was a writer for television , film , and radio .
Paddy Crosbie ( 1 October 1913 -- 2 September 1982 ) was the Irish creator of the radio and television programmes The School Around The Corner and Back To School .
Blessed Pio Alberto del Corona , O.P. ( 5 July 1837 - 15 August 1912 ) , born Alberto del Corona , was a Roman Catholic Italian archbishop and the founder of the Dominican Sisters of the Holy Spirit .
René Marcelin ( 12 June 1885 - 24 September 1914 ) was a French physical chemist , who died in World War I at a young age .
Camillo Guerra ( Naples 21 May 1797 -- 10 March 1874 Naples ) was an Italian painter , active mainly in Naples , Italy .
John Aloysius Blake ( 1826 -- 22 May 1887 ) was an Irish nationalist politician and Member of Parliament .
John Laney ( died 1633 ) , of Cratfield and Ipswich , Suffolk , was an English politician .
Sir Ifor Williams ( 16 April 1881 -- 4 November 1965 ) was a Welsh scholar who laid the foundations for the academic study of Old Welsh , particularly early Welsh poetry .
İsmail Selen ( 1931 , Bolu - 23 May 1991 , Ankara ) was a retired general in the Turkish Gendarmerie .
Charles Ransford died on 11 July 1886 at The Hospital of St. Cross in Winchester , Hampshire , England .
Charles Stedman ( 1753 - -1812 ) was a British Army officer who fought in the American War of Independence and afterwards wrote a detailed history on the conflict .
Edvard Engelsaas ( 17 November 1872 -- 3 August 1902 ) was a Norwegian speed skater and world champion .
Chrysocheir ( Greek : Χρυσόχειρ ) , also known as Chrysocheres , Chrysocheris , or Chrysocheiros ( Χρυσόχερης/Χρυσόχερις/Χρυσόχειρος ) , all meaning `` goldhand '' , was the last leader of the Paulician principality of Tephrike from 863 to 872 .
Ulrich , 10th Prince Kinsky of Wchinitz and Tettau ( German : Ulrich Ferdinand Adolf Antonius Bonaventura Maria Fürst Kinsky von Wchinitz und Tettau ; 15 August 1893 -- 19 December 1938 ) was the titular pretender Prince Kinsky of Wchinitz and Tettau .
Joaquin Alberto Vargas y Chávez ( 9 February 1896 -- 30 December 1982 ) was a noted Peruvian painter of pin - up girls .
Sim On ( 1375 -- 18 January 1419 ( the 23rd day of the 12th lunar month 1418 ) ) was a Prime Minister or Chief State Councillor of the Korean Joseon Dynasty from September 1418 to December 1418 and the father of a Queen and father - in - law to King Sejong .
Nicholas II of Niemodlin ( Polish : Mikołaj II Niemodliński ; c. 1462 -- 27 June 1497 ) , was a Duke of Opole - Brzeg - Strzelce - Niemodlin in 1476 ( as co - ruler of his father ) and sole Duke of Niemodlin from 1476 until his death .
Ralph Churton ( 1754 - -1831 ) was an English churchman and academic , archdeacon of St David 's and a biographer .
Ramananda Chatterjee ( Bengali : রামানন্দ চট্টোপাধ্যায় ) ( 29 May 1865 -- 30 September 1943 ) was founder , editor , and owner of the Calcutta based magazine , the Modern Review .
James Hamilton Siree Clarke ( 25 January 1840 -- 9 July 1912 ) , better known as Hamilton Clarke , was an English conductor , composer and organist .
Auxentius of Mopsuestia ( died 360 ) was bishop of Mopsuestia , and is a saint in the Eastern Orthodox and Roman Catholic churches .
Jean Gillon ( 1919 - -2007 ) was a Brazilian furniture designer .
Anas ibn Malik ibn Nadar al - Khazraji Al - Ansari ( Arabic : أنس بن مالك الخزرجي الأنصاري‎ , c.612 - 712 , or died 709 ) was a well - known sahabi ( companion ) of the Islamic prophet Muhammad .
Hanifa Safi ( died 13 July 2012 ) was the regional head of the Women 's Affairs Ministry for Laghman Province , Afghanistan , since 2008 .
Henry John May ( 16 July 1867 -- 19 November 1939 ) was a British co - operative movement activist .
Duan Yuanfei ( 段元妃 ) ( died 396 ) , formally Empress Cheng'ai ( 成哀皇后 , literally `` the successful and lamentable empress '' ) , was an empress of the Chinese / Xianbei state Later Yan .
Branko Gavella ( 29 July 1885 -- 8 April 1962 ) was a Croatian theatre director , critic and essayist .
Stephen Peer ( 1840 - 1887 ) was a tightrope walker who , though he completed the feat successfully many times , fell to his death while walking a tightrope over Niagara Falls .
Evelyn Greeley ( 1888 - -1975 ) was a prominent actress in the early years of silent film , appearing in approximately 30 films from 1915 to 1922 .
Johannes Schenck ( or Schenk , 3 June 1660 - -after 1712 ) was a Dutch musician and composer .
James Erskine , 6th Earl of Buchan ( died 1640 ) , was the eldest son of John Erskine , Earl of Mar , by his second wife , Lady Margaret Stuart , daughter of Esme Stewart , duke of Lennox .
Allan Maconochie , Lord Meadowbank FRSE FSA(Scot ) ( 1748 - -1816 ) was a Scottish advocate , academic jurist , judge and agriculturalist .
Heinrich Feisthauer ( 14 September 1898 -- 11 November 1964 ) was an opponent of the Nazi regime and survivor of Sachsenhausen concentration camp of Silesian origin .
Katarina Asplund ( 1690 - 1758 ) , was a Finnish pietist .
Luigi Piacenza ( 22 March 1935 -- 14 November 2009 ) was an Italian botanist , with expertise in ethnobotany and paleobotany .
Margo MacDonald ( née Aitken ; 19 April 1943 -- 4 April 2014 ) was a Scottish teacher , broadcaster and politician .
Karl Friedrich Köppen ( 26 April 1808 -- 26 April 1863 ) was a German teacher and political journalist .
Ruggero Mastroianni ( 7 November 1929 -- 9 September 1996 ) was an Italian film editor ; critic Tony Sloman has called him `` arguably , the finest Italian film editor of his generation . ''
Georgios Sakellarios ( Greek : Γεώργιος Σακελλάριος ; 1765 - -1838 ) was a chief physician at the court of Ali Pasha .
Wang Hongyi ( 王弘義 ) ( died 694 ) was a secret police official during the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty and Wu Zetian 's Zhou Dynasty .
Clifton Cappie Towle ( 1888 - -1946 ) , founding member of The Anthropological Society of New South Wales in 1928 with William Walford Thorpe .
Edwin Duncan Sandys , Baron Duncan - Sandys ( /ˈsændz/ ) CH PC ( 24 January 1908 -- 26 November 1987 ) was a British politician and minister in successive Conservative governments in the 1950s and 1960s .
Johannes Hähle ( 15 February 1906 -- 10 June 1944 ) was a German military photographer during World War II .
Crispian St. Peters ( 5 April 1939 -- 8 June 2010 ) was an English pop singer - songwriter , best known for his work in the 1960s , particularly his 1966 hits , `` The Pied Piper '' and `` You Were on My Mind . ''
Domingo Bucci ( San Carlos Centro 1894 - Arrecifes 1933 ) was an Argentine racing driver .
Dr Charles Kearns Deane Tanner ( 20 September 1849 - 21 April 1901 ) was an Irish surgeon and politician .
Joseph Rodes Buchanan ( 1814 in Frankfort , Kentucky -- 1899 ) was an American physician and professor of physiology at the Eclectic Medical Institute in Covington , Kentucky .
Professor Nasir Imanguliyev died in 1998 , in Baku .
Odd Grønvold ( 8 September 1907 -- 18 February 1992 ) was a Norwegian royal servant .
Graeme McMahon ( 1940 -- 1 July 2014 ) was an Australian rules football player and executive , best known as chairman of Essendon from 1997 to 2003 .
Lieutenant Colonel Charles Terence Chichele Plowden ( 6 February 1883 - 13 July 1956 ) was a British army officer , military administrator and diplomat who served as political agent of the Baluchistan and Resident and Chief Commissioner of Coorg from 1933 to 1937 .
Timothy Akis , born around 1944 in Tsembaga village , Simbai Valley , Madang Province , Papua New Guinea , died in 1984 , was a Papua New Guinean artist .
John Conrad Otto ( born near Woodbridge , New Jersey , 15 March 1774 ; died in Philadelphia , 26 June 1844 ) was a United States physician .
Imane Khalifeh ( 1955 - -1995 ) was a Lebanese educator and peace activist .
Hal Downey ( 1877 - 1959 ) was an American hematologist .
Anna of Eppstein - Königstein ( Königstein , 1481 -- Stolberg , 7 August 1538 ) was the daughter of Philip I of Eppstein - Königstein and his wife , Louise de la Marck .
Saint Genebald ( Genebaldus , Genebandus ) ( French : Génebaud , Génebaut , Guénebauld ) ( died 550 AD ) was a Frankish bishop of Laon .
Don Diego de San Francisco Tehuetzquititzin ( sometimes called Tehuetzquiti or Tehuetzqui ) ( died 1554 ) was the 16th tlatoani and second governor of Tenochtitlan .
David Basnett , Baron Basnett ( 9 February 1924 -- 25 January 1989 ) was a prominent British trade union leader .
John Dalrymple , 5th Earl of Stair ( 1720 - -1789 ) was a Scottish soldier and politician .
Herbert James Craig CBE ( 30 September 1869 - 18 March 1934 ) was a British Liberal Party politician , businessman and barrister .
Ted Politz ( 28 July 1889 -- 14 February 1967 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Philip Albright Small Franklin ( 1 February 1871 - - 14 August 1939 ) was president and chairman of International Mercantile Marine Company ( IMM ) from 1916 to 1936 .
Carlo Somigliana ( 20 September 1860 -- 20 June 1955 ) was an Italian mathematician and a classical mathematical physicist , faithful member of the school of Enrico Betti and Eugenio Beltrami .
Lawrence Malcolm Allison ( 1894 - -1974 ) was a maker of gliders and was a pioneer aviator .
Alf Murray ( 1914 -- 12 March 1999 ) was an Irish Gaelic footballer who played as a right wing - forward for the Armagh senior team .
Friedrich Wilhelm Konow ( 11 July 1842 , in Mechow -- 18 March 1908 , in Teschendorf ) was a German entomologist who specialised in Hymenoptera especially Tenthredinidae .
Sir Salathiel Lovell ( 1631/2 - -1713 ) was an English judge , Recorder of London , an ancient and bencher of Gray 's Inn , and a Baron of the Exchequer .
Myron Stout ( 1908 - -1987 ) was an American abstract painter whose geometric paintings and drawings bridged the styles of Abstract Expressionism and Minimalism .
Nir Poraz ( 14 May 1971 -- 14 October 1994 ) ( Hebrew : ניר פורז ) was an Israeli Defence Forces Captain who was killed in action by Hamas during the failed October 14 , 1994 rescue mission for IDF soldier Nachshon Wachsman in Bir Nabbalah .
Oleg Tronko ( 20 June 1918 , Kiev , Russian Empire - 27 February 1939 , Rome , Italy ) was a Catholic convert from Orthodoxy and a seminarist from Russicum .
Takis Kanellopoulos ( Greek : Τάκης Κανελλόπουλος ; 26 October 1933 -- 21 September 1990 ) was a Greek film director and screenwriter .
Liu Jianfeng ( 劉建鋒 ) ( d. 896 ) , courtesy name Ruiduan ( 銳端 ) , was a warlord late in the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty , who controlled Wu'an Circuit ( 武安 , headquartered in modern Changsha , Hunan ) from 894 to his death in 896 .
Marjorie Grice - Hutchinson ( 26 May 1908 -- 12 April 2003 ) was an English economist , best known for her work on the history of economic thought in Spain , and particularly that of the late Scholastic School of Salamanca .
Guy Middleton Powell ( 14 December 1907 -- 30 July 1973 ) , better known as Guy Middleton , was an English film character actor .
Heather Stohler ( 29 November 1979 -- 11 May 2008 ) was an American model .
William Henry Hudson ( 4 August 1841 -- 18 August 1922 ) was an author , naturalist , and ornithologist .
Robert Connell ( 1871 - -1957 ) was a clergyman and politician in British Columbia .
John Francis Toye ( 27 January 1883 -- 13 October 1964 ) was an English music critic , teacher , writer and educational administrator .
Lieutenant General Sagat Singh , PVSM ( 14 July 1918 -- 26 September 2001 ) was a three - star General in the Indian Army notable for his participation in liberation of Goa and later in Bangladesh .
General Lázár Mészáros ( English : Lazarus Mészáros ) ( 20 February 1796 in Baja -- 16 November 1858 in Eywood ) , was the Minister of War during the 1848 Hungarian Revolution .
Friedrich Hopfner ( 28 October 1881 -- 5 September 1949 ) was an Austrian geodesist , geophysicist and planetary scientist .
Bartolomeo Panciatichi ( 1507 - 1582 ) was an Italian humanist and politician .
Alessio de Marchis or il Marchis ( Naples , 1684 - 1752 , Perugia ) was an Italian painter of the early 18th century , active mainly in Rome and Urbino , mainly as a landscape painter .
James Halman ( c. 1639 -- 23 December 1702 ) was an academic of the University of Cambridge .
Humphrey FitzAlan , 15th Earl of Arundel , 5th Baron Maltravers ( 30 January 1429 -- 24 April 1438 ) .
Air Commodore Arthur Vere Harvey , Baron Harvey of Prestbury CBE ( 31 January 1906 - -5 April 1994 ) was a British Conservative politician , and Member of Parliament ( MP ) for 26 years .
Arthur Lismer , CC ( 27 June 1885 -- 23 March 1969 ) was an English - Canadian painter and member of the Group of Seven .
Louis Adamic ( Slovene : Alojz Adamič ) ( 23 March 1898 -- 4 September 1951 ) was a Slovene - American author and translator , mostly known for writing about and advocating for ethnic diversity of America .
Reginald Grey , 3rd Baron Grey de Ruthyn ( c. 1362 -- 30 September 1440 ) , a powerful Welsh marcher lord , succeeded to the title on his father 's death in July 1388 .
Arthur Clarence Pillsbury ( 1870 - -1946 ) was a United States photographer , best known for landscapes of Yosemite National Park , photos of the 1906 San Francisco earthquake , and time lapse photography of flowers .
Alexander Bliss ( 29 December 1827 -- 30 April 1896 ) was assistant quartermaster general of the Union forces and a Colonel in the United States Army during the American Civil War .
Julio César Britos Vázquez ( 18 May 1926 -- 27 March 1998 ) was an Uruguayan footballer , who played for CA Peñarol and Real Madrid .
Pierre Grimod du Fort ( 1692 -- October 1748 ) was a fermier général and art collector under Louis XV , and a member of the famous Grimaud family .
Francesco Fracanzano ( 1612 - -1656 ) was an Italian painter who participated in the Masaniello rebellion .
Ataur Rahman Khan died in Dhaka on 7 December 1991 and is buried beside Parliament .
Haika Grossman ( Hebrew : חייקה גרוסמן‎ , 20 November 1919 -- 26 May 1996 ) was an Israeli politician and member of Knesset .
Carlo Fassi ( 20 December 1929 -- 20 March 1997 ) was an Italian figure skater and international coach whose students included several World and Olympic champions .
Prof Robert Percival Cook FRSE ( 1906 - 1989 ) was an Australian - born biochemist .
Joseph W. Dailey ( 17 February 1917 -- 5 July 2007 ) served as the fifth Sergeant Major of the Marine Corps from 1 August 1969 until he retired from active duty in the Marine Corps on 31 January 1973 .
Sir Harry Ord died on 20 August 1885 from heart attack .
Christian Henrik Arendrup ( March 25 , 1837 -- 1913 ) was Governor - General of The Danish West Indies , from 1881 to 1893 .
Devanand Swami ( 1803 - -1854 ) was an Indian swami .
Milos Konopasek ( died in Boston , Massachusetts , 9 January 2002 ) was a Czechoslovakia - born mechanical engineer best known as the creator of TK !
León Zuckert ( 4 May 1904 , Poltava -- 29 May 1992 , Toronto ) was a Canadian composer , conductor , arranger , violinist , violist and radio pioneer of Ukrainian descent .
Gaspare Bazzani ( 21 April 1701 - -6 May 1780 ) was an Italian painter active in Reggio Emilia as a painter of vedute or landscapes , as well as a scenic designer .
Ștefan Tomșa or Ștefan VIII ( Polish : Stefan VIII Tomża ) ( d. 5 May 1564 in Lwów ) was the ruler of Moldavia in 1563 and 1564 .
Ardeshir Cowasjee ( 13 April 1926 -- 24 November 2012 ) ( Urdu : اردشير کاوﺳﺠﻰ‎ ) was a Pakistani newspaper columnist , social activist , and philanthropist .
Aaron Cleveland ( 29 October 1715 -- 17 August 1757 Philadelphia ) was a clergyman .
Berit Wallenberg ( 1902 - -1995 ) was a Swedish archaeologist , art historian , photographer , and donor .
Mykhajlo Levitsky ( or Mykhailo Levytskyi ( Ukrainian : Михайло Левицький , Polish : Michał Lewicki ) ) ; 17 February , 1774 -- 14 January , 1858 ) was the Metropolitan Archbishop of the Ukrainian Greek Catholic Church from 1816 until his death in 1858 and a Cardinal of the Catholic Church .
Oswald Pryor ( 15 February 1881 -- 13 June 1971 ) was a South Australian cartoonist noted for his depictions of life in the Copper triangle , particularly of miners from Cornwall .
Zlata Petković ( 11 February 1954 -- 3 December 2012 ) was a Serbian actress , model , television host and singer .
Ananias Dare ( c. 1560 -- June 27 , 1587 , legal death ) was the husband of Eleanor White , whom he married at St Bride 's Church in Fleet Street , City of London .
Robert Parry Nisbet JP DL ( 1793 -- 31 May 1882 ) was a British public man .
Philip Silver ( 1909 - -1999 ) , of New York City , was a philatelist who specialized in the field of air mail stamps , known as aerophilately .
Micheál Ó Mordha ( English : Michael Moore ) ( c.1639 - 1723 ) was an Irish priest , philosopher and educationalist .
Harry Lampe ( 14 September 1874 -- 25 August 1939 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with the South Melbourne Football Club in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Nguyễn Quyền ( 1869 - -1941 ) was a Vietnamese scholar - gentry anti - colonial revolutionary activist who advocated independence from French colonial rule .
Nicolás Francés , ( died 1468 ) was a Spanish painter and miniaturist .
Margaret Oliphant Wilson Oliphant ( née Margaret Oliphant Wilson ) ( 4 April 1828 -- 25 June 1897 ) , was a Scottish novelist and historical writer , who usually wrote as Mrs. Oliphant .
Adnan Kahveci ( 20 February 1949 in Sürmene , Trabzon Province -- 5 February 1993 in Gerede ) was a noted Turkish politician who served as a key advisor to Prime Minister Turgut Özal throughout the 1980s .
Nigel Heseltine ( 3 July 1916 -- 1995 ) was an English author , of travel books , short stories , plays , and poetry , and worked as an Agronomist for the UN FAO .
Atholl Fleming MBE ( 6 December 1894 -- 6 May 1972 ) was a British actor and an Australian radio personality .
Walter Davies ( 15 July 1761 -- 5 December 1849 ) , commonly known by his bardic name Gwallter Mechain ( `` Walter of Mechain '' ) , was a Welsh poet , editor , translator , antiquary and Anglican clergyman .
Robert Satanowski ( January 20 , 1918 -- August 9 , 1997 ) was a Polish general who later became a major European orchestra and opera conductor .
John Robert Procter , ( 16 March 1844 in Mason County , Kentucky -- 12 December 1903 in Washington , D.C. ) was an American geologist and civil service reformer .
Fabrizio Castello ( 1562 - -1617 ) was an Italian painter of Genoese origin settled in Spain .
Sophia of Bavaria ( Czech : Žofie Bavorská ; German : Sophie von Bayern ; 1376 -- 4 November 1428 ) was a Queen of Bohemia and the spouse of Wenceslaus , King of Bohemia and King of the Romans .
Lars Knutson Liestøl ( 13 June 1839 -- 15 December 1912 ) was the Norwegian Minister of Auditing 1888 - 1889 , as well as head of the Ministry of the Interior in 1888 .
Mary Ann Rundall ( -- 2 October 1839 ) was a British educational writer who developed history books based on memorising facts using symbols .
Abdessadeq Cheqara ( 1931 -- October 31 , 1998 ) ( in Arabic : عبد الصادق شقارة ) was a Moroccan singer of traditional Andalusian classical music and Moroccan folk music .
Trahaearn ap Caradog ( died 1081 ) was a King of Gwynedd .
Judah Uziel ( d. 1634 , Venice , probably ; Jewish Encyclopedia of 1971 says he died ca . 1600 ) was an Italian scholar of the 16th century , born in Spain .
Count Adolf III of Nassau - Wiesbaden - Idstein ( by a different way of counting : Adolf IV ; 10 November 1443 -- 6 July 1511 ) was a son of Count John II of Nassau - Wiesbaden - Idstein and his wife Maria of Nassau - Dillenburg ( 1463 - -1504 ) .
Third Lieutenant Leonidas I. Robinson ( unknown -- June 6 , 1891 ) was the first graduate of the School of Instruction of the Revenue Cutter Service to die in the line of duty .
Sir Edward Maunde Thompson , GCB ( 1840 -- 14 September 1929 ) was a British palaeographer and Principal Librarian and first Director of the British Museum .
Henrik Have ( 14 March 1946 -- 12 September 2014 ) was a Danish author and artist .
François Delange ( 1935 - June 2007 ) was a Belgian physician and researcher who contributed to thyroid research .
Isaac Woodbridge Riley ( born New York City , 20 May 1869 ; died September 1933 ) was a United States historian of philosophy whose studies of Mormonism and Christian Science made him a focus of controversy .
John Buckle Barlee ( 2 June 1831 -- August 1870 ) was an English rower who won the Silver Goblets at Henley Royal Regatta .
Charles Terront ( 9 April 1857 -- 31 October 1932 ) was the first major French cycling star .
Edward Frank Wise ( 3 July 1885 -- 5 November 1933 ) , commonly known as E.F.Wise or Frank Wise was an economist , Civil Servant at the National Insurance Commission , War Office and Ministry of Food and Board of Trade .
Doug Gillespie ( 13 December 1887 -- 6 January 1946 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played for Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Robert O'Dwyer ( in Gaelic : Riobárd Ó Duibhir ) ( 27 January 1862 -- 6 January 1949 ) was an Irish composer mainly known for having written one of the first operas in the Irish language .
Alan Archibald Campbell - Swinton FRSE ( 18 October 1863 - 19 February 1930 ) was a Scottish consulting electrical engineer , who provided the theoretical basis for the electronic television , two decades before the technology existed to implement it .
Yang Wenguang ( 楊文廣 ) ( died 1074 ) was a general in ancient China 's Northern Song Dynasty .
Brigadier General Neil Douglas Findlay CB ( 7 May 1859 -- 10 September 1914 ) was a British Army general .
Vic Truman ( 21 December 1899 -- 7 November 1976 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton and Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Giovanni Battista Mingardi ( Born Padua , died Venice 1796 ) was an Italian painter , active in a late - Baroque style mainly in Venice and its mainland territories .
Sir Charles Holroyd ( 9 April 1861 -- 17 November 1917 ) was an English artist and curator .
Pandolfo I Malatesta ( c. 1267 -- 6 April 1326 ) , son of Malatesta da Verucchio , was an Italian condottiero and Lord of Rimini from 1317 .
Wilhelm Phillip Daniel Schulz ( 6 March 1805 -- 1 August 1877 ) , also known as Guillermo Schulz , was a German mine engineer and geologist who spent most of his professional life in Spain .
Sir Chittampalam Abraham Gardiner ( 6 January 1899 -- December 1960 ) was a Ceylon Tamil businessman and member of the Senate of Ceylon .
Zia Fariduddin Dagar ( 15 June 1932 -- 8 May 2013 ) was an Indian classical vocalist in the Dhrupad , the oldest existing form of north Indian classical music ( Hindustani classical music ) and part of the Dagar family of musicians .
Taras Kiktyov ( Ukrainian : Тарас Юрійович Кіктьов ; 7 November 1986 -- 16 July 2012 ) was a Ukrainian professional football player .
Hubertus Czernin ( more fully , Hubertus Alexander Felix Franz Maria Czernin von und zu Chudenitz ; 17 January 1956 -- 10 June 2006 ) was an Austrian investigative journalist .
Anne Commire ( 11 August 1939 -- 23 February 2012 ) was an American playwright and editor .
James Howe McClure ( 1851 -- 1909 ) was a Scottish rugby football player and along with his brother George Buchanan McClure , has the distinction of being the first twin to be capped in international rugby .
Gerald James Whitrow ( 9 June 1912 -- 2 June 2000 ) was a British mathematician , cosmologist and science historian .
Mafalda Salvatini ( 17 October 1886 - 13 June 1971 ) was an Italian opera singer who was primarily active in Germany during the first half of the 20th century .
József Jung , ( 1734 , Jihlava , Margraviate of Moravia -- 22 August 1808 , Pest ) was a Hungarian architect .
Francis William Topham ( Leeds 15 April 1808 -- 31 March 1877 Córdoba ) was an English watercolourist and engraver .
Kishore Pawar ( c. 1926 -- 2 January 2013 ) was an Indian trade union leader and politician .
Dominick Labino ( 1910 - -1987 ) was an internationally known scientist , inventor , artist and master craftsman in glass .
Joe Wark ( 9 October 1947 -- 1 October 2015 ) was a Scottish professional footballer who spent his entire professional career with Motherwell , making 464 appearances in the Scottish Football League .
Prahalad Chunnilal Vaidya ( P.C.Vaidya ; 23 May 1918 -- 12 March 2010 ) , was an Indian physicist and mathematician , renowned for his instrumental work in general theory of relativity .
Sir Matthew John Tierney , Bart . , M.D. ( 24 November 1776 -- 28 October 1845 ) was an Irish surgeon who became Physician - in - Ordinary to Kings George IV and William IV of the United Kingdom .
Kurt Eberling , Sr . ( 17 June 1930 -- 6 March 2008 ) was a German - American chef and the inventor of SpaghettiOs .
Sara Anne McLagan ( c. 1856 -- 20 March 1924 ) was the first Canadian woman newspaper editor .
Pandit Raghunath Panigrahi ( 10 August 1932 -- 25 August 2013 ) was an Indian classical singer and music director .
Mikko Ampuja ( 25 October 1882 , Viipurin maalaiskunta - 15 September 1947 ) was a Finnish blacksmith and politician .
Johann Baptist Singenberger ( John Singenberger ) ( 25 May 1848\ -- 29 May 1924 ) was a Swiss composer , music teacher , editor and publisher .
Karma Tensung ( died 1611 ) , in full Karma Tensung Wangpo ( Wylie : Kar ma bstan srung dbang po ) , was a king of Tsang ( West Central Tibet ) who probably reigned from 1599 to 1611 .
Maksym Slavinsky ( also as Slavynsky Ukrainian : Максим Антонович Славинський ; 12 August 1868 in Stavyshche , Kiev Governorate - 23 November 1945 in Kiev ) was a Ukrainian journalist , political and public figure , diplomat and statesman .
Bain Hugh Clapperton ( 18 May 1788 -- 13 April 1827 ) was a Scottish naval officer and explorer of West and Central Africa .
Ashbel Green Simonton ( January 20 , 1833 -- December 9 , 1867 ) was a North - American Presbyterian minister and missionary , the first missionary to settle a Protestant church in Brazil , Igreja Presbiteriana do Brasil ( Presbyterian Church of Brazil )
Sir John Wray , 2nd Baronet ( 27 November 1586 -- 31 December 1655 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1614 and 1648 .
Shi Chaoyi ( 史朝義 ) ( died 763 ) was the final emperor of the Yan state that was established in rebellion against the Chinese Tang Dynasty .
Felix of Bourges ( died c. 580 ) was a bishop of Bourges who later became recognized as a saint .
Da'ud Abu al - Fadl ( 1161 - -1242 ) was a Karaite Jewish physician who lived in Egypt in the twelfth century CE . He born at Cairo in 1161 and died there about 1242 .
Ephraim Udall ( died 1647 ) was an English Royalist divine .
Sutan Sjahrir ( 5 March 1909 -- 9 April 1966 ) , an avant garde and idealistic Indonesian intellectual , was a revolutionary independence leader .
Harold Bennett ( 17 September 1899 -- 15 September 1981 ) was an English actor best remembered for having played ' Young Mr. Grace ' in the 1970s British sitcom Are You Being Served ? .
Abdullahi Qarshe ( Somali : Cabdullaahi Qarshe , Arabic : عبدالله قارشي‎ ) ( 1924 - -1994 ) was a Somali musician , poet and playwright known as the `` Father of Somali music '' .
