Johannes de Quadris ( Quatris ) ( before 1410 -- 1457 ? ) was an Italian composer of the early Renaissance .
Sanda Min Hla ( Burmese : စန္ဒာမင်းလှ , pronounced : ( sàɴdà mɪ́ɴ l̥a̰ ) ; died c. 1363 ) was the queen consort of three kings of Hanthawaddy Kingdom , and the real palace power behind the throne .
Seitzhan Omarov ( 1907 - 1985 ) was a Kazakh writer , the author of numerous short stories , sketches , fairy tales .
Patrick Musimu ( 12 October 1970 -- 21 July 2011 ) was a Belgian freediver , sport business manager , marketing and event manager , and physiotherapist .
Jørgen Boberg ( 2 October 1940 -- 24 August 2009 ) was a self - taught Surrealist Danish painter and illustrator .
John Plessington ( c. 1637 -- 19 July 1679 ) , also known as John Plesington , William Scarisbrick and William Pleasington , was an English Catholic priest who was executed by the English Crown for violating the ban on the presence of Catholic priests in the kingdom .
Basiliscus ( Latin : Flavius Basiliscus Augustus ; Greek : Βασιλίσκος ) ( d. 476/477 ) was Byzantine Emperor from 475 to 476 .
Sir Alexander Bryce , KCH ( died 1832 ) , was a major - general and colonel - commandant Royal Engineers .
Ghulam Mohammed Abdul Khader ( died 1993 ) was the seventh prince of the House of Arcot .
Thomas Joseph Banks ( 1828 - -1896 ) , sometimes known as `` Thomas John Banks '' , was a British portrait and landscape painter .
István Oláh ( 16 December 1926 -- 15 December 1985 ) was a Hungarian military officer and politician , who served as Minister of Defence from 1984 until his death .
Heinz Bosl ( 21 November 1946 -- 12 June 1975 ) was a German ballet dancer .
Josef Dörries ( 7 June 1923 -- 9 July 2007 ) was a highly decorated Unteroffizier in the Wehrmacht during World War II and a Stabsfeldwebel in the Bundeswehr .
Ramón S. Sabat ( born 1902 , Cienfuegos - died 1986 , Miami , Florida ) was a musician and the Cuban founder of the pioneering record label Panart , which he established in 1944 , eventually gaining international sale of its releases .
Laurentius Suslyga or Laurence Suslyga ( Polish : Wawrzyniec Suslyga ) ( 1570 - -1640 ) , was a Polish Jesuit historian , chronologist , and an author of Baroque visual poetry .
Mai ( c.1751 - 1780 ) , mistakenly known as Omai in Britain , was a young Ra'iatean man who became the second Pacific Islander to visit Europe , after Ahu - toru who was brought to Paris by Bougainville in 1768 .
Yazdin ( died 627 ) was a Iranian aristocrat , who served as the financial minister of the Sasanian king Khosrau II ( r. 590 - 628 ) .
James Leonard Plimpton ( 1828 , Medfield , Massachusetts - 1911 ) was an American inventor who is known for changing the skating world with his patented roller skates in 1863 .
Dwight Fiske ( 1892 - -1959 ) was an American nightclub entertainer and pianist noted for his saucy stories and risque recordings .
Ferenc Sas ( 16 August 1915 -- 3 September 1988 ) , born as Ferenc Sohn , in Argentina known as Francisco `` Sas '' Sohn , was a Hungarian football player .
Oscar Fay Adams ( 1855 - 1919 ) was a United States editor and author .
James Wright Gordon ( 1809 -- December 1853 ) , usually referred to as J. Wright Gordon , was a Whig politician from the U.S. state of Michigan .
M. Wylie Blanchet , née Muriel Wylie Liffiton ( 2 May 1891 -- 9 September 1961 ) was a Canadian travel writer .
Vicente Quesada ( 1812 - 1877 ) was a Chilean lawyer and lawmaker .
Frederic , Count of Luna ( Spanish : Fadrique ; c. 1401 -- 29 May 1438 ) , was a contender for the crown of Aragon .
Walter Bayley ( 1529 - -1593 ) , was an English physician .
Laurence Chaderton ( c. September 1536 -- 13 November 1640 ) was an English Puritan divine , and one of the translators of the King James Version of the Bible .
Max Bartel ( 1879- 2 July 1914 , Nürnberg ) was a German entomologist Max Bartel was an insect dealer ( Insektenhändler ) in Berlin .
Richard de Bury ( 24 January 1287 -- 14 April 1345 ) , also known as Richard Aungerville or Aungervyle , was an English priest , teacher , bishop , writer , and bibliophile .
Madame Therese ( floruit 1706 - 1729 ) , was the professional name of a famous Dutch brothel keeper .
Hermann Weinsberg , also known as Hermann von Weinsberg ( 1518 - -1597 ) was a city councillor in Cologne and a diarist whose autobiographical writings , long obscure , are now considered to be of historical importance .
Lucy Barfield ( 2 November 1935 -- 3 May 2003 ) was the godchild of C.S. Lewis .
Georgius Pelino ( fl . 1438 - -1463 ) was a Catholic priest , the abbot of Ratac Abbey and diplomat of Skanderbeg and Venetian Republic .
Gary Frisch ( 22 January 1969 -- 10 February 2007 ) was co - founder of the Gaydar website .
Walter Russell Bowie ( October 8 , 1882 -- April 23 , 1969 ) , was a priest , author , editor , educator , hymn writer , and lecturer in the Episcopal Church .
Elijah ben Solomon Abraham ha - Kohen ( died 1729 ) was dayyan of Smyrna , almoner and preacher .
Wolraad Woltemade ( c.1708 -- 1 June 1773 ) was a Cape Dutch dairy farmer , who died while rescuing sailors from the wreck of the ship De Jonge Thomas in Table Bay on 1 June 1773 .
Mathai Manjooran ( 13 October 1912 -- 14 January 1970 ) was an Indian independence activist from Kerala , socialist revolutionary , Member of Parliament , Minister of Labour ( economics ) in the second E.M.S. Namboodiripad communist ministry , and above all a proponent for the formation of the Kerala State .
Gustav Borgen ( born 10 June 1865 , died 16 August 1926 ) was a Norwegian photographer .
Juan Bautista Paz ( 1772 - -1844 ) was an Argentinian jurist and lawyer , a member of the National Congress of 1819 and the General Conference of 1824 , and several times cabinet minister and deputy governor of Tucumán Province during the first half of the nineteenth century .
Desmond Dupré ( 19 December 1916 , London -- 16 August 1974 , Tonbridge , Kent ) was an English lutenist and a prominent figure in the 20th century revival of early music .
Jean - Baptiste Capronnier ( 1 February 1814 -- 31 July 1891 ) was a Belgian stained glass painter .
Jeremias Drexel S.J. ( also known as Hieremias Drexelius or Drechsel ) ( August 15 , 1581 -- 19 April 1638 ) was a Jesuit writer of devotional literature and a professor of the humanities and rhetoric .
Elisha Crymes ( c 1614 - March 1690 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1646 and 1661 .
Joseph P. Overton ( 4 January 1960 -- 30 June 2003 ) was a Senior Vice President of the Mackinac Center for Public Policy .
John Sulyard ( born by 1518 - 1575 ) , of Wetherden , Suffolk , was an English politician .
Francesco Ghittoni ( 1855 - -1928 ) was an Italian painter , mainly of genre paintings of the life of rural workers , but also portraits , sacred subjects , and , late in life , landscapes .
Isaac Klein ( September 5 , 1905 -- 1979 ) was a prominent rabbi and halakhic authority within Conservative Judaism .
Jane Lewson ( née Vaughan ) ( 1700 - 1816 ) , commonly known as Lady Lewson , was an eccentric centenarian .
William Seth Agar ( 25 December 1815 -- 23 August 1872 ) was an English Catholic canon .
Khedrup Gelek Pelzang , 1st Panchen Lama ( 1385 - -1438 CE ) -- better known as Khedrup Je -- was one of the main disciples of Je Tsongkhapa , whose reforms to the Kadam tradition of Atiśa are considered the beginnings of the Gelug school of Tibetan Buddhism .
Eric Irvin ( 30 November 1908 -- 1 July 1993 ) was an Australian writer and historian of Australian theatre .
Zachary Crofton ( 1626 - -1672 ) was an Anglo - Irish nonconforming minister and controversialist , in England from the 1640s .
Paul Behncke ( 13 August 1869 -- 4 January 1937 ) was a German admiral during the First World War , most notable for his command of the Third Battle Squadron of the German High Seas Fleet during the Battle of Jutland .
Reverend Father Raoul Desribes ( born in 1856 , died in 1940 ) was a French Jesuit archaeologist notable for his work on prehistory in Lebanon , particularly the archaeological site of Minet Dalieh at Ras Beirut .
Shaul Amor ( Hebrew : שאול עמור‎ , 24 December 1940 -- 2 October 2004 ) was an Israeli politician who served as a Minister without Portfolio between January and July 1999 .
Roberto Parga ( 4 February 1937 -- 18 March 2015 ) was an Uruguayan judge who served on the Supreme Court from 2000 to 2007 .
Jimmy Holiday ( 24 July 1934 , Sallis , Mississippi -- 15 February 1987 ) was an American R&B singer and songwriter .
George Tunstal Redmayne , more usually G T Redmayne ( 1840 - 1912 ) , was the youngest of four sons of Giles Redmayne and his wife , Margareta Robey .
Sir Hugh Paterson , 2nd Baronet ( circa 1685 -- 23 March 1777 ) was a Scottish Jacobite .
Pomponio Nenna ( baptized 13 June 1556 -- 25 July 1608 ) was a Neapolitan Italian composer of the Renaissance .
Étienne de La Grange ( died 26 November 1388 ) was a French politician of the group of counselors of kings Charles V and Charles VI designated as the Marmousets by their detractors .
Isabelle de Steiger , née Lace ( 28 February 1836 -- 1 January 1927 ) , was an English painter , theosophist , occultist and writer .
Bernt Wilhelm Westermann ( 1781 in Copenhagen - 1868 ) was a wealthy Danish businessman who collected insects .
Richard Sanders Rogers ( 2 December 1861 - 28 March 1942 ) was a distinguished Australian medical doctor , and world authority on Australasian orchids .
Jakob Erbar ( 8 February 1878 -- 7 January 1935 ) was a German professor of graphic design and a type designer .
Henri de Buade de Frontenac ( 1596 - -1622 ) was a French aristocrat during the age of Louis XIII of France , best known as the father of Louis de Buade de Frontenac , the future Lieutenant General of the colony of New France in North America .
Jules de Clérambault ( ca . 1660 -- August 17 , 1714 ) was a French ecclesiastic and Abbot of Saint - Taurin d’Évreux .
Alexander Jamieson ( 1782 - -1850 ) was a Scottish writer and schoolmaster of the early 19th century , now best known as a rhetorician .
Eddie Thomson ( 25 February 1947 -- 21 February 2003 ) was a Scottish football ( soccer ) player and coach .
Lieutenant General Sir Joseph John Talbot Hobbs KCB , KCMG , VD ( 24 August 1864 -- 21 April 1938 ) was an Australian architect and First World War general .
Ramai Dev ( 1360 - -1385 ) was a king of Patna ( princely state ) who laid the foundation of Chauhan rule in Western Odisha in the 14th century .
Ozias Humphry ( or Humphrey ) ( 8 September 1742 -- 9 March 1810 ) was a leading English painter of portrait miniatures , later oils and pastels , of the 18th century .
Sextus Otto Lindberg ( 29 March 1835 -- 20 February 1889 ) was a Swedish physician and botanist , known as a bryologist .
Gerrit Jan Heijn ( 14 February 1931 , Zaandam -- 9 September 1987 ) was a Dutch businessman , who was a top manager of Ahold until his death in 1987 .
David Samwell ( 15 October 1751 -- 23 November 1798 ) was a Welsh naval surgeon and poet .
Alfred Roller ( 2 October 1864 -- 21 June 1935 ) was an Austrian painter , graphic designer , and set designer .
Arne Kokkvoll ( 1925 -- 19 September 1998 ) was a Norwegian historian , librarian / archivist and politician for the Labour Party .
Elaheh ( Persian : الهه‎‎ ; born on 1934 , died on 15 August 2007 ) was an Iranian singer .
Brigadier Nelson Russell , CB , DSO , MC ( b. 7 July 1897 , Lisburn , Co. Antrim , Northern Ireland - d. 20 October 1971 , Newcastle , County Down , Northern Ireland ) was a British soldier who served in both World Wars .
Robert Wornum died on 29 September 1852 after a short illness .
Sir Christopher Nevile ( ca . 1631 -- 18 November 1692 ) , of Haddington , Aubourn , Lincolnshire , was an English Member of Parliament .
Ford Grey , 1st Earl of Tankerville ( 20 July 1655 -- 24 June 1701 ) , 1st Viscount Glendale , and 3rd Baron Grey of Warke , was an English nobleman and statesman .
Thomas Dover , M.D. ( 1660 - -1742 ) , sometimes referred to as `` Doctor Quicksilver '' , was an English physician .
Georg Karl Maria Seidlitz ( June 19 , 1840 , St. Petersburg -- 1917 , Irschenhausen near Munich ) was a German doctor and entomologist .
Richard Edlin or Edlyn ( 1631 - -1677 ) , was an English astrologer .
Hermann Gunnarsson ( 9 December 1946 -- 4 June 2013 ) commonly referred to by his nickname , Hemmi Gunn , was an Icelandic television and radio personality , performer and former football and handball player at an international level .
Charles Lucy ( 1814 -- 19 May 1873 ) was an English historical painter of the Victorian era .
Vikramaditya Varaguna ( 885 - -925 ) was a king of Ay rulers in South India kerala .
Sir James William Colvile ( 12 January 1810 -- 6 December 1880 ) was a British lawyer , civil servant and then judge in India , and a judge on the Judicial Committee of the Privy Council , the court of last resort for the British colonies .
Paolo Vergani ( 1753 - -1820 ) was an Italian Catholic political economist who wrote on the economy of the Papal States .
James Justinian Morier ( 1780 -- 19 March 1849 ) was a British diplomat and author noted for his novels about Qajar dynasty Iran , most famously for the Hajji Baba series .
Luman Reed ( 1787 - -1836 ) was a successful American merchant and an important patron of the arts .
Gopal Chandra Bhattacharya ( 1 August 1895 -- 8 April 1981 ) was an Indian entomologist and naturalist .
Enoch Wood Perry , Jr. ( 1831 - -1915 ) was a painter from the United States .
Bartholomeus Maton ( 1641 -- after 1684 ) , was a Dutch Golden Age painter active in Sweden .
Colonel Claude Hugh Toye MBE ( 29 March 1917- 15 April 2012 ) was a British Army intelligence officer who worked in India and Burma during World War II . Working in the Combined Services Directorate of Intelligence , Toye was tasked with interrogation of captured troops of the Japanese army and the Indian National Army .
Simeon Burt Wolbach ( 3 July 1880 -- 19 March 1954 ) was an American pathologist , researcher , teacher , and journal editor who elucidated the infection vectors for Rocky Mountain spotted fever and epidemic typhus .
Leo Picard , also known as Yehudah Leo Picard ( Hebrew : יהודה ליאו פיקרד‎ , 3 June 1900 -- 4 April 1997 ) , was an Israeli geologist and an expert in the field of hydrogeology .
Eda Kersey ( 15 May or 16 May 1904 -- 13 July 1944 ) was a British violinist who was renowned for her brilliant playing .
Kostas Karagiannis ( Greek : Κώστας Καραγιάννης ; 1932 -- 17 February 1993 ) was a Greek film director .
Léa Roback ( 3 November 1903 -- 28 August 2000 ) was a Canadian trade union organizer , social activist , pacifist , and feminist .
Teresa Deevy ( 21 January 1894 -- 19 January 1963 ) was a deaf Irish dramatist , short story writer , and writer for radio .
Joseph Tepper 1886 - 1977 was a Russian , Jewish , American portrait painter and artist .
Jan Grodek or Jan Grodek of Sanok ( - 1554 ) , son of mayor of Sanok , was a nine - time rector of the Academy in Kraków , Poland between 1540 and 1552 .
Sir Leopold Halliday Savile , KCB , MICE ( 31 August 1870 - -1953 ) was a British civil engineer .
Herbert Hannam ( died 1983 ) was a British policeman within the Metropolitan Police Service .
Thomas Gapes ( 1848 -- 16 April 1913 ) was Mayor of Christchurch 1893/94 .
Rolf Kirkvaag ( 20 September 1920 -- 24 January 2003 ) was a Norwegian journalist , and a radio- and TV personality .
Sir Edward Hannes M.D. ( died 1710 ) was an English physician .
Harry Ralph ( 21 May 1919 -- 17 July 2004 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) and in the South Australian National Football League ( SANFL ) .
' Umar ibn Hafs Hazarmard ( Arabic : عمر بن حفص هزارمرد‎ ) ( d. November 27 , 771 ) was a member of the Muhallabid family who served as a provincial governor for the Abbasid Caliphate during the reigns of Abu al-'Abbas ( r. 749 - -754 ) al - Mansur ( r. 754 - -775 ) .
Syed Waheed Akhtar ( Urdu : سید وحید اختر ‎ ) ( 12 August 1934 in Aurangabad ( Deccan ) -- 13 December 1996 ) was an Urdu poet , writer , critic , orator , and a Muslim scholar and philosopher .
Henry O'Brien , 5th Earl of Thomond ( 1588 -- 26 July 1639 ) was an Irish peer , styled Lord Ibrickane until 1624 .
Nikephoros I Komnenos Doukas , Latinized as Nicephorus I Comnenus Ducas ( Greek : Νικηφόρος Α΄ Κομνηνός Δούκας , Nikēphoros I Komnēnos Doukas ) , ( c. 1240 -- c. 1297 ) was ruler of Epirus from 1267/8 to c. 1297 .
John Brinsley the Elder ( fl . 1581 - -1624 ) was an English schoolmaster , known for his educational works .
Omar Shegewi or Sheghewi ( Arabic : عمر الشغيوي‎ ) ( unknown-1928 ) was a Libyan resistance leader who fought against Italian colonization .
Kazimierz Barcikowski ( Polish pronunciation : ( kaˈʑimjɛʂ bart͡ɕiˈkɔfskʲi ) ; 22 March 1927 , Zglechów - 10 July 2007 , Warsaw ) was a Polish politician .
Peter Kruse ( 30 January 1955 -- 1 June 2015 ) was honorary professor of organizational psychology at the University of Bremen and professional consultant for collective intelligence .
Dick Crayne ( April 24 , 1913 -- August , 1985 ) was an American football fullback for the Brooklyn Dodgers .
Jack Garden ( 3 March 1895 -- 1 December 1955 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Essendon in the VFL .
Karl Woermann ( 4 July 1844 -- 4 February 1933 ) was a German art historian and museum director .
Carl Johan Schönherr ( 10 June 1772 -- 28 March 1848 ) was a Swedish entomologist who revised the taxonomy of beetles , including weevils .
Morton Lowry , born Edward Morton Lowater ( 13 February 1914 -- 26 November 1987 ) was a British actor .
Floyd Johnson ( 7 July 1900 , Des Moines , Idaho -- 1 June 1986 ) , nicknamed `` The Auburn Bulldog '' , was an American heavyweight boxer who was known for his stiff punch .
Cecylia Vetulani ( 11 April 1908 -- 2 January 1980 ) was a Polish art historian and conservator - restorer who did research mostly in the field of Warmia and Masuria folk art . Custodian of the Museum of Warmia and Mazury in Olsztyn ( 1950 - -1956 ) .
Rostislav Mikhailovich ( Hungarian : Rosztyiszláv , Bulgarian , Russian and Ukrainian : Ростислав Михайлович ) ( after 1210 / c. 1225 -- 1262 ) was a Rus ' prince ( a member of the Rurik dynasty ) , and a dignitary in the Kingdom of Hungary .
Dr. Mihály Dömötör ( 1 October 1875 , Bíňovce -- 2 February 1962 ) was a Hungarian politician , who served as Interior Minister for three months in 1920 .
Oskar Alexander Richard Büttner ( 28 September 1858 - 1927 ) was a German botanist and mineralogist involved in the exploration of the Congo .
Idris Gawr ( English : Idris the Giant ; c. 560 -- 632 ) was a king of Meirionnydd in early medieval Wales .
Bertha Mahony ( 1882 - -1969 ) , also known as Bertha Mahony Miller , is considered a figurehead of the children 's literature movement .
Mabel Murray Hickson , née Mabel Greenhow ( 2 February 1859 , Esher -- 12 November 1922 Esher ) , was an English writer of short stories .
Sir William Keith , 4th Baronet , ( 1669 -- 18 November 1749 ) served as lieutenant - governor of the Colonies of Pennsylvania and Delaware , 1717 - -26 .
Sir Thomas Wolryche , 1st Baronet ( 1598 - -1668 ) was an English landowner and politician who sat in the House of Commons for Wenlock between 1621 and 1625 .
Ailsa Garland ( 1917 - -1982 ) was a British fashion journalist .
Sir William Robert Grove , PC , QC , FRS ( 11 July 1811 -- 1 August 1896 ) was a Welsh judge and physical scientist .
Verna Fields ( née Hellman , 21 March 1918 -- 30 November 1982 ) was an American film editor , film and television sound editor , educator , and entertainment industry executive .
Howard Hawks Mitchell ( January 13 , 1885 , Marietta , Ohio -- 1943 ) was an American mathematician who worked on group theory and number theory and who introduced Mitchell 's group .
Samuel Lorenzo Knapp ( born in Newburyport , Massachusetts , 19 January 1783 ; died in Hopkinton , Massachusetts , 8 July 1838 ) was a United States author and lawyer .
Paltiel Daykan ( Hebrew : פלטיאל דייקן ; ( born 12 May 1885 ; died 12 February 1969 ) was an Israeli jurist .
Don L. Johnson ( 1927 - -2006 ) was an outdoor writer from Wisconsin .
William Stryker Gummere ( /ɡʌˈmɛr/ ; 1852 - -1933 ) was Chief Justice of the Supreme Court of New Jersey .
Pagano della Torre ( died July 30 , 1365 ) was Patriarch of Aquileia from 1319 until 1332 .
Maurice Mariaud ( 1875 - -1958 ) was a French silent film director , actor and screenwriter .
George Edward Briggs FRS ( 25 June 1893 -- 7 February 1985 ) was Professor of Botany at the University of Cambridge .
Sola i Karlstad ( the Sun in Karlstad ) was the nickname for Eva Lisa Holtz ( 1 January 1739 i Karlstad -- 24 September 1818 ) , a Swedish waitress and innkeeper who became the symbol for the Swedish city of Karlstad .
Anthonie de Lorme , also Anthonius de Lorme , Anthonie Delorme , Anthonius Delorme , Anthonie de l'Orme , Anthonie del Orme , Anthonius de l'Orme , Anthonius del Orme , ( 1610 - -1673 ) was a Dutch painter .
Amasa Wright ( 1787 - -1861 ) originally owned the land under the Chicago loop .
Ding Yuan ( died 189 ) , courtesy name Jianyang , was a regional governor and minor warlord during the late Han Dynasty period of Chinese history .
Maharaja Sir Rajendra Narayan Singh Deo KCIE ( 31 March 1912 -- 23 February 1975 ) was an Indian politician and the last ruler of the princely state of Patna in Odisha before Indian independence in 1947 .
Stan Laurel ( born Arthur Stanley Jefferson ; 16 June 1890 -- 23 February 1965 ) was an English comic actor , writer and film director , most famous for his role in the comedy duo Laurel and Hardy .
General Sir Henry Errington Longden KCB , CIE ( January 1819 -- 29 January 1890 ) was a British Army officer who served as Adjutant - General in India .
Ivan Owen ( 19 August 1927 -- 17 October 2000 ) was a British voice actor , who created the vocal persona of the puppet Basil Brush .
General Michel Laurent Marie Joseph Lafont ( 1874 - -1961 ) was the third Chief Scout of Scouts de France from 1936 to 1948 , the first and only Chief Scout of Scoutisme Français from 1940 to 1948 , and member of the International Committee of the World Organization of the Scout Movement ( WOSM ) .
John Maxim ( 20 July 1925 -- 20 January 1990 ) , sometimes credited as John Wills , was an English film and television actor .
Sir John Davie , 1st Baronet ( 1588 - -1654 ) of Creedy in the parish of Sandford , near Crediton , Devon , was a member of the Devonshire gentry and served as Member of Parliament for Tiverton in 1621 - 2 and as Sheriff of Devon ( 1629 - 1630 ) .
Very Rev. Lord Charles Murray - Aynsley ( 21 October 1771 -- 5 May 1808 ) was an English dean .
Pino Daniele ( 19 March 1955 -- 4 January 2015 ) was an Italian singer - songwriter , and guitarist , whose influences covered a wide number of genres , including pop , blues , jazz , and Italian and Middle Eastern music .
( Mary Sophia ) Charlotte Howe , Viscountess Howe ( 23 September 1703 -- 13 June 1782 ) was a British courtier and politician .
Samuel Maunder ( 1785 - 1849 ) was an English writer and composer of many works .
Josef Monsrud ( 29 May 1922 , Lunner , Oppland -- 12 December 2009 ) was a Norwegian forester and resistance member during World War II . He hailed from Harestua in Lunner .
Bernard Connor or O'Connor M.D. ( c.1666 - -1698 ) was an Irish physician and historian .
Shen Zigao ( Chinese : 沈子高 ; Wade -- Giles : Shen Tzu - kao ; 1895 - -1982 ) , DD , was an Anglican bishop in China .
John Neilson Lake ( 19 August 1834 , Ernestown , Ontario , Canada -- 12 February 1925 ) was originally a preacher for the Methodist Church in Canada and eventually selected the site that became the city of Saskatoon , Saskatchewan , Canada .
Mohammad Abdul Ahed ( 1919 -- November 2001 ) was an architect and painter from Pakistan .
Ali Nurullah Hasan ( 1867 or 1870 in Bıyıklı village near Şumnu , Danube Vilayet - 1912 in İstanbul ) was a Turkish wrestler .
Dirk Hannema ( 16 September 1895 - 7 July 1984 ) was a controversial museum director and art collector .
Prof . Dr. Carlos Trincão ( 30 May 1903 -- 1968 ) was a Portuguese philatelist who signed the Roll of Distinguished Philatelists in 1953 .
Sir Richard Reynell , 2nd Baronet ( 1673 - -1723 ) was an Anglo - Irish politician and landowner who sat in the Irish House of Commons as member for Wicklow .
Dervish Bejah Baloch ( c. 1862 -- 1957 ) , also known as Bejah Dervish , was an Australian camel driver who had a significant role in the exploration and development of inland Australia .
Jef Dutilleux ( 1876 - 1960 ) was a Belgian painter , mainly active in the first half of the 20th century .
Hans Strøm ( 25 January 1726 -- 1 February 1797 ) was a prominent Norwegian zoologist and naturalist .
Gaetano Mormile ( Naples , 1839 - 1890 ) was an Italian painter , mainly of genre subjects , often peasants in folkloric dress , but also vedute and Neo - Pompeian subjects .
Anatoli Ivanovich Bogdanov ( Russian : Анатолий Иванович Богданов ; 1 January 1931 -- 30 September 2001 ) was a former Soviet sport shooter and Olympic champion .
Lianella Carell ( 6 May 1927 -- 22 December 2000 ) was an Italian film actress and screenwriter .
Diouldé Laya ( aka Juulde Layya ; 1937 - 27 July 2014 ) was a noted Nigerien sociologist and from 1977 to 1997 was director of the Centre d'Etudes Linguistiques et Historiques par Tradition Orale ( CELHTO ) in Niamey .
Nassib Lahoud ( 23 November 1944 -- 1 February 2012 ) was a Lebanese - Christian political figure .
Guy Krohg ( 27 July 1917 -- 19 October 2002 ) was a Norwegian painter , illustrator and scenographer .
John Yasutaro Naide D.D. ( December 22 , 1866 -- 1945 ) was an Anglican Bishop of the Diocese of Osaka , in the Nippon Sei Ko Kai , the Province of the Anglican Communion in Japan .
Dmytro Dedko ( Demetrius Dedko , Ukrainian : Дмитро Дедько ) was a Lord of Ruthenia in 1340 ( 1323 ) -- 1349 .
Fritz Wächtler ( 7 January 1891 - 19 April 1945 ) was a Nazi German politician and Gauleiter of the eastern Bavarian administrative region of Gau Bayreuth .
Michael Rowntree ( 16 February 1919 -- 23 September 2007 ) was a British journalist and social campaigner .
Ralph de Cromwell , 3rd Baron Cromwell ( c. 1393 -- 4 January 1456 ) was an English politician and diplomat .
Jean de Montereul ( c. 1614 , Paris -- 27 April 1651 , Paris ) was a French ecclesiastic and diplomat .
Cliff Twemlow ( 14 October 1937 -- 5 May 1993 ) was an English actor , nightclub bouncer , horror paperback author and library music composer .
Brinsley Butler , 2nd Earl of Lanesborough , PC ( Ire ) ( 4 March 1728 -- 24 January 1779 ) , styled The Honourable until 1756 and Lord Newtown - Butler from 1756 to 1768 , was an Irish politician and peer .
Raymond McGrath ( 7 March 1903 -- 23 December 1977 ) was an Australian - born architect and interior designer who for the greater part of his career was Principal Architect for the Office of Public Works in Ireland .
Gourgen `` Guros '' Paronyan ( Armenian : Գուրգեն Գևորգի `` Գուրոս '' Պարոնյան-Հովսեփյան ; 1905 - -1981 ) is an Armenian painter , Honoured Artist of the Armenian SSR , Member of Armenian Artists ' Union
Maria Vicol ( née Taitiș , 17 October 1935 -- 13 March 2015 ) was a Romanian foil fencer , Olympic bronze medalist in 1960 and an Olympic team bronze medalist in 1968 .
Ramón Tamayo ( 1921 - -2008 ) was a Spanish producer , businessman and impresario .
Francis Herring M.D. ( died 1628 ) was an English physician , known as a medical and religious writer .
Henry Bamford Parkes ( 13 November 1904 -- 7 January 1972 ) was an author and professor of history at New York University .
Anna Smitshuizen ( February 1751 , Alkmaar -- 29 June 1775 , Amsterdam ) , was a Dutch prostitute and the victim of a cause célèbre murder .
Lester Gaba ( 1907 -- 12 August 1987 ) was an American sculptor , writer and retail display designer .
Biyu of Baekje ( died 455 , r. 427 - -455 ) was the twentieth king of Baekje , one of the Three Kingdoms of Korea .
Benjamin Minge Duggar ( 1872 - -1956 ) was an American plant physiologist .
Asin of Baekje ( died 405 ) ( r. 392 - -405 ) was the seventeenth king of Baekje , one of the Three Kingdoms of Korea .
Vice Admiral Sir Horatio Thomas Austin ( 1801 -- 16 November 1865 ) was a British officer in the Royal Navy , and an explorer .
Lieutenant General Habibullah Khan Khattak also known as Muhammad Habibullah Khan ( October 17 , 1913 -- 1994 ) was a Pakistani Army officer born in Karak , Khyber Pakhtoonkhwa , Pakistan .
Frederick Tisdall ( 1893 - -1949 ) was one of three Canadian pediatricians who developed the infant cereal Pablum .
Clare Boylan ( 21 April 1948 -- 16 May 2006 ) was an Irish author , journalist and critic for newspapers , magazines and many international broadcast media .
On 14 November 1942 Konstantin Zaslonov died a hero 's death in a battle with a German death squad near Kupovat , Senno Raion , Vitebsk Oblast , Belorussian SSR .
Kim Ho Jik ( 16 April 1905 -- 31 August 1959 ) was the first Korean convert to The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter - day Saints ( LDS Church ) and was a key figure in opening South Korea to missionary work of the LDS Church .
Inés Rodríguez Girón ( died in 1265 ) was infanta of the Kingdom of Castile as the second wife of Infante Philip of Castile .
Jan Christiaan Lindeman ( 26 June 1921 -- 18 July 2007 ) was a Dutch botanist specialized in the Flora of Suriname .
Deli Emir Ahmed Agha ( Turkish : Deli Emir Ahmed Ağa , `` Emir Ahmed Agha the Mad '' ; died November 1753 ) , later known as Seyyid Emir Ahmed Pasha , was an Ottoman statesman and military leader .
Catherine Arnauld ( 1590 - -1651 ) was a French religious figure of the 17th century , belonging to the Arnauld family of Jansenists .
James Rees ( 1802 , Norristown , Pennsylvania -- 1885 ) was an American author , playwright , and editor .
Richard Óg de Burgh , 2nd Earl of Ulster and 3rd Baron of Connaught ( 1259 -- 29 July 1326 ) , called The Red Earl and often named as Richard de Burgo , was one of the most powerful Irish nobles of the late 13th and early 14th centuries .
David Sherman Boardman ( 8 December 1768 -- 2 December 1864 ) was an American lawyer , judge , and state assemblyman in the early United States .
King Sagato Alofi was the Tu'i Agaifo 1997 - 2002 .
Sir George Lauder of the Bass , Knight ( died 27 June 1611 , on the Bass Rock ) , was a cleric , Privy Counsellor , and Member of the Scottish Parliament .
Meade McClanahan ( 1894?--1959 ) was an industrial engineer and businessman who was elected to the Los Angeles City Council in 1945 but was ousted by voters in 1946 based upon his support for controversial preacher and political organizer Gerald L.K. Smith .
James Catanach ( 28 November 1921 -- 29 March 1944 ) , known as `` Jim '' or Jimmy , was an Australian Handley Page Hampden bomber pilot who was taken prisoner during the Second World War .
Sir Francis Lycett ( 1803 - 29 October 1880 ) was a British businessman and philanthropist , and a prominent member of the Methodist Church .
Olaf Krohn ( 4 June 1863 -- 18 June 1933 ) was a Norwegian satirical illustrator , educated as painter .
Oliver Cope ( 1902 - 30 April 1994 ) , was an American surgeon known for his work in parathyroid surgery , burns treatment and breast cancer treatment .
The Reverend John Smithies ( 1802 - -1872 ) was a Wesleyan Methodist missionary who served in Newfoundland , the Swan River Colony of Western Australia , and Tasmania .
Henrik Kalocsai ( pronounced : xenrik kalochaee ) 28 November 1940 -- 22 May 2012 ) was a Hungarian athlete who specialized in the triple jump and long jump .
Albert T. Morgan ( died 15 April 1922 ) was a Civil War soldier and Reconstruction - era Radical Republican senator of the Mississippi legislature .
Balakrishnabuwa Ichalkaranjikar ( 1849 - -1926 ) was an Indian vocalist of Khayal - genre of Hindustani classical music .
Hugo Rasmussen ( 22 March 1941 -- 30 August 2015 ) was a Danish bassist .
Vice Admiral Arthur Kemmis Betty DSO ( 1877 -- 1961 ) was a senior Royal Navy officer .
Adolf Pansch ( 2 March 1841 , Eutin -- 14 August 1887 ) was a German anatomist and naturalist .
Henry Ibbotson ( 1816 ? -- 12 February 1886 in York ) , was an English botanist .
James Robin ( pronounced ROE - bin ) ( 14 November 1817 -- 23 July 1894 ) was a prominent businessman in the early days of South Australia .
William Vorilong , also known as Guillermus Vorrilong , Willem of Verolon , William of Vaurouillon , Guilelmus de Valle Rouillonis , etc . ( ca . 1390 - 1463 ) was a French philosopher and theologian .
Peter Sterry ( 1613 - -1672 ) was an English independent theologian , associated with the Cambridge Platonists prominent during the English Civil War era .
Tahawar Ali ( died 1854 ) was a noble man in the court of Bhonsle Dynasty at Nagpur .
Jasper Heywood ( 1535 -- 9 January 1598 ) was an English Jesuit priest .
Frances Williams ( 1904 -- 1978 ) was a composer and conductor , particularly known for her choral works .
Granville Leveson - Gower , 1st Marquess of Stafford PC ( 4 August 1721 -- 26 October 1803 ) , known as Viscount Trentham from 1746 to 1754 and as The Earl Gower from 1754 to 1786 , was a British politician from the Leveson - Gower family .
John Bruce Norton ( 8 July 1815 -- 13 July 1883 ) was a British lawyer and educationist who served as the Advocate - General of Madras Presidency .
James Brougham ( 16 January 1780 -- 22 December 1833 ) was a British Whig politician .
Frederic James ( 1915 - -1985 ) was an American painter who specialized in watercolors .
Walter of Saint Omer ( French : Gautier de Saint - Omer ; d 1174 ) , also known as Walter of Fauquembergues or Walter of Tiberias , was the son of William II of Saint Omer and Melisinde of Picquigny , and Prince of Galilee and Tiberias .
Richmond William Hullett ( 15 November 1843 - 1914 ) was an English 19th century headmaster , explorer and plant collector .
Sir Edward Dering , 1st Baronet ( 1598 - -1644 ) was an English antiquary and politician .
Robert Catesby ( b. in or after 1572 -- 8 November 1605 ) was the leader of a group of provincial English Catholics who planned the failed Gunpowder Plot of 1605 .
Karl Johannes Eskelund ( 1918 - 1972 ) was a Danish journalist and best - selling author who wrote primarily in English .
Sir Edward Cust , 1st Baronet , KCH ( 17 March 1794 -- 14 January 1878 ) was a British soldier , politician and courtier .
Nicholas Trott ( 19 January 1663 -- 21 January 1740 ) was an 18th - century British judge , legal scholar and writer .
Maria Ersdotter ( 1685 -- 19 July 1721 ) was a Swedish woman executed for incest after having a child with her former stepson .
Matthias Hafenreffer ( 24 June 1561 -- 22 October 1619 ) was a German orthodox Lutheran theologian in the Lutheran scholastic tradition .
Remo Germani , stage name of Remo Speroni ( 31 May 1938 -- 18 October 2010 ) was an Italian singer and occasional actor , mainly successful in the 1960s .
Florence Gill ( born 27 July 1877 - 19 February 1965 ) was an English voice actress .
Joseph Finger ( 1887 - -1953 ) was an Austrian - born architect most active in Texas in the 1930s and 1940s , responsible for a number of Houston Art Deco landmarks .
Admiral Farajollah Rasai ( Persian : فرج‌الله رسائی‎‎ , 1910 - 2002 ) was the Commander of the Imperial Iranian Navy from 1961 to 1972 and the most Senior Naval Commander of the Iranian Navy .
Lawrence V. Redman ( September 1 , 1880 - -November 26 , 1946 ) , was a Canadian chemist and businessman who spent much of his adult life in the United States .
Martin O'Reilly ( 1829 - -1904 ) was a blind Irish piper .
Captain Sue S. Dauser died on 11 March 1972 .
Francis Russell , 2nd Earl of Bedford , KG ( c. 1527 -- 28 July 1585 ) was an English nobleman , soldier and politician and godfather to Francis Drake .
Kjeld Petersen ( 1 July 1920 -- 24 May 1962 ) was a Danish film and stage actor .
Sir Derek Wanless ( 29 September 1947 -- 22 May 2012 ) was a former English banker and a former adviser to the Labour Party .
Johann Moriaen ( born Nuremberg c.1591 - 1668 ) was a German alchemist and early chemist , known as an associate of Samuel Hartlib .
Peter Edmund Jones M.D. ( 30 October 1843 - 29 June 1909 ) was a Mississauga Ojibwa chief of New Credit .
John de Hotham ( or Hodum ; died 1361 ) was an English medieval college head and university chancellor .
Benjamin Griggs ( 1690 -- 1768 ) was one of the earliest European settlers of the area that would later be known as Griggstown in Franklin Township , Somerset County , New Jersey , United States .
Robert Sharples ( 2 July 1913 -- 8 September 1987 ) was a British musical conductor , composer and bandleader , whose work encompassed films and well - known British television programmes in the 1960s and 1970s .
Captain Laurent Touyeras ( 10 November 1910 in Sainte - Sigolène , Haute - Loire -- 14 August 1980 in Tarbes , Hautes - Pyrénées ) was a French artillery captain in the Maginot Line during the Second World War .
Francis Rombouts ( 22 June 1631 -- 1691 ) was the 12th Mayor of New York City , ( formerly New Amsterdam ) , from 1679 to 1680 .
Ezzatollah Sahabi ( 9 May 1930 -- 31 May 2011 ) was an Iranian scholar , humanitarian , democracy activist , politician and former parliament member .
Xu Yixin ( Chinese : 徐以新 ) ( November 14 , 1911 -- December 30 , 1994 ) was an associate of the 28 Bolsheviks .
Richard Thomas Baker ( 1 December 1854 -- 14 July 1941 ) was an Australian economic botanist , museum curator and educator .
Johan Frans Podolyn or Johann Franz Podolyn ( Lisbon 29 May 1739 - Gothenburg 29 May 1784 ) was a Swedish numismatist who published on Punic currency in his possession which had been found on the island of Corvo in the Azores .
Maldras ( or Masdras ) ( died February 460 ) was the Suevic King of Galicia from 456 until his death .
Joe Beeston ( 23 February 1947 -- 25 February 2008 ) was the CEO of Highland Spring .
Andrew of Rhodes ( Andrew of Colossus ; died 1440 ) was a Greek Dominican theologian .
Agostino Dati , also known as Augustinus Datus or Dathus ( 1420 -- 6 April 1478 ) was a fifteenth - century orator , historian and philosopher best known for his grammatical textbook Elegantiolae .
Zong Bing ( Chinese : 宗炳 ; Wade -- Giles : Tsung Ping , 375 - 444 , style name Shaowen 少文 ) was a Chinese artist and musician who wrote the earliest text on landscape painting .
Kiya Afrasiyab ( Persian : کیا افراسیاب‎ ) , was the founder of the Afrasiyab dynasty , ruling from 1349 to 1359 .
Humbert Pugliese ( 1884 - -1955 ) was an Australian film exhibitor and producer .
Lyubov Zakharchenko ( Russian : Захарченко , Любовь Ивановна ) , ( 4 April 1961 , Rostov - on - Don - 21 January 2008 , Moscow ) was a Russian poet and singer - songwriter .
Giulio Segni da Modena , also Julio Segni ( Modena , 1498- Rome , 1561 ) was an Italian composer known for his ricercars in Musica Nova ( Venice 1540 ) .
Ludovico Buti ( c. 1560 - after 1611 ) was an Italian painter , active mostly in Florence .
Joe Lovett ( 18 October 1902 -- 26 May 1949 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with North Melbourne and Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Robert Erwin Johnson ( 3 February 1923 -- 28 January 2008 ) was a University of Alabama professor of history and considered `` one of the finest scholars of the nineteenth century U.S. Navy and U.S. Coast Guard '' .
James Dillon , 1st Earl of Roscommon ( died March 1642 ) was an Irish peer .
María Francisca Ana de Castro , called La bella toledana ( ca.1686 -- December 23 , 1736 ) was a Spanish immigrant to Peru , renowned for her beauty and hauteur .
Julie Alexander ( 9 May 1938 - -31 January 2003 ) ( born as Julia Yvonne Alexander ) was a British model and actress of the late 1950s and early 1960s known for playing glamorous roles including Rosalie Dawn in The Pure Hell of St Trinian 's .
George Linley ( 1798 - 10 September 1865 ) , was an English verse - writer and musical composer .
Arthur Robbins ( 4 February 1920 -- 8 November 2010 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Collingwood in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Holbrook Gaskell II ( 7 December 1846 -- 2 July 1919 ) was a chemical industrialist in Widnes , Lancashire , England .
Carlo Capra ( 21 September 1889 , Strambino -- 19 August 1966 ) was an Italian professional football player .
Vlatko Vuković Kosača ( died 1392 ) was a 14th - century Bosnian nobleman , duke of duchy of Hum , Grand Duke of Bosnia ( Bosnian : Veliki Vojvoda Bosanski ) and one of the best military commanders of King Tvrtko I of Bosnia .
Tito Agujari ( 25 April 1834 - 2 November 1908 ) was a well - known Italian portraitist and history painter .
Norman Carling ( 1902 - -1971 ) was an English designer / modeller in ceramics , who created a large number of Art Deco models and joined Maling pottery in 1935 from the firm of A.J. Wilkinson , a company which also employed Clarice Cliff .
Camillo Róndani ( 21 November 1808 -- 17 September 1879 ) was an Italian entomologist noted for his studies of Diptera .
Jacob Freud ( 1815 - 1896 ) was the father of Sigmund Freud , the founder of psychoanalysis .
Robinson McIlvaine ( 17 July 1913 -- 24 June 2001 ) was a career US diplomat who was President of the African Wildlife Foundation from 1978 to 1982 .
Janullah Hashimzada ( 1969 - 24 August 2009 ) ( جان الله هاشم زاده ) was an Afghan journalist and bureau chief in Peshawar , Pakistan for the Afghanistan Shamshad TV channel .
Richard Radcliffe ( died 9 October 1660 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons in 1656 .
Naomi Weisstein ( 1939 -- March 2015 ) was an American professor of psychology , neuroscientist , and author .
Peter Williams , Jr. ( 1786 - -1840 ) was an African - American Episcopal priest , the second ordained in the United States , and an abolitionist in New York City .
Arnold Möller ( 4 May 1581 -- 14 October 1655 ) , was a German calligrapher .
Jim Kane ( February 2 , 1937 -- January 28 , 2003 ) was a Nebraska high school football , basketball , track and cross country coach , and was named the state 's `` Coach of the Year '' in 1983 , and was posthumously named to the state 's High School Hall of Fame .
Luigi Diligenza ( 10 February 1921 -- 25 May 2011 ) was an Italian Prelate of Roman Catholic Church .
Agnes Maule Machar ( 23 January 1837 -- 24 January 1927 ) was a Canadian author and social reformer .
William Saville - Kent ( 10 July 1845 , Sidmouth , Devon -- 11 October 1908 , Bournemouth , Dorset ) was an English marine biologist .
Penelope Ann Rachel , Lady Reed ( 4 August 1914 -- 22 January 1982 ) , known as Penelope Dudley - Ward , was an English actress .
Henry of Bracton , also Henry de Bracton , also Henrici Bracton , or Henry Bratton also Henry Bretton ( c. 1210 -- c. 1268 ) was an English cleric and jurist .
Ralph Bernal ( 2 October 1783 or 2 October 1784 - 26 August 1854 ) was a British Whig politician and art collector .
Major General Rowland Laugharne ( c.1607 - -1675 ) was a soldier in the English Civil War .
Lieutenant - Colonel Sir Matthew Nathan GCMG , PC ( 3 January 1862 -- 18 April 1939 ) was a British soldier and colonial administrator , who variously served as the Governor of Sierra Leone , Gold Coast , Hong Kong , Natal and Queensland .
Ernő Bosnyák , ( Zombor , Austria - Hungary 2 January 1876 -- Sombor , Yugoslavia 9 August 1963 ) was a Hungarian cameraman , film director and printer .
Tarquinio Merula ( 24 November 1595 -- 10 December 1665 ) was an Italian composer , organist , and violinist of the early Baroque era .
Jasper Fish ( buried 28 July 1791 at Sevenoaks , Kent ) was a noted professional cricketer in the 18th century who was chiefly associated with Kent in the 1760s and 1770s .
Frances Claudia Wright , OBE ( 5 March 1919 -- 2 April 2010 ) was a prominent Sierra Leonean lawyer during the 20th century .
Matteo Piccione ( 1615 - 1671 ) was an Italian painter , active in Rome , as a painter of religious subjects .
Angelo Luzzani ( 1896 -- 1960 ) was an Italian lawyer and football player .
Saunders Mac Lane ( 4 August 1909 -- 14 April 2005 ) was an American mathematician who co - founded category theory with Samuel Eilenberg .
Frank Lake ( 6 June 1914 -- 10 May,1982 ) was one of the pioneers of pastoral counselling in the United Kingdom .
Prince Trung Vũ Trần Thủ Độ ( 1194 -- 1264 ) was a general and leader of the Trần clan during the reign of Lý Huệ Tông and Lý Chiêu Hoàng in the kingdom of Đại Việt ( now Viet Nam ) .
Michał Florian Rzewuski ( died 1687 ) was a Polish - Lithuanian nobleman and politician , Treasurer of the Crown Court .
Teofil Cyprian Wolicki ( 1768 - -1829 ) was an 18th - century Primate of Poland and Bishop of Poznań and Włocławek .
Don Keyter ( 13 September 1931 -- 11 November 1986 ) was Australian rules footballer who played with South Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Barbara Noble ( 1907 - -2001 ) was an English publisher and novelist .
Sakura Sōgorō or better known as Sōgo - sama ( 1605 -- September 1653 ) , was a legendary Japanese farmer whose real family name was Kiuchi .
Robert Klippel AO ( 19 June 1920 -- 19 June 2001 ) was an Australian constructivist sculptor and teacher .
Radu G. Vlădescu ( 1886 -- 1964 ) , a Romanian professor born in Buzău , taught at the Faculty of Veterinary Medicine of the University of Agronomical Sciences and Veterinary Medicine , Bucharest .
Manuel António Lino ( 4 January 1865 , in Angra do Heroísmo -- 15 June 1927 , in Angra do Heroísmo ) was a medic , politician , poet and dramatist , who became Civil Governor of the District of Horta .
Kilian Hennessy ( 19 February 1907 -- 1 October 2010 ) was a French business magnate , of Irish origin , and patriarch of the Hennessy cognac company .
Thomas Gerard , 1st Baron Gerard ( c. 1564 -- 15 January 1618 ) was a Staffordshire and Lancashire landowner and politician , a member of six English parliaments for three different constituencies .
Harry De Gray ( 1866 - -1952 ) was the Chairman of the Shanghai Municipal Council for 2 years from 1911 to 1913 .
Harold James Merilees ( January 5 , 1908 -- September 19 , 1972 ) was an advertising executive and political figure in British Columbia .
Erik Brate ( 13 June 1857 -- 11 April 1924 ) was a Swedish linguist and runologist .
Conrad IV , Count of Rietberg ( c. 1371 -- 21 June 1428 ) was Count of Rietberg from 1389 until his death .
Major William Oliver Smedley MC ( 1911 - -1989 ) was a British businessman involved in classical liberal politics and pirate radio .
Sir Matthew Boynton , 1st Baronet ( c. 1591 -- 12 March 1647 ) was an English landowner and politician who sat in the House of Commons in two parliaments between 1621 and 1647 .
Francis Charles Massingberd ( 3 December 1800 -- 5 December 1872 ) was an English churchman and writer , chancellor of the diocese of Lincoln , England .
Li Mian ( Chinese : 李勉 ; 717 -- September 14 , 788 ) , courtesy name Xuanqing ( 玄卿 ) , formally Duke Zhenjian of Qian ( 汧貞簡公 ) , was an official and general of the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty , serving as a chancellor during the reign of Emperor Dezong .
Gunnar Nilsen ( 31 March 1913 -- 3 October 1984 ) was a Norwegian business person .
James Franklin Perry ( 1790 - -1853 ) was an early settler and prominent citizen of Texas .
Nutan Samarth Bahl ( 4 June 1936 -- 21 February 1991 ) , better known as Nutan , was an Indian actress .
Fred Cherry ( 15 April 1926 -- 30 July 2003 ) was an American activist for greater rights for johns ( clients of prostitutes ) .
Joseph Windham ( 1739 - -1810 ) was an English antiquarian .
Shah Quli Khan Zangana ( Persian : شاه قلی خان زنگنه‎‎ , died 1716 ) , was a Kurdish nobleman , who served as the vizier of the Safavid king ( shah ) Sultan Husayn ( r. 1694 - -1722 ) from 1707 to 1716 .
Augustus L. Hart ( October 15 , 1849 -- 1901 ) was the 13th Attorney General of California .
Norm MacLeod ( 8 October 1904 - 7 October 1951 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played for Collingwood in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) during the late 1920s and early 1930s .
Thom Gunn ( 29 August 1929 -- 25 April 2004 ) , born Thomson William Gunn , was an Anglo - American poet who was praised for his early verses in England , where he was associated with The Movement and his later poetry in America , even after moving toward a looser , free - verse style .
Jean - Frédéric Edelmann ( Johann Friedrich Edelmann , 5 May 1749 -- 17 July 1794 ) was a French classical composer .
John Ayrton Paris , FRS ( 1785 -- 24 December 1856 ) was a British physician .
Charles Henry Chapman ( 1879 - -1972 ) , who signed his work as C. H. Chapman , was a British illustrator and cartoonist best known for his work in boys ' story papers such as The Magnet where the character Billy Bunter appeared .
Odofredus ( died 3 December 1265 ) was an Italian jurist .
Gennadi Tumat ( 1964 - -1996 ) was a renowned Tuvinian master of throat singing .
According to the chronology developed by Moskov , Vinekh would have reigned 754 - -762 .
Ana Galvis Hotz ( 22 June 1855 -- 2 November 1934 ) was the first Colombian woman to have obtained a medical degree as a Doctor of Medicine .
Donal MacCarthy Reagh ( Irish : Domhnall Mac Carthaigh Riabhach ) ( 1450/1460 - -1531 ) was the 9th Prince of Carbery from 1505 to his death in 1531 .
Johann Peter Julius Hoffory ( 9 February 1855 Aarhus - 12 April 1897 Westend ) was a Danish - German philologist , phonetician , and Germanic scholar .
Aneesur Rahman ( 24 August 1927 -- 6 June 1987 ) pioneered the application of computational methods to physical systems .
Artur Kukk ( 22 June 1899 -- 19 April 1958 ) was an Estonian wrestler .
Frederic Thomas Somerby or F.T. Somerby ( 1814 - -1871 ) was a painter and `` sporting writer '' in Boston , Massachusetts , in the mid-19th century .
Sarvepalli Gopal ( 23 April 1923 -- 20 April 2002 ) was a well - known Indian historian .
John Derek Jarrett ( 18 March 1928 -- 28 March 2004 ) was an English schoolteacher , historian , and writer .
Dermot Curtis ( 26 August 1932 -- 1 November 2008 ) was an Irish international footballer .

Fr . Peter Daly , Irish priest , c.1788 - -1868 .
Gerald Claude Eugene Foster ( 30 November 1885 -- 25 February 1966 ) , best known as G. C. Foster , was a Jamaican sportsman who excelled at sprinting , cricket , and tennis , and later became a well - known athletics coach and cricket umpire .

Pat Twomey ( 2 April 1929 -- 22 November 1969 ) was an Australian rules footballer , who played in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .

Zhang Liao ( 169 - -222 ) , courtesy name Wenyuan , was a military general serving under the warlord Cao Cao in the late Eastern Han dynasty .
Leslie Evershed - Martin , OBE ( 1903 - -1991 ) was a British theatre impresario , city councillor and optician .
Ludwig Straniak ( 1879 - 1951 ) , was a German mystic , Germanic revivalist and most notably a pendulum dowser .
Lady Elizabeth Basset , DCVO ( 5 March 1908 -- 30 November 2000 ) was born Elizabeth Legge , the daughter of the 7th Earl of Dartmouth .
Gilbert Maxwell ( February 13 , 1910-November 1979 ) was a poet , New York actor , and author .

Robert Pleasants ( 1723 - -1801 ) was an American educator and abolitionist .

George Deas Brown ( born 6 September 1922 -- 1 January 2014 ) was an Australian politician .
Maria Palmer ( born Maria Pichler , 5 September 1917 -- 6 September 1981 ) was an Austrian - born American actress .
Emrys George Bowen FRGS , FSA , also known as E. G. Bowen ( 28 December 1900 -- 8 November 1983 ) , was an internationally renowned geographer with a particular interest in the physical geography and social geography of his native Wales .
Ecmel Kutay ( 1927 - -1998 ) was a General in the Turkish military and served as the 24th Mayor of Istanbul from 1981 to 1982 .
Andrew Vinius ( Russian : Андре́й Андре́евич Ви́ниус , Andrey Andreyevich Vinius ) ( 1641 - -1717 ) was a Russian statesman and a friend of Peter the Great .
Sir Edward Wardour ( died 14 March 1645 ) was an English office holder and politician who sat in the House of Commons between 1621 and 1625 .
Bartholomaeus of Drahonice ( c. 1390 -- 1443 ) was a Bohemian soldier , and author of a chronicle of the Hussite revolution .
Fra Alof de Wignacourt ( 1547 -- 14 September 1622 ) was a French nobleman who was the 54th Grand Master of the Order of St. John of Jerusalem from 10 February 1601 to his death in 1622 .
Sultan Sidi Muhammad ibn Sharif ( ? -- 2 August 1664 ) was the ruler of Tafilalt between 1636 - 64 .
David Edward Sutch ( 10 November 1940 -- 16 June 1999 ) , also known as 3rd Earl of Harrow , or simply Screaming Lord Sutch , was an English musician .
Mary Jean Stone ( born at Brighton , Sussex , in 1853 ; died at Battle , Sussex , 3 May 1908 ) was an English historical writer .
Philipp Ludwig I , Count of Hanau - Münzenberg ( 21 November 1553 -- 4 February 1580 ) succeeded his father in the government of the County of Hanau - Münzenberg in 1561 .
Louis C. Hunter ( 1898 -- 1984 ) was a professor of economic history at American University .
Markos Natsinas ( 1925 - 2001 ) is a former Greek politician .
William Alexander McArthur ( 1857 -- 7 June 1923 ) , was a British Liberal politician and businessman .
Shingai Tanaka ( born 1942 in Tottori , Japan -- 6 October 2007 in Kyoto ) was a Japanese calligrapher who studied under Master Goshin Yasui , becoming one of the country 's best shodō artists .
Adolf Dieudonné ( 29 August 1864 -- 25 October 1944 ) was a German physician and hygienist , born in Stuttgart .
Gruffudd Gryg ( fl . c.1340 - -1380 ) was a Welsh poet from Anglesey , North Wales .
Thomas Wright Hill ( 24 April 1763 in Kidderminster -- 13 June 1851 in Tottenham ) was a mathematician and schoolmaster .
John Jugge ( died 1588 ) was an English member of the Stationers ' Company , and the son of Richard Jugge .
Chong Ah Fatt ( 17 January 1936 - 11 July 1987 ) was a former Chairman of the Marine Parade Citizen 's Consultative Committee .
Jean Fouchard ( 2 March 1912 - 30 September 1990 ) was a Haitian historian , journalist , and diplomat .
Donnchad Grana Ó Cellaigh , Irish Lord , died 1589 .
John Blissard ( 1803 , Northampton , England -- 1875 ) was a Church of England vicar and the father of mathematician and Church of England vicar John Charles Blissard who introduced the umbral calculus .
Reverend Charles Pritchard ( 29 February 1808 -- 28 May 1893 ) was a British astronomer , clergyman , and educational reformer .
Sir George Rawdon , 1st Baronet ( 1604 - -1684 ) , of Moira , County Down which he founded , was an English army officer and politician .
Admiral Harry Powlett , 6th Duke of Bolton PC ( 6 November 1720 -- 25 December 1794 ) was a British nobleman and naval officer .
María Enriqueta Camarillo ( also known as María Enriqueta Camarillo y Roa de Pereyra ) ( 1872 - -1968 ) was a Mexican poet novelist , short story writer and translator .
Rabbi Avraham Yitzchak Bloch ( Hebrew : אברהם יצחק בלוך‎ ; 1891 - -1941 ) was the Chief Rabbi and Rosh Yeshiva of the Telz Yeshiva in Lithuania , and one of the greatest pre - Holocaust Rabbinic figures .
Christine Wetherill Stevenson ( 1878 - 1922 ) was an heiress of the Pittsburgh Paint Company .
Richard Bradshaigh or Bradshaw ( alias Barton , 1602 - -1669 ) , was an English Jesuit .
Paula Fürst ( August 6 , 1894 -- probably June 1942 ) was a German reform educator of Jewish descent .
Gabriel Estêvão Monjane ( 1944 -- 1990 ) is one of only seventeen individuals in medical history to have reached eight feet or more in height .
Edward Chetwynd ( 1577 - -1639 ) was an English churchman , Dean of Bristol from 1617 .
James E. Hagan ( January 25 , 1902 -- November 1965 ) was an American businessman and politician who served in the Massachusetts House of Representatives and as the twenty first mayor of Somerville , Massachusetts .
Athanasius Allanson ( 11 June 1804 -- 13 January 1876 ) was an English Benedictine monk and historian , and Abbot of Glastonbury from 1874 to 1876 .
Malice Green was a resident of Detroit , Michigan who died while in police custody after being arrested by Detroit police officers Walter Budzyn and Larry Nevers on November 5 , 1992 during a traffic stop .
Erika Wendt , née Erika Schwarze ( 1917 -- 9 April 2003 ) was a German secretary .
John William Logan , known as `` Paddy '' Logan , ( 1845 -- 25 May 1925 ) , was a civil engineering contractor and Liberal Member of Parliament ( MP ) for Harborough in Leicestershire .
Kumārajīva ( simplified Chinese : 鸠摩罗什 ; traditional Chinese : 鳩摩羅什 ; pinyin : Jiūmóluóshí ; Wade -- Giles : Chiu1 mo2 lo2 shih2 , 344 - -413 CE ) was a Buddhist monk , scholar , and translator from the Kingdom of Kucha .
Claude Bendier ( died 1677 ) was a doctor of the Sorbonne , canon of Saint - Quentin , Aisne , and a well - known French bibliophile .
