Una Troy Walsh ( 1913 - -1993 ) was an Irish novelist and playwright who wrote under the names Elizabeth Connor and Una Troy .
Georgios Psyllas ( Greek : Γεώργιος Ψύλλας , 1794 - -1878 ) was a Greek scholar and politician , and editor during the Greek War of Independence of the newspaper Efimerida ton Athinon .
Abercius of Hieropolis ( Greek Αβέρκιος , died ca . 167 ) was a bishop of Hierapolis ( modern Castabala ) at the time of Marcus Aurelius , also known as Abercius Marcellus .
Manuel Menezes ( 1922 -- 15 June 1996 ) was an Indian business executive , chairman of the Indian Railway Board .
Hans Andreas Tanberg Gløersen ( 16 February 1836 -- 1 September 1904 ) was a Norwegian forest manager .
Heinz Jentzsch ( 13 March 1920 -- 21 April 2012 ) was the most successful horse trainer in the history of German horse racing .
Yuri Nemyrych ( Ukrainian : Юрій Стефанович Немирич , Polish : Jerzy Niemirycz ) ( 1612 - -1659 ) was a Polish - Ruthenian magnate and politician .
Anselm Bayly ( died 1794 ) was an English churchman and author of various works , chiefly of a theological and critical nature .
Harry V. Roberts ( 1923 - -2004 ) , American statistician , was a distinguished teacher and a pioneer in looking at the applications of Bayesian statistics to business decision making and in Total Quality Management .
Jetti Veera Raghavulu ( died 7 June 2013 ) , better known as J. V. Raghavulu ( Telugu : జె. వి. రాఘవులు ) , was an eminent Indian music director and playback singer .
Harriet Lane Levy ( 1867 - -1950 ) is a California writer best known for her memoir , 920 O’Farrell Street .
Aram Miskaryan ( 1973 -- 23 June 2009 ) was an Armenian sportsman and President of the Armenian Mu Tay Federation .
Giovanni Domenico Nardo ( 4 March 1802 -- 7 April 1877 ) was an Italian naturalist from Venice , although he spent most of his life in Chioggia , home port of the biggest fishing flotilla of the Adriatic .
Secondo Pia ( 1855 - -1941 ) was an Italian lawyer and amateur photographer .
Charles Louis Stanislas Heurteloup ( 16 February 1793 , Paris - 1864 ) was a French physician .
Hart T. Mankin ( died 1995 ) was a United States lawyer and judge who served as General Counsel of the Navy from 1971 to 1973 .
Yakov Permyakov ( Russian : Пермяков , Яков ) ( died 1712 ) was a Russian seafarer , explorer , merchant , and Cossack .
François - Isidore Gagelin ( 10 May 1799 -- 17 October 1833 ) was a French missionary of the Paris Foreign Missions Society in Vietnam .
Jacques Cujas ( or Cujacius ) ( 1522 -- 4 October 1590 ) was a French legal expert .
Rosa Welt - Straus ( 1856 -- 1938 ) was a suffragist and feminist .
John Crayford ( died 1547 ) was a Master of both Clare College , Cambridge and University College , Oxford , England .
John Malcolm Gray , CBE ( 28 July 1934 - 19 November 2009 ) was a Scottish businessman and the former chairman and chief executive of the Hongkong and Shanghai Banking Corporation in Hong Kong from 1993 until his retirement in 1996 .
Titus Clodius Eprius Marcellus ( committed suicide AD 79 ) was a prominent Roman senator , twice consul , best known for his prosecution of the Stoic senator Thrasea Paetus and his bitter quarrel with Helvidius Priscus .
Captain James Robert Mosse ( 1745 - -1801 ) was a British naval officer and military hero killed during his command at the Battle of Copenhagen during the Napoleonic Wars .
Charles Gray Round ( 28 January 1797 -- 1 December 1867 ) was a barrister and the Conservative member of parliament ( MP ) for North Essex 1837 - -47 .
Gertrude Elizabeth Shane ( née Hine ; 1877 - -1951 ) was an Irish poet born in Belfast and who lived much of her life in County Donegal .
Ivan Samoylovych ( Russian : Ива́н Само́йлович Самойло́вич , Polish : Iwan Samojłowicz , Ukrainian : Іван Самойлович ) ( died 1690 ) was the Hetman of Left - bank Ukraine from 1672 to 1687 .
Andrew Thomas Jamieson ( ca 1823 -- October 31 , 1872 ) was a politician in British Columbia .
Count Christian Louis Casimir of Sayn - Wittgenstein - Ludwigsburg ( German : Graf Christian Ludwig Casimir zu Sayn - Wittgenstein - Berleburg in Ludwigsburg ) ( 13 July 1725 , Berleburg -- 6 May 1797 , Rheda ) was a Count of Sayn - Wittgenstein - Ludwigsburg in 1750 - -1796 .
Lancelot Errington , also Launcelot or Lancelott , ( 1657 - 1745 ) was a master mariner noted for his capture of Lindisfarne during the Jacobite Rising of 1715 .
Nan Chauncy ( 28 May 1900 -- 1 May 1970 ) was a British - born Australian children 's writer .
Francis Stanfield ( 1835 - 1914 ) was an English Catholic priest who worked in the Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Westminster .
Stanley Wells Kemp , FRS ( 14 June 1882 -- 16 May 1945 ) was an English marine biologist .
Rawson Hart Boddam ( 1734 -- 20 May 1812 , Bath ) was the former Governor of the Bombay Presidency during the rule of the East India Company in British India from 1784 - -1788 .
Antonio Iranzo ( 4 May 1930 -- 7 July 2003 ) was a Spanish film actor in 77 feature films .
Mustafa Suha Arın ( 23 January 1942 - 1 February 2004 ) was a Turkish film director , writer , producer and educator .
Eva Aschoff ( 16 April 1900 -- 20 September 1969 ) was a German visual artist known for her bookbinding and calligraphy .
Robert Scott Moncrieff ( 1 December 1793 -- 18 June 1869 ) was a Scottish advocate but is largely remembered as an amateur illustrator and caricaturist .
Leo Catozzo ( 10 December 1912 -- 4 March 1997 ) was an Italian award winning film editor .
Daniel Beale ( 1759 - -1842 ) was a Scottish merchant and fur trader active in the Far East mercantile centres of Bombay , Canton and Macau as well as at one time the Prussian consul in China .
Ellen Dickson ( 1819 -- 4 July 1878 ) was an English composer who also used the pseudonym Dolores Dickson .
Natalma ( March 26 , 1957 -- January 29 , 1985 ) was an American - bred Thoroughbred racehorse best known as the dam ( mother ) of the most important sire , and sire of sires , of the 20th Century , Northern Dancer .
Isaac of Seleucia ( died 410 ) was a Patriarch of the Persian Church , who is celebrated among the Catholicoi for having reorganized the Persian Church after the terrible persecution that overwhelmed it under Shapûr II .
Gregory Ivy ( 1904 - -1985 ) was chairman of the art department at Woman 's College , now the University of North Carolina at Greensboro , from 1935 to 1961 .
Loree Murray ( January 2 , 1921 -- 2009 ) was a community activist in Washington DC . Murray moved to DC in the early 1940s from Pinehurst , North Carolina .
John Edwards - Vaughan , also known as John Edwards ( 29 March 1772 -- 16 August 1833 ) was a Welsh politician who sat in the House of Commons in two periods between 1818 and 1832 .
Percy Orthwein ( 1888 - 1957 ) was an American heir and business executive in advertising from St. Louis , Missouri .
Saint Herbert of Derwentwater ( ? - 20 March 687 ) was an Anglo - Saxon priest and hermit who lived on St. Herbert 's Island , a small island in Derwentwater .
When Winfield Scott Stratton died on 14 September 1902 , he left the bulk of his estate for the establishment of the Myron Stratton Home , for `` the aged poor and dependent children ; '' named for his father Myron Stratton .
John Zeleny ( 1872 - -1951 ) was a Czech - American physicist at the University of Minnesota , who in 1911 invented the Zeleny electroscope .
James Ormiston McWilliam ( 1808 - -1862 ) was a Scottish naval surgeon , physician and writer on infectious diseases , best known as medical officer to the 1841 Niger expedition .
John Harington , 1st Baron Harington ( 1281 - -1347 ) of Aldingham in Furness , Lancashire , was an English peer , created Baron Harington by writ of summons to Parliament dated 1326 .
William Burt Pope ( 1822 -- 1903 ) was an English Christian theologian in the Methodist tradition .
Charlie Sutton ( 3 April 1924 -- 5 June 2012 ) was an Australian rules footballer in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Frederick Ward ( 30 June 1894 -- 10 September 1953 ) , known as Fred or Yaffer Ward , was an English footballer who made 245 appearances in the Football League playing for Lincoln City ( in three separate spells ) , Wigan Borough and Rochdale .
Severin Binius ( 1573 , Randerath , present - day Western Germany -- 14 February 1641 ) was a German Roman Catholic priest , historian and critic .
Nahed Sherif ( Arabic : ناهد شريف ) , also romanised as Nahied Sherif , ( 1 January 1942 - 7 April 1981 ) was an Egyptian actress who came to prominence in Egyptian and Lebanese films of the 1960s and 1970s .
Nathaniel Hallowes ( 1582 -- 1661 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons of England from 1640 to 1653 and again in 1659 .
Mustafa Mashhur ( Ar . : مصطفى مشهور ) ( lived 1921 -- November 14 , 2002 ) was the fifth General Guide ( leader ) of the Muslim Brothers .
Lida Gustava Heymann ( 15 March 1868 -- 31 July 1943 ) was a German feminist , pacifist and women 's rights activist .
Claudio Brindis de Salas Monte ( Havana , 30 October 1800 -- 17 December 1872 ) was a black violinist and double bass player who directed the most famous Cuban dance orchestra of his day .
Eva Kristine Vetulani - Belfoure ( 1 October 1924 -- 25 March 2004 ) was a Polish translator , teacher and writer who emigrated to the United States in the early 1950s .
Stevan Dedijer ( 25 June 1911 -- 13 June 2004 ) was a Yugoslav academic and a pioneer of Business Intelligence .
René Fonjallaz ( 1907 -- December 1993 ) was a Swiss bobsledder who competed in the late 1920s and early 1930s .
Ray Parkin ( 6 November 1910 -- 19 June 2005 ) was an Australian writer , amateur artist , and self - taught historian , noted for his memoirs of World War II and a major work on James Cook 's Endeavour voyage .
J. Garber Drushal ( July 16 , 1912 -- December 3 , 1982 ) was the eighth President of The College of Wooster , in Wooster , Ohio USA .
Jaybahadur Hitan Magar ( 17 July 1949 -- 11 December 2009 ) was a politician , campaigner , writer and literati of Nepal , and a member of the Nepalese Congress Party ( NC ) .
Gaspare Sommaripa ( died 1402 ) was a Lord of Paros by right of his wife .
Jackie Mann DFM ( 11 June 1914 -- 12 November 1995 ) was a British former RAF fighter pilot in the Battle of Britain , who in later life was kidnapped by Islamists in Lebanon in May 1989 , and held hostage for more than two years .
Sun Qifeng ( 1583 - -1675 ; 孫奇逢 ; Sun Ch'i - feng in Wade Giles ) was a native of Rongcheng County in Zhili Province .
Tajammul Hussain Malik ( June 13 , 1924 - 2003 ) was a 2-star general officer in the Pakistan army and the former General Officer Commanding of the 23rd Division of Pakistan Army , retiring with the rank of major general .
Federico Mazzotta ( 1839 - 1897 ) was an Italian painter , mainly of genre subjects , but also historic and Neo - Pompeian themes .
W.B. Mathews ( 1865 - -1931 ) was a `` pioneer figure in the water development program of Los Angeles '' and chief counsel for the Metropolitan Water District of Southern California .
José Antonio Saravia or José Antonio Sarabia ( Villanueva del Fresno , Spain , 1785 -- Kamenetz , now in Ukraine , 2 April 1871 ) was an army officer during the Napoleonic Wars .
Ottokar Fischer Marteau , also known as ( born ) Ottokar Fischer ( November 10 , 1873 , Leschan ( Czech : Lešany ) - December 1 , 1940 ) was born in a small village Leschan in Austrian Empire .
Maria Skytte af Duderhof ( died 1703 ) was a Swedish Baroness and Countess known for her unconventional life style .
Fritz Mauthner ( 22 November 1849 -- 29 June 1923 ) was an Austro - Hungarian novelist , theatre critic , satirist , and exponent of philosophical skepticism derived from a critique of human knowledge .
Robert Vivian Storer ( 1900 - -1958 ) , Australian venerealogist , sex educator , and writer , was born in Adelaide in 1900 .
Cináed mac Conaing ( died 851 ) was King of Knowth in the medieval Irish province of Mide , succeeding his father Conaing mac Flainn in 849 .
Buth Diu ( d. c. 1972 ) was a politician who was one of the leaders of the Liberal Party in Sudan in the years before and after independence in 1956 .
Maurice Burton ( 28 March 1898 -- 9 September 1992 ) was a British zoologist and popular science author , who produced many natural history encyclopedias and books including a skeptical treatment of the Loch Ness Monster .
Colonel Francis Hacker ( died 19 October 1660 ) was an English soldier who fought for Parliament during the English Civil War and one of the Regicides of King Charles I of England .
Ewaryst Estkowski ( 1820 - -1856 ) was a Polish teacher , education activist , and editor of Szkoła Polska ( Polish School ) magazine .
Kenth Andersson ( 13 July 1944 -- 20 January 2011 ) was a Swedish middle - distance runner and running agent .
Emanuel Gifford ( died c 1633 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons twice between 1621 and 1626 .
Peter Weekes ( 21 February 1947 -- 26 December 1994 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Đoan Nam Vương Trịnh Khải ( chữ Hán:鄭楷 , 1763 - 1786 ) was one of the Trịnh lords in northern Vietnam .
Örjan Lüning ( 30 May 1919 − 24 September 1995 ) was a Swedish philatelist who was a specialist in aerophilately .
Admiral William Compton , 4th Marquess of Northampton , KG ( 20 August 1818 -- 11 September 1897 ) , known as Lord William Compton from 1828 to 1877 , was a British peer and naval commander .
Reuben Levy ( 28 April 1891 -- 6 September 1966 ) was Professor of Persian at the University of Cambridge , who wrote on Persian literature and Islamic history .
William Sandeman ( born Luncarty , Scotland 1722 , died Perth , Scotland 1790 ) was a leading Perthshire linen and later cotton manufacturer .
M. A. Mansoor ( 1881 - -1968 ) was an antiquarian who compiled an exquisite collection of Amarna Period sculptures .
Vice - Admiral Henry Boyle Townshend Somerville CMG ( 7 September 1863 -- 24 March 1936 ) was a British navy officer who was murdered by the IRA .
Joseph Coincé ( 1764 - -1833 ) was a French Jesuit and physician .
John Rainolds ( or Reynolds ) ( 1549 -- 21 May 1607 ) was an English academic and churchman , of Puritan views .
Gladstone Guest ( 26 June 1917 -- 17 July 1998 ) was an English footballer .
Grace Eldering ( 1900 - -1988 ) was an American public health scientist , known for her involvement in the creation of a vaccine for whooping cough along with Pearl Kendrick .
Charles Oyston ( 12 May 1869 -- 15 July 1942 ) was an English first - class cricketer , who played fifteen matches for Yorkshire County Cricket Club from 1900 to 1909 .
E. Warren Clark ( 1849 - -1907 ) was an American educator who taught thousands of young Japanese the rudiments of modern science while employed as a teacher in Japan from 1871 - 75 .
Alem Zewde Tessema ( died 1974 ) was an Ethiopian military figure .
John Conroy Hutcheson ( 1840- 1897 ) was a British author of novels and short stories about life aboard ships at sea .
George Bax Holmes ( 3 May 1803 -- 31 March 1887 ) was an English fossil collector .
Cú Dínaisc mac Conasaig ( also called Cudinaisc , Cudinaisg , Cú Dínisc , Cudiniscus ) ( c.720 -- 791 ) , was the Abbot of Armagh , Ireland from 768 to 772 .
Eivind Tverbak ( April 1897 , Sørfold , Salten -- 1982 ) was a Norwegian novelist and children 's writer from Sørfold .
Abdullah ibn Umar ( ) ( c.610 - -693 CE ) was the son of the second Caliph Umar and a brother - in - law of the Islamic prophet Muhammad .
Henrik Jæger ( 4 January 1854 -- 17 December 1895 ) was a Norwegian literary historian , literary critic and playwright .
Lucien Paye ( born in Vernoil - le - Fourrier , Maine - et - Loire on 18 June 1907 -- died 1972 ) was a former French politician .
Charles Jerram ( 1770 - -1853 ) was an English evangelical priest of the Church of England .
Abraham Saba ( 1440 - -1508 ) was a preacher in Castile who became a pupil of Isaac de Leon .
Katharina Henot ( or Henoth ) , ( 1570 -- 19 May 1627 ) , was a German postmaster and an alleged witch , burned at the stake for sorcery in Cologne in Germany .
A. Martin Freeman ( 1878 in Tooting , London -- 1959 ) was a scholar of medieval Irish texts and collector of Irish music .
Auguste Aramini ( 1875 - -1950 ) was a French - born Canadian singer .
Henri Membertou ( died 18 September 1611 ) was the sakmow ( Grand Chief ) of the Mi'kmaq First Nations tribe situated near Port Royal , site of the first French settlement in Acadia , present - day Nova Scotia , Canada .
Anna Margaret Ross Alexander ( 1913 - -1995 ) was a philanthropist , who organized the first mental health fund drive in Marion County , Indiana .
Jeronimus Sweerts ( 1603 -- 1636 ) , was a Dutch Golden Age still life painter .
Sir Joseph Whitworth , 1st Baronet ( 21 December 1803 -- 22 January 1887 ) was an English engineer , entrepreneur , inventor and philanthropist .
Sheen T. Kassouf ( 1929 - -2006 ) was an economist known for research in financial mathematics .
Abdul Azim al - Deeb ( Arabic : عبد العظيم الديب‎ ) ( 1929 - 5 January 2010 ) was a professor at Qatar University .
James Leonard Corning ( 1855 -- 1923 ) was an American neurologist , mainly known for his early experiments on neuraxial blockade in New York City .
Albrecht Fleckenstein ( 3 March 1917 -- 4 April 1992 ) was a German pharmacologist and physiologist best known for his discovery of calcium channel blockers .
Beda Mayr was a Bavarian Benedictine philosopher , apologist , and poet ( born 15 January 1742 at Daiting near Augsburg ; died 28 April 1794 , in the monastery of Heiligenkreuz in Donauworth .
Rudolph Dittrich ( 23 December 1850 , Breslau - 19 December 1922 , Breslau ) was a German entomologist specialising in Coleoptera and Hymenoptera .
Ozias Thurston Linley ( 1765 - -1831 ) was one of seven musical siblings born to the composer Thomas Linley the elder and his wife Mary Johnson .
Thomas Fitzmaurice , 18th Baron Kerry and Baron Lixnaw ( 1574 - -1630 ) was an Irish military leader in the Nine Years ' War .
Da Lam Tserenchimed ( Mongolian : Да лам Цэрэнчимэд , Standard Tibetan : ཏཱ་བླ་མ་ཚེ་རིང་འཆི་མེད། ; 1869 -- 1914 ) was a prominent lama and early 20th century Mongolian independence leader .
Thomas Blague ( or Blage ) ( c.1545 - -1611 ) was an English churchman and author , dean of Rochester from 1592 .
Friedrich Freiherr von Broich ( 1 January 1896 -- 24 September 1974 ) was a German career military officer and panzer commander in World War II . On 12 May 1943 , Von Broich was captured by the British Army along with the remnants of the 10th Panzer Division in Tunisia .
John Alexander MacWilliam ( 31 July 1857 -- 13 January 1937 ) , a physiologist at the University of Aberdeen in the late nineteenth and early twentieth centuries , was a pioneer in the field of cardiac electrophysiology .
Tudur Aled ( c. 1465 - -1525 ) was a late medieval Welsh poet , born in Llansannan , Denbighshire .
Aharon Goldstein ( Hebrew : אהרן גולדשטיין‎‎ , born 19 December 1902 , died 12 October 1976 ) was an Israeli politician who served as a member of the Knesset for the Liberal Party and Gahal between 1963 and 1974 .
George Rowley ( 4 April 1782 -- 5 October 1836 ) was Dean and Master of University College , Oxford and Vice - Chancellor of Oxford University .
Paul Löwinger ( 10 November 1904 -- 17 December 1988 ) was an Austrian actor , theatre manager and writer .
Saints Cantius , Cantianus , and Cantianilla ( all died May 31 , circa 304 AD ) are venerated as saints and martyrs by the Christian church .
Paul Liao ( Chinese : 廖偉志 ; 5 October 1949 -- 20 May 2015 ) was a Taiwanese businessman .
Irene Roberts ( 24 September 1908 - February 1996 ) better known as her professional name Renee Roberts was an English actress who is best remembered for her portrayal of Miss Ursula Gatsby in Fawlty Towers between 1975 and 1979 .
Suzanne Spaak ( 6 July 1905 - 12 August 1944 ) was a World War II French Resistance operative .
Maurice Beddow Bayly MRCS , LRCP ( died 1962 ) was an English physician , anti - vivisection activist , and anti - vaccination campaigner .
John Michael Berning ( 1941 - 2006 ) : librarian , anglican , bell ringer and author .
Rear Admiral John Moresby ( 15 March 1830 -- 12 July 1922 ) was a British Naval Officer who explored the coast of New Guinea and discovered the site of Port Moresby .
Rupert Doone ( born Ernest Reginald Wollfield in Redditch , Worcestershire 1903 -- 1966 ) was a British dancer , choreographer , theatre director , and teacher in London .
Emanuele Gerada ( 18 May 1920 -- 21 January 2011 ) was a Maltese prelate of the Roman Catholic Church and Titular Archbishop of Nomentum .
Hans Ludwig Engel ( 1630 - -22 April 1674 ) was a Roman Catholic canon lawyer , best known as the author of Collegium Universi Juris Canonici .
William Frederick Steuart ( 1816 - -1889 ) was a Maryland - born medical doctor who served in the Confederate States Army during the American Civil War .
Count Sir Luigi Preziosi ( 29 July 1888 -- 30 July 1965 ) was a Maltese politician and a doctor who specialized in ophthalmology .
Yvonne Jammet ( 1900 -- 30 August 1967 ) was a French landscape painter and sculptor , who spent her career in Ireland .
Friedrich Carl Albert Schreuel , also known as Frederik Karel Albert Schreuel and Jan Christian Aelbert Schreuel ( 14 June 1773 -- 1853 ) , was a Dutch - born painter .
Harry Lawrence Bradfer - Lawrence ( 1 April 1887 -- 19 October 1965 ) was an antiquarian with a particular interest in Norfolk and Yorkshire , England .
Victor Serebriakoff ( 17 October 1912 -- 1 January 2000 ) was one of the early members and a leading light of Mensa .
Duan Ye ( simplified Chinese : 段业 ; traditional Chinese : 段業 ; pinyin : Duàn Yè ; died 401 ) was the first king of Northern Liang of the Sixteen Kingdoms period in Chinese history .
Karel Johan Gustav Hartlaub ( 8 November 1814 -- 29 November 1900 ) was a German physician and ornithologist .
Bartholomäus Ziegenbalg ( 10 July 1682 -- 23 February 1719 ) was a member of the Lutheran clergy and the first Pietist missionary to India .
Isaac Beeckman ( 10 December 1588 -- 19 May 1637 ) was a Dutch philosopher and scientist , who , through his studies and contact with leading natural philosophers , may have `` virtually given birth to modern atomism '' .
Tio Tek Djien ( also Djin ; 2 December 1895 -- 17 December 1975 ) , also styled T. D. Tio , Jr. , was a Chinese Indonesian stage manager and playwright turned film producer .
Vinko Coce ( 22 December 1954 -- 27 October 2013 ) was a Croatian opera and pop singer .
Maud de Braose , Baroness Mortimer ( 1224 -- shortly before 23 March 1301 ) was a noble heiress , and one of the most important , being a member of the powerful de Braose family which held many lordships and domains in the Welsh Marches .
Moncure Robinson ( February 2 , 1802- November 10 , 1891 ) was an American civil engineer , railroad planner and builder and a railroad and steamboat owner , who is considered one of America 's leading Antebellum period civil engineers .
Ptolemy II Philadelphus ( Greek : Πτολεμαῖος Φιλάδελφος , Ptolemaîos Philádelphos , 309 - -246 BCE ) was the king of Ptolemaic Egypt from 283 to 246 BCE .
Neil Aggett ( 6 October 1953 , Nanyuki -- 5 February 1982 ) was a white South African medical doctor and trade union organiser who died whilst in detention after being arrested by the South African Security Police .
Lieutenant - General Albemarle Bertie , 9th Earl of Lindsey ( 17 September 1744 -- 17 September 1818 ) was a British nobleman and general .
Sir Bryant Godman Irvine ( 25 July 1909 -- 3 May 1992 ) was a Canadian - born British Conservative politician .
Herman Hotchkiss ( 1 July 1765 -- 20 February 1836 ) was an early settler of East Haven , Connecticut and is credited as founder of Fair Haven , Connecticut .
August Bach ( 30 August 1897 -- 23 March 1966 ) was an East German Christian Democratic politician .
Richard Baret ( died 1401 ) , of Eastgate Street , Gloucester , was an English politician .
Rajab Ali Tabrizi ( died in 1670 ) was an Iranian and Shiat philosopher and mystic of the 17th century .
James Englebert Teschemacher ( b. in Nottingham , England , 11 June 1790 ; d. near Boston , Massachusetts , 9 November 1853 ) was a scientist .
Don Lusher OBE ( 6 November 1923 - 5 July 2006 ) was a jazz and big band trombonist best known for his association with the Ted Heath Big Band .
Dr George Alexander Gibson FRSE FRCPE LLD ( 1854 - -1913 ) was a physician , medical author and amateur geologist .
Edward Brabazon , 1st Baron Ardee ( c.1548 -- 7 August 1625 ) was an Anglo - Irish peer .
Johann Köler ( 8 March 1826 -- 22 April 1899 ) was a leader of the Estonian national awakening and a painter .
Giovanni de Gamerra ( 26 December 1742 -- 29 August 1803 ) was a cleric , a playwright , and a poet .
Michael Davie ( 15 January 1924 Cranleigh , Surrey -- 7 December 2005 , Ewelme , Oxfordshire ) was a British journalist .
Margaret Stevenson Miller ( 1896 -- 1979 ) was a British lecturer and researcher , who campaigned for women 's rights .
Josef Bayer ( 6 March 1852 -- 12 March 1913 ) was an Austrian composer and the director of the Austrian Court Ballet from 1883 until his death .
William I of Baux ( Occitan : Guilhèm dei Bauç , archaic Guillem or Guilhem dels Baus , French : Guillaume des Baux or du Baus , Latin : Guillelmus de Balcio ; c. 1155 -- June 1218 ) was the Prince of Orange from 1182 until his death .
Georg Daniel Teutsch ( December 12 , 1817 , Schässburg , Transylvania - July 2 , 1893 , Hermannstadt , Transylvania ) was a Transylvanian historian and Lutheran ( Augsburg Confession ) bishop .
Dwight James Baum ( 1886 - -1939 ) was an American architect most active in New York and in Sarasota , Florida .
Dr. Michael Philip West ( 1888 -- 1973 ) was an English language teacher and researcher who worked extensively in India in the mid 1900s .
Air Vice Marshal Ian Dougald McLachlan , CB , CBE , DFC ( 23 July 1911 -- 14 July 1991 ) was a senior commander in the Royal Australian Air Force ( RAAF ) .
Dionigi di Borgo San Sepolcro OESA ( Roberti of Roberti , Dennis ) ( c. 1300 -- 31 March 1342 ) was an Augustinian monk who was at one time Petrarch 's confessor , and who taught Boccaccio at the beginning of his education in the humanities .
Sophie Angelika of Württemberg - Oels ( 30 May 1677 - 11 November 1700 ) , was a Duchess of Württemberg - Oels by birth and by marriage Duchess of Saxe - Zeitz - Pegau - Neustadt .
François Dufault ( or Dufaut ) ( before 1604 ( ? ) -- ca . 1672 ? ) was a French lutenist and composer .
Sangeetha Kalanidhi Maharajapuram Santhanam ( Tamil : மகாராஜபுரம் ஸந்தானம் ) , ( December 3 , 1928-June 24 , 1992 ) was one of the great Carnatic music vocalists of the 20th century .
Roland ( Frankish : Hruodland ) ( died 15 August 778 ) was a Frankish military leader under Charlemagne who became one of the principal figures in the literary cycle known as the Matter of France .
Robert Hallam ( aka Alum or Halam ; died 4 September 1417 ) was an English churchman , Bishop of Salisbury and English representative at the Council of Constance .
John Blackwall ( 20 January 1790 -- May 1881 ) was a British naturalist with a particular interest in spiders .
Lady Julia Namier ( also known as Iulia de Beausobre , née Iulia Michaelovna Kazarina ) ( 1893 - 1977 ) was a Russian writer , who married the British historian Lewis Bernstein Namier .
Claudio de Arciniega ( Spanish pronunciation : ( ˈklauðjo ðe arθiˈnjeɣa ) ; c. 1520 - -1593 ) was a Spanish architect and sculptor .
Anders Daae ( 21 April 1838 -- 19 December 1910 ) was a Norwegian prison director .
Abner of Burgos ( ca . 1270 -- ca . 1347 , or a little later ) was a Jewish philosopher , a convert to Christianity and polemical writer against his former religion .
Sighsten Herrgård ( 8 January 1943 -- 20 November 1989 ) was a Finnish - born Swedish fashion designer and major trendsetter in Stockholm .
Nicolau dos Reis Lobato ( 24 May 1946 -- 31 December 1978 ) was an East - Timorese politician and national hero .
Carroll Glenn ( 28 October 1918 -- 25 April 1983 ) was an American violinist and music educator .
Kamalesh Maitra ( 28 April 1928 -- 22 April 2005 ) , often referred to by the title Pandit , was an Indian classical musician , composer and teacher .
Addac or Attaces ( died 418 ) was king of the western Alans in Hispania ( the Iberian Peninsula , modern Spain and Portugal ) .
Sir William Soame , 1st Baronet ( also Soames ) ( c.1645 - -1686 ) was an English translator and diplomat .
William Ermested BD DCanL ( d. 1558 ) was a Canon of Windsor from 1554 - 1558 and Master of the Temple .
Frederick Christian Lewis ( 1779 - -1856 ) was an English etcher , aquatint and stipple engraver , landscape and portrait painter and the brother of Charles Lewis ( 1786 - -1836 ) .

Sydney Watson OBE ( 1903 - -1991 ) was an English church musician .
Vekoslav Grmič ( 4 June 1923 -- 21 March 2005 ) was a Slovenian Roman Catholic bishop and theologian , known for his sympathy towards Socialist ideas .

Jock Young ( 4 March 1942 -- 16 November 2013 ) was a sociologist and criminologist .
Juš Kozak ( 26 June 1892 -- 29 August 1964 ) , also known under the pseudonym Jalanov , was a Slovenian writer , playwright , and editor .
Ernst van Heerden ( 20 March 1916 -- 30 September 1997 ) was a leading Afrikaans poet .
Albino Bernardini ( 18 October 1917 -- 31 March 2015 ) was an Italian writer and pedagogue .
Scorpus ( c. 68 - -95 AD ) was a famous charioteer in Roman times who lived at the end of the 1st century AD .
Kunga Lekpa ( Tibetan : ཀུན་དགའ་ལེགས་པ , Wylie : Kun dga legs pa , 1433 - -1483 ) was a King of Tibet who ruled from 1448 to 1481 .
Malladi Venkata Satyanarayana Rao ( మల్లాది వెంకట సత్యనారాయణ రావు ) ( 6 May 1932 -- 1 November 1996 ) was a violinist and radio artist , honoured with the title Sangeetha Kalanidhi .
David Anthony Hilton Yates , FRCP ( born 15 August 1930 , died 13 September 2004 ) , known as Anthony Yates , was an English rheumatologist and consultant , president of the British Association for Rheumatology and of the Rheumatology and Rehabilitation Section of the Royal Society of Medicine .
Ezekiel Hopkins ( died 1690 ) was an Anglican divine in the Church of Ireland , who was Bishop of Derry from 1681 to 1690 .
Major Samuel Hill Lawrence VC ( 22 January 1831 -- 17 June 1868 ) , born in Cork , was an Irish recipient of the Victoria Cross , the highest and most prestigious award for gallantry in the face of the enemy that can be awarded to British and Commonwealth forces .
Mary Olive Edis , later Edis - Galsworthy ( 3 September 1876 - 28 December 1955 ) was a British photographer who was famous for autochrome phototographs and portrait photography .
William Ludlam ( 1717 - -1788 ) was an English clergyman and mathematician .
Matti Oravisto ( 23 October 1921 -- 15 November 2001 ) was a Finnish actor who appeared in theatre , film and television .
Charles Deslondes was one of the slave leaders of the 1811 German Coast Uprising , a slave revolt that began on January 8 , 1811 , in the Territory of Orleans .
Air Vice - Marshal John Frederick Powell OBE ( 12 June 1915 -- 24 November 2008 ) was a long - serving officer at RAF College Cranwell .
Walter Tennyson ( 1899 - 1980 ) was a British actor and film director of the silent era .
Mehmet Cevat Abbas Gürer ( 1887 -- July 4 , 1943 ) was an officer of the Ottoman Army and Turkish Army .
Edward C. Krause ( December 14 , 1914 -- November 20 , 1950 ) was an American politician and businessman from Wisconsin .

Bhabesh Chandra Sanyal commonly known as B. C. Sanyal ( 22 April 1901 -- 9 August 2003 ) , the doyen of modernism in Indian art , was an Indian painter and sculptor and an Art teacher to three generations of artists .

Johnny Almond ( 29 July 1946 -- 18 November 2009 ) was a British musician , who is best known for his recordings with the Alan Price Set , Fleetwood Mac , John Mayall and Mark - Almond .
Joseph Crane Hartzell ( 1 June 1842 -- 6 September 1929 ) was an American Missionary Bishop of the Methodist Episcopal Church who served in the United States and in Africa .
Stephen Lefeaver ( born 1791 in Marden , Kent ; died 26 July 1867 in Marden ) was an English first - class cricketer associated with Kent who was active in the 1820s .
Jonathan Dymond ( 1796 - -1828 ) was an English Quaker and an ethical philosopher who is known for his monograph An Enquiry into the Accordancy of War with the Principles of Christianity .

Queen Tufa ( 禿髮王后 , personal name unknown ) ( died 423 ) was a queen of the Chinese / Xianbei state Western Qin .
Rabbi Jacob Pollak ( other common spelling Yaakov Pollack ) was the founder of the Polish method of halakhic and Talmudic study known as the Pilpul ; born about 1460 ; died at Lublin in 1541 .
Elazar Abuhatzeira ( 9 August 1948 -- 29 July 2011 ) was an Orthodox Sefardi rabbi and kabbalist , known among his followers as the `` Baba Elazar . ''

Adolph F. Meyer ( c. 1899 -- 1988 ) is an American pastor who died in Newark , New Jersey .
Otto , Lord of Arkel ( c. 1330 -- 26 March or 1 April 1396 ) was Lord of Arkel from 6 May 1360 until his death .
Arthur Coulin ( 20 September 1869 -- 9 November 1912 ) was an Austro - Hungarian Romanian painter and art critic .
Sir Thomas Nott ( 11 December 1606 -- 1681 ) was an English royalist army officer and an original fellow of the Royal Society .
Lorraine Fox ( 1922 - -1976 ) was an American illustrator and commercial artist who illustrated magazines , book covers , and advertisements .
Gotthard Deutsch ( 31 January 1859 -- 14 October 1921 ) , also spelled Gottard Deutsch , was a scholar of Jewish history .
Lionel Eric Hayward ( more commonly known as Eric Hayward ; 2 August 1917 -- 1976 ) was an English professional footballer who played as a defender .
Conny Vandenbos ( 16 January 1937 -- 7 April 2002 ) was a popular Dutch singer .
Maurice Loyal Huggins ( 19 September 1897 - 17 December 1981 ) was a scientist who independently conceived the idea of hydrogen bonding and who was an early advocate for their role in stabilizing protein secondary structure .
Henry Curtis Meanor ( or H. Curtis Meanor , 1929 - -2008 ) was a former United States federal judge .
Sanshi Imai ( 今井 三子 , 1900 - -1976 ) was a Japanese mycologist of Hokkaido Imperial University .
The Dryburne Martyrs , Richard Hill , Richard Holiday , John Hogg and Edmund Duke ( all died 27 May 1590 ) were English Roman Catholic priests and martyrs , executed at Dryburne , County Durham , in the reign of Elizabeth I. Not much is known of their early lives .
Kenneth Steel ( RBA , SGA , 9 July 1906 -- 1970 ) was a British artist creating works of art primarily in watercolor .
Cécile Cerf ( 12 January 1916 -- 29 December 1973 ) was a member of the French Resistance during World War II . During World War II , Cerf played an active role in the Main - d'œuvre immigrée groups under the aegis of the FTP - MOI resistance movement .
Alfred Klee ( 25 January 1875 - 10 November 1943 ) was the younger associate of Theodor Herzl and one of the earliest leaders of German Zionism .
Chong Chee Kin ( c.1973 -- 1 November 2012 ) was a Singaporean journalist who worked for The Straits Times .
Ignacy Hryniewiecki ( Russian : Игнатий Иоахимович Гриневицкий ; Ignaty Ioakhimovich Grinevitsky ; 1856 -- 13 March 1881 ) ( Party name : Kotik , Russian for `` Kitten '' ) was a member of the People 's Will and the principal assassin of Tsar Alexander II of Russia .
Leszek of Dobrzyń ( pl : Leszek dobrzyński ; bef . 1302 - bef . 10 July 1316 ) , was a Polish prince member of the House of Piast and Duke of Dobrzyń during 1312 - 1316 with his brothers .
Suzanne Gabriello ( born Suzanne Yvonne Henriette Marie Galopet ; 24 January 1932 -- died 9 August 1992 ) was a French singer and actress .
The Reverend William Wilks ( 1843 - -1923 ) was a notable British horticulturalist and clergyman .
René Sommer ( 1951 - 5 October 2009 ) was a Swiss inventor and computer programmer , credited as a co - inventor of the computer mouse .
Martin Berkofsky ( 9 April 1943 -- 30 December 2013 ) was an American classical pianist , known primarily for his interpretations of music by Franz Liszt and Alan Hovhaness .
Gigi Reder ( 25 March 1928 -- 8 October 1998 ) was an Italian character actor , best known for the role of Filini in the Fantozzi film series .
Lill Tschudi ( 1911 - -2004 ) was a Swiss artist associated with the Grosvenor School of Modern Art .
Colleen Madamombe ( born 1964 , died 31-May-2009 ) was a Zimbabwean sculptor .
Kostas Papachristos ( Greek : Κώστας Παπαχρήστος ; 1916 -- 1995 ) was a Greek actor who was known for his comedic acting roles .
Adam von Trautmannsdorf ( 1579 - 1617 ) , kaiserlicher Kämmerer und oberster Kriegsrat , general of the Croatian and Austrian Littoral .
William Hilton RA ( 3 June 1786 -- 30 December 1839 ) , was an English portrait and history painter .
Sir Ralph Winwood ( c. 1563 -- 27 October 1617 ) was an English diplomat and statesman to the Jacobean court .
Eileen Colgan ( 1933/1934 -- 10 March 2014 ) was an Irish theatre , television and film actress .
Dragut ( Turkish : Turgut Reis ) ( 1485 -- 23 June 1565 ) was an Ottoman Greek Admiral and privateer who also served as Bey of Algiers ;
Sesson Shukei ( orig . Satake Heizo ) ( 1504 - 1589 ) was a Japanese Zen monk and painter from the Muromachi period born in what is modern day Ibaragi Prefecture .
Albert de Rippe ( Alberto da Ripa ) ( c. 1500 - -1551 ) was an Italian lutenist and composer .
Beryl Mercer ( 13 August 1882 -- 28 July 1939 ) was an actress of stage and screen who was based in the United States .
Samuel Mugglestone ( 1765 -- 11 December 1839 ) was an English professional cricketer who made 3 known appearances in major cricket matches from 1789 to 1791 .
Richenza of Northeim ( c. 1087/1089 -- 10 June 1141 ) , a member of the comital House of Northeim , was Duchess of Saxony from 1106 , German queen ( formally Queen of the Romans ) from 1125 and Holy Roman Empress from 1133 until the death of her husband Lothair of Supplinburg in 1137 .
Maestro Aldo Piga was a music composer from 1928 to 1994 in New York , USA .
Taillefer embarked from the shore of Normandy where the Allies landed on D - Day in World War II . The Battle of Hastings was on 14 October 1066 , and Taillefer died on that day ;
Ndre Mjeda ( 20 November 1866 -- 1 August 1937 ) was an Albanian poet and activist .
Thomas Nugent , 6th Earl of Westmeath KP PC ( Ire ) ( April 1714 -- 7 September 1792 ) , styled Lord Delvin from 1752 to 1754 was an Irish peer and freemason .
Faye Tso ( 1933 - 2004 ) was a Navajo potter and herbal medicine healer .
Pierino Baffi ( 15 September 1930 -- 27 March 1985 ) was an Italian road bicycle racer from Vailate .
William Brace ( 23 September 1865 -- 12 October 1947 ) was a Welsh trade unionist and Liberal and Labour politician .
Patrick Gwynne ( 1913 - -2003 ) was a British modernist architect with Welsh roots , best known for designing and building The Homewood , which he left to the National Trust in 2003 .
Ciril Cvetko ( 8 January 1920 -- 18 January 1999 ) was a Slovene composer and conductor , brother of the musicologist Dragotin Cvetko .
Thomas Bull ( c. 1605 -- October 12 , 1684 ) , also known as Captain Thomas Bull , was an early settler in the Connecticut Colony who is counted as one of the founders of Hartford , Connecticut .
Edward Wilkinson ( 1846 - -1918 ) was an American naturalist and museum curator .
Harvey H. Cluff ( 1836 - -1916 ) was a business , civic and educational leader in late-19th - century Provo , Utah .
Roderick Macalpine Downie ( ca . 1934 - -1986 ) was an English multihull sailboat designer and sailor .
Carlos Arzani ( 27 November 1909 -- 30 January 1952 ) was an Argentine driver , born in Buenos Aires , who raced private Alfa Romeos , mostly in South America .
George Cedric Wright ( April 13 , 1889 -- 1959 ) was an American violinist and wilderness photographer of the High Sierra .
Duke Nicholas of Württemberg ( German : Herzog Nikolaus von Württemberg ; 1 March 1833 -- 22 February 1903 ) was an officer in the army of the Austrian Empire .
Abram Newman ( 1736 - -1799 ) ( aka Abraham Newman ) was a partner in one of the leading grocers in 18th century London that imported a wide range of produce including tea , coffee , sugar and spices .
Roy Finlayson ( 31 March 1909 -- 19 July 1997 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Mund and Maire , Johannes Ludwig Leopold Mund ( 1791 Berlin - 1831 ) and Louis Maire , also born in Berlin of French parents , were two natural history collectors who arrived in the Cape Colony on 13 October 1816 , and were sponsored by the Museum of Natural History in Berlin .
Haim - Moshe Shapira ( Hebrew : חיים משה שפירא‎ , 26 March 1902 -- 16 July 1970 ) was a key Israeli politician in the early days of the state 's existence .
Francis Rawdon Chesney ( 16 March 1789 -- 30 January 1872 ) was a British general and explorer .
Thomas Baynham ( 1536 - 1611 ) was Lord of the Manor of Clearwell , in the Forest of Dean , Gloucestershire .
Andrew Vázsonyi ( 1916 - -2003 ) , also known as Endre Weiszfeld and Zepartzatt Gozinto ) was a mathematician and operations researcher .
Karl Fabel ( born October 20 , 1905 -- 3 March 1975 Pischertshofen ) is considered to have been one of the most ingenious chess composers .
Dirk Bach ( 23 April 1961 -- 1 October 2012 ) was a German television comedy actor , best known as co - host of Ich bin ein Star --
Nils Holmer ( 1904 - -1994 ) was a Swedish linguist who carried out significant fieldwork into the Scottish Gaelic , in particular the southern dialects of Kintyre , Arran and Argyll and published several key books and articles on the topic .
Sri Paduka Tuanku Sultan Otteman II Perkasa ' Alam Shah ibni al - Marhum Sultan ' Amal ud - din al - Sani Perkasa ' Alam Shah ( 1945 - 1967 ) was a former Sultan of Deli , in which the kingdom 's capital was Medan , in North Sumatra .
Pieter Cramer ( 21 May 1721 ( baptized ) -- 28 September 1776 ) , was a wealthy Dutch merchant in linen and Spanish wool , remembered as an entomologist .
Robert Waithman ( 1764 -- 6 February 1833 ) , Lord Mayor of London , was born at Wrexham .
Sir Edward Bashe ( died 12 May 1653 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons between 1628 and 1640 .
Wanda Błeńska , also spelled Wanda Blenska ( 30 October 1911 -- 27 November 2014 ) , was a Polish leprosy expert and missionary who succeeded to develop the Buluba Hospital in Uganda into an internationally recognized centre for leprosy treatment .
Giulio Quaglio III ( 1764 in Laino -- 30 January 1801 in Munich ) was a scenic designer and architect from a branch of the Quaglio family of artists that moved to Germany in the 18th Century and was the last to be born in the family 's home town .
Paddy Bedford ( circa 1922 -- 14 July 2007 ) , aka `` Goowoomji '' , was a contemporary Indigenous Australian artist from Warmun in the Kimberley , and one of eight Australian artists selected for an architectural commission for the Musée du quai Branly .
Li Xiaowen ( Chinese : 李小文 ; pinyin : Lǐ Xiǎowén ; 2 March 1947 -- 10 January 2015 ) , also known as `` Shoes academician '' ( Chinese : 布鞋院士 ) and `` Sweeping monk '' ( Chinese : 扫地僧 ) , was a Chinese scientist and professor at Beijing Normal University .
Menko Bormanzhinov ( 1855 -- 1919 ) was a Buddhist priest of Kalmyk origin who was born in the Bokshirgankan aimak in the Salsk District of the Don Cossack Host sometime in 1855 .
Saint Perpetuus ( French : Saint - Perpetue ) ( died December 30 , 490 AD ) was the sixth Bishop of Tours , from 460 to 490 .
Vice Admiral Sir ( Frank ) Forrester Rose KCB DSO ( 1878 -- 3 March 1955 ) was a Royal Navy officer who went on to be Commander - in - Chief , East Indies Station .
Reşid Mehmed Pasha , also known as Kütahı ( Greek : Μεχμέτ Ρεσίτ πασάς Κιουταχής , 1780 - -1839 ) , was a prominent Ottoman statesman and general who reached the post of Grand Vizier in the first half of the 19th century , playing an important role in the Greek War of Independence .
Charles Golding Constable ( 1821 - -1878 ) was a member of the British East India Company 's navy , joining up in his youth .
Jacob Philipp Hackert ( 15 September 1737 -- 28 April 1807 ) was a landscape painter from Brandenburg , who did most of his work in Italy .
Ken Carlon ( 5 October 1923 -- 5 January 2004 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Datuk Abdullah Hussain ( 25 March 1920 -- 31 December 2014 ) was a Malaysian novelist and writer .
Mael Ruanaidh Ua Dubhda , died 1005 .
Gailene Stock ( 28 January 1946 -- 29 April 2014 ) CBE AM was an Australian - born ballerina , teacher and Director of the Royal Ballet School in Covent Garden .
Rosario E. Aguilar ( ca . 1792 -- 1847 ) was an early settler of San Diego , California .
Thomas Manners , 1st Earl of Rutland , 12th Baron de Ros of Helmsley ( c. 1492 -- 20 September 1543 ) , KG , of Belvoir Castle , Rutland , was created Earl of Rutland by King Henry VIII in 1525 .
Prince Bernhard of Saxe - Weimar - Eisenach ( Bernhard Carl Alexander Hermann Heinrich Wilhelm Oscar Friedrich Franz Peter ; 18 April 1878 -- 1 October 1900 ) was a member of the Grand Ducal House of Saxe - Weimar - Eisenach and a Lieutenant in the Prussian Army .
Malcolm Fleming , 3rd Lord Fleming ( c. 1494 -- 10 September 1547 ) , was Lord Chamberlain of Scotland to King James V , from 1524 .
Charles Jean Baptiste Collin - Mezin ( 1841 - -1923 ) was a distinguished French maker of violins , violas , cellos , basses and bows .
James Bainham ( died 1532 ) was an English lawyer and Protestant reformer , burned as a heretic in 1532 .
Johannes Thienemann ( 12 November 1863 -- 12 April 1938 ) was a German ornithologist and a pioneer bird bander who established the Rossitten Bird Observatory , the world 's first .
Humayun Ahmed ( pronounced : ( ɦumae̯un aɦmed̪ ) ; 13 November 1948 -- 19 July 2012 ) was a Bangladeshi writer , dramatist , screenwriter and filmmaker .
After the early death of his father , Ocko II tom Brok ( 1407 - -1435 ) was Chieftain of the Brokmerland and the Auricherland in East Frisia ( initially under the guardianship of his grandmother , Foelke ) .
William Henry James Blakemore ( 1871 , in West Midlands Birmingham , England -- 1945 ) was an English engraver , and medallist at the Royal Mint London .
Amon Bazira ( 1944 - -1993 ) was a Pan - Africanist leader and organiser who created an extensive intelligence network that was a clandestine component of the struggle to end the regime of Ugandan military dictator and president , Idi Amin .
Sulev Nõmmik ( 11 January 1931 , in Tallinn -- 28 July 1992 , in Kuressaare ) was an Estonian theatre and movie director , actor , humorist and comedian .
Bidit Lal Das ( 15 June 1938 -- 8 October 2012 ) , commonly known as Potol Babu , was a popular Bangladeshi folk singer and composer from Sylhet .
Tore Johansson ( 19 October 1903 -- 12 May 1971 ) , better known by the stage name Tor Johnson , was a Swedish professional wrestler ( billed as The Super Swedish Angel ) and actor .
Ted Shiels ( 25 June 1908 -- 9 October 1987 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Oskar Halecki ( 26 May 1891 , Vienna -- 17 September 1973 , White Plains , New York ) was a Polish historian , social and Catholic activist .
James Alday ( 1516 - 1576 ? ) was a 16th - century English navigator , explorer and privateer .
Otto Carl Friedrich Westphal ( 1800 -- 1879 ) was a German physician and Geheimer Sanitätsrath ( privy medical counsellor ) .
Francis Tallents ( 1619 - -1708 ) was a non - conforming English Presbyterian clergyman .
After reigning over Hindustani classical music genre , for five decades , as the Queen of Thumri , Shobha Gurtu died on 27 September 2004 , and was survived by her two sons .
Lauriston S. Taylor ( 1 June 1902 - 26 November 2004 ) was an American physicist known for his work in the field of radiation protection and measurement .
Saint Richard Reynolds , O.Ss . S ( c. 1492 -- 4 May 1535 ) was an English Brigittine monk executed in London for refusing the Oath of Supremacy to King Henry VIII of England .
John Freningham ( 1345 - -1410 ) was an English politician and a member of Parliament for Kent .
Augusta Amherst Austen ( 2 August 1827 -- 5 August 1877 ) was a British organist and composer , chiefly of hymns .
Thomas Clifford , 8th Baron de Clifford , also 8th Lord of Skipton ( 25 March 1414 -- 22 May 1455 ) , was the elder son of John , 7th Baron de Clifford , and Elizabeth Percy , daughter of Henry `` Hotspur '' Percy and Elizabeth Mortimer .
Sir Arthur Lasenby Liberty ( 13 August 1843 -- 11 May 1917 ) was a London merchant , and the founder of Liberty & Co. Born in Chesham , Buckinghamshire , England , the son of a draper , he began work at sixteen with an uncle who sold lace , and later another uncle who sold wine .
Katriel Katz was an Israeli diplomat who died in 1988 at the age of 80 .
William Herbert , 1st Baron Powis ( c.1573 -- 7 March 1655 ) was a Welsh politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1597 and 1629 .
George Edward Hughes ( 8 June 1918 -- 4 March 1994 ) was a philosopher and logician whose principal scholarly works were concerned with modal logic and medieval philosophy .
John Bernard O'Hara ( 29 October 1862 - 31 March 1927 ) was an Australian poet and schoolmaster .
Ralph de Diceto ( d. ca . 1202 ) was archdeacon of Middlesex , dean of St Paul 's Cathedral ( from ca . 1180 ) , and author of two chronicles , the Abbreviationes chronicorum and the Ymagines historiarum .
Adrian Hearn ( 16 March 1920 -- 18 October 1993 ) is a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton and Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Alwyn Lindsay ( 4 June 1923 -- 24 August 2001 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Geelong in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Mike McCluskie ( ? -1871 ) was a little - known gambler and occasional lawman from Ohio , who was the instigator of the Gunfight at Hide Park , which took place on August 19 , 1871 , in Newton , Kansas .
Jan Janz Slop , or Jan Slob ( 1643 , Edam -- 1727 ) , was a Dutch Golden Age painter .
Constantin Tobescu ( 1893 -- 1951 ) was a Romanian general of the Romanian Gendarmerie ( Jandarmeria ) during World War II , deserter on August 23 , 1944 , one of the principal executors of Antonescu 's racial purity policies .
John Boyd Dunlop ( 5 February 1840 -- 23 October 1921 ) was a Scottish - born and educated inventor and veterinary surgeon who spent most of his career in Ireland .
John Wharlton Bunney ( 20 June 1828 -- 23 September 1882 ) was an English topographical and landscape artist of the nineteenth century .
Lieutenant General Edward Wolfe ( 1685 - -26 March 1759 ) was a British army officer who saw action in the War of the Spanish Succession , 1715 Jacobite Rebellion and the War of Jenkins Ear .
Lloyd Chandler ( 1896 - -1978 ) was an American Appalachian Folk musician and Free Will Baptist preacher from Madison County , North Carolina .
Abundius of Umbria ( died 303 ) was a deacon and martyr during the Diocletian persecution .
John Fursdon , in religion Cuthbert ( died 1638 ) , was an English Benedictine monk .
John St Clair , Master of Sinclair ( 5 December 1683 -- 2 November 1750 ) was a Scottish noble and Tory politician .
Janusz Kurczab ( 6 September 1937 -- 11 April 2015 ) was a Polish fencer , mountaineer and expedition leader .
Alan Solem , full name George Alan Solem ( 21 June 1931 -- 26 . March 1990 ) was an American malacologist , a biologist who studied mollusks .
William Parr , 1st Baron Parr of Horton ( c. 1483 -- 10 September 1547 ) was the son of William Parr , 1st Baron Parr of Kendal and his second wife , the Hon . Elizabeth Fitzhugh , later Lady Vaux of Harrowden .
John Handfield ( circa 1693 - 1787 ) was a British military officer , member of the Nova Scotia Council , and office holder .
Frederick W. Stavely ( 1894 - 1976 ) was a researcher at the Firestone Tire & Rubber Company who in 1953 , while investigating the reaction of butyl lithium on butadiene discovered that polymerization of isoprene with metallic lithium produced polyisoprene ( dubbed `` coral rubber '' because of its appearance ) with a high cis content .
Pessah Bar - Adon ( Hebrew : פסח בר - אדון ; b. 1907 , d. 1985 ) was a Polish - born , Israeli archaeologist and writer .
Sir Thomas Bathe , 1st Baron Louth ( died 1478 ) , was an Irish peer and judge of the fifteenth century .
John Burdett Wittenoom ( 24 October 1788 -- 23 January 1855 ) was a colonial clergyman who was the second Anglican clergyman to perform religious services in the Swan River Colony , Australia , soon after its establishment in 1829 .
Mahendradatta ( 961 - -1011 CE ) , also known as Gunapriyadharmapatni , was the queen of Bali , the queen consort of Udayana Warmadewa , also popularly known as King Udayana from Warmadewa dynasty .
George Adams Kaufmann , also George Adams and George von Kaufmann , ( 8 February 1894 , Maryampol , Galicia , then part of the Austro - Hungarian Empire -- 30 March 1963 , Edgbaston , UK ) was a British mathematician , translator and anthroposophist .
Mina Klabin Warchavchik ( born 1896 - death 1969 ) was a Brazilian landscape architect .
Pat Darling ( born 31 August 1913 , Casino , New South Wales , Australia -- died 2007 ) was an Australian servicewoman and nursing sister with the 2/10th Australian General Hospital .
Irene McCormack RSJ ( 21 August 1938 -- 21 May 1991 ) was an Australian member of the Sisters of St Joseph of the Sacred Heart who worked as a missionary in Peru .
Johannes Klencke , van Klenck or Klenckius ( bapt . 5 March 1620 , Amsterdam - early 1672 , Batavia , Dutch East Indies ) was a Dutch teacher in philosophy at the Athenaeum Illustre in Amsterdam .
Frédéric Pelletier ( 1 May 1870 -- 30 May 1944 ) was a Canadian choir conductor , music educator , composer , music critic , journalist , civil servant , military officer , and physician .
John Humphreys Davies ( 15 April 1871 -- 10 August 1926 ) was a Welsh lawyer , bibliographer and educator .
Aemilia Laracuen ( Emilia MacKinley ) ( 1925 -- 2007 ) was an American artist and muse of poet Robert Graves Aemilia Laracuen inspired many of Graves 's love poems and was also the illustrator of one of his best - known poetry anthologies , Love Respelt .
Szymon Goldberg ( 1 June 1909 -- 19 July 1993 ) was a Polish - born classical violinist and conductor , latterly an American .
Gómez González de Manzanedo ( died 12 October 1182 ) was a Castilian magnate who governed Calahorra and defended the border with Navarre in the 1150s and 1160s .
Enrico Coleman ( 21 June 1846 -- 14 February 1911 ) was an Italian painter of British nationality .
Edmund the Martyr ( also known as St Edmund or Edmund of East Anglia , died 20 November 869 ) was king of East Anglia from about 855 until his death .
Richard Charles Guthridge ( 11 June 1837 -- 13 October 1934 ) was a British merchant seaman and was recognised in 1998 by the Premier of Victoria in Australia as one of the earliest and most significant pioneers of the State .
Ralph Latham ( 17 October 1924 -- 11 June 2012 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Hilderic ( 460s -- 533 ) was the penultimate king of the Vandals and Alans in North Africa in Late Antiquity ( 523 - -530 ) .
Massimo Pilotti ( 1 August 1879 -- 29 April 1962 ) was an Italian jurist and judge .
Pierre Labatut , also known as Pedro Labatut ( Cannes 1776 - Salvador 1849 ) was a French general who fought in the Brazilian War of Independence .
Lillias Rumsey Sanford ( 1850 - 1940 ) was the founder of Rumsey Hall School , the second private nondenominational pre - preparatory school in the United States , originally located in Seneca Falls , New York .
Mercy Williams ( Malayalam:മേഴ്സി വില്ല്യംസ് ; c. 1947 -- 19 November 2014 ) , a teacher turned politician , was the 16th Mayor of Kochi , Kerala , and the first woman to hold that position in Kochi .
Tore Hedin ( 7 January 1927 -- 22 August 1952 ) was a Swedish mass murderer , spree killer and police officer .
Shi Zhi ( Chinese : 石祇 ; died 351 ) was briefly , for about one year , an emperor of the Chinese / Jie state Later Zhao .
Lena Smedsaas ( 20 March 1951 -- 6 January 2014 ) was a Swedish journalist and writer .
Eustace the Monk ( Old French : Eustache le Moine ; c. 1170 -- 24 August 1217 ) , born Eustace Busket , was a mercenary and pirate , in the tradition of medieval outlaws .
Mustafa Rahi , ( 1931 - -1986 ) was a poet of classical and neo classical Urdu Ghazal from Pakistan .
Silas Tertius Rand Bill ( September 9 , 1842 in Liverpool , Nova Scotia- December 1890 ) was a Nova Scotia born politician , merchant , shipowner and glass sculptor .
Ormond Aebi ( 1916 -- July 2004 ) was an American beekeeper who was reported to have set the world 's record for honey obtained from a single hive in one year , 1974 , when 404 pounds of honey were harvested , breaking an unofficial 80-year - old record of 303 pounds held by A. I. Root .
Hannibal Potter ( 1592 - -1664 ) was an English clergyman and college head in Oxford during the First English Civil War .
Bartolomé Maximiliano Moré ( 24 August 1919 -- 19 February 1963 ) , known as Benny Moré , was a famous Cuban singer .
Abu al - Abbas al - Azafi or in full Abu al - Abbas Ahmad abu Abdallah Muhammad ibn Ahmad al - Lakhmi al - Sabti ( 1162 - -1236 ) was a religious and legal scholar and member of the Banu al - Azafi who ruled Ceuta in the 13th century .
Fan Changjiang ( simplified Chinese : 范长江 ; traditional Chinese : 范長江 ; 6 October 1909 -- 23 October 1970 ) , born Fan Xitian ( 范希天 ) , was a Chinese journalist and writer .
Basil Salvadore D'Souza ( Konkani : बासिल साल्वादोर डी सोझा ( Devanagari ) , ಬಸಿಲ್ ಸಲ್ವದೊರೆ ದ ಒಜ ( Kannada ) ; 23 May 1926 -- 5 September 1996 ) was the Bishop of the Roman Catholic Diocese of Mangalore from 22 March 1965 until his death on 5 September 1996 .
Olof Åhlström ( 15 August 1756 -- 11 August 1835 ) was a Swedish civil servant , composer and music publisher .
Adolf Bastian ( 26 June 1826 -- 2 February 1905 ) was a 19th - century polymath best remembered for his contributions to the development of ethnography and the development of anthropology as a discipline .
Hui Cheung - ching , SBS , JP ( 4 September 1942 , Puning , Guangdong , China -- 6 January 2005 , Hong Kong ) was the member of the Legislative Council of Hong Kong in 1998 - -2004 for the Import and Export constituency .
Karl Jónsson ( 1135 - -1213 ) was an Icelandic writer , poet and clergyman .
Isa Meireles ( c. 1932 -- 27 August 2008 ) was a Portuguese journalist , reporter and writer .
Roland Shaw , born Roland Edgar Shaw - Tomkins , ( 26 May 1920 - 11 May 2012 ) was an English composer , musical arranger , and orchestra leader .
Prof William Mackay Davidson FRSE RSM ( 1909 - 1991 ) was a Scottish pathologist , haematologist and expert on human chromosomes .
Francesco Laudadio ( 2 January 1950 -- 6 April 2005 ) was an Italian director , screenwriter and producer .
Makhdoom Jahaniyan Jahangasht ( مخدوم سید جہانیاں جہانگشت البخاری ) ( b 1308- d 1384 ) was a famous Sufi saint from the South Asia .
Ferdinand August Maria Franz von Ritgen ( 11 October 1787 -- 14 April 1867 ) was a German obstetrician born in the Westphalian village of Wulfen ( now part of Dorsten ) .
Sabri Kalkandelen ( 1862 , Kalkandelen , Ottoman Empire -- 8 April 1943 , Istanbul , Turkey ) was a poet and chief of the Istanbul Imperial Library .
William Cornysh the Younger ( also spelled Cornyshe or Cornish ) ( 1465 -- October 1523 ) was an English composer , dramatist , actor , and poet .
Juan de Tecto ( born in Ghent , 1468 ; died in Honduras , 1526 ) was a Flemish missionary to the New World .
Per Lütken was a Danish glassmaker ( 1916 - -1998 ) , most famous for his works at Holmegaard Glass Factory ( `` Holmegaard Glasværk '' in Danish ) .
Vlado Singer ( born ; 21 October 1908 -- October 1943 ) was a Kingdom of Yugoslavia politician and a prominent member of the Croatian Ustaše movement .
Karl Touton ( 2 May 1858 , Alzey -- 27 September 1934 , Wiesbaden ) was a German dermatologist and amateur botanist .
Wilson Roy Wheeler ( 1905 - 1988 ) was an Australian postman and professional ornithologist .
Vladimir Davydov ( December 14 ( O.S. December 2 ) 1871 -- December 27 ( O.S. December 14 ) 1906 ) was the second son of Lev and Alexandra Davidov and nephew , as well as lover , of the composer Pyotr Ilyich Tchaikovsky , who called him `` Bob '' .
Ni Yuanlu ( Chinese : 倪元璐 ; pinyin : Ní Yuánlù ; Wade -- Giles : Ni Yüan - lu ; ca . 1593 - 1644 ) was a high - ranking official , calligrapher , and painter during the Ming dynasty of Chinese history .
Gerald Vann , O.P. ( 24 August 1906 - 14 July 1963 ) was a British Roman Catholic theologian and philosopher .
Daniel Watson ( c 1617 - June 1683 ) was an English lawyer and politician who sat in the House of Commons in 1659 and 1660 .
Roberto Frassinelli ( 1811 - -1887 ) was a German archaeologist , naturalist , bibliophile , and a draftsman .
James Cornwalsh ( died 1441 ) was an Irish judge who held the office of Chief Baron of the Irish Exchequer .
Rajendra Kumar Tuli ( 20 July 1929 -- 12 July 1999 ) was an Indian film actor who starred in Bollywood films .
Stoigniew ( died October 16 , 955 ) was an Obotrite leader , reigning in the middle of the tenth century .
Alberto Jonás ( June 8 , 1868 , Madrid -- November 10 , 1943 , Philadelphia ) was a Spanish pianist , composer , and piano pedagogue .
Dame Julia Myra Hess , DBE ( 25 February 1890 -- 25 November 1965 ) was a British pianist .
Aina Erlander ( born Andersson ; 28 September 1902 -- 24 February 1990 ) was a Swedish lecturer .
Bruce Belfrage ( 30 October 1900 -- August 1974 ) was an English actor , BBC newsreader and British Liberal Party politician .
Anthony , Duke of Brabant , also known as Antoine de Brabant , Antoine de Bourgogne and Anthony of Burgundy ( August 1384 -- 25 October 1415 , at the battle of Agincourt ) , was Duke of Brabant , Lothier and Limburg .
Isidoro Diéguez Dueñas ( 19 January 1909 -- 21 January 1942 ) was a Spanish bricklayer who joined the Spanish Communist Party , fought in the Spanish Civil War ( 1936 - -39 ) and went into exile .
On the night of 30 June/1 July 1999 , in the operations to capture Point 4812 , Lieutenant Keishing Clifford Nongrum was tasked to assault the feature from South - Eastern direction .
Claude Cornish ( 31 August 1888 -- 25 June 1975 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Professor Hellmut Wolff ( 30 March 1906 - 22 March 1986 ) , was a German academic , mystic , Germanic revivalist , and most notably a Pendulum dowser .
José Joaquín de Viana ( 1718 - -1773 ) was a Spanish military and political figure , Governor of Montevideo between 1751 and 1764 and 1771 and 1773 .
Tibor Gánti ( 10 September 1933 -- 15 April 2009 ) was a Hungarian theoretical biologist and biochemist , who is best known for the chemoton , a model for defining the minimal nature of life .
Jan Boldingh ( 3 January 1915 , Buitenzorg -- 4 August 2003 , Schiedam ) was a noted Dutch chemist .
William Lowther , 1st Earl of Lonsdale KG ( 29 December 1757 -- 19 March 1844 ) was a British Tory politician and nobleman .
William Plender , 1st Baron Plender GCB JP DL ( 20 August 1861 -- 19 January 1946 ) , known as Sir William Plender between 1911 and 1923 and as Sir William Plender , Bt , between 1923 and 1931 , was a British chartered accountant and public servant .
Charles Henry Hamilton Wright ( 9 March 1836 , Dublin -- 22 March 1909 ) was an Irish Anglican clergyman .
Tawfiq Canaan ( Arabic : توفيق كنعان‎ ) ( 24 September 1882 -- 15 January 1964 ) was a pioneering physician , medical researcher , ethnographer and Palestinian nationalist .
Jane Evans ( 1907 - -2004 ) was the Executive Director of the National Federation of Temple Sisterhoods ( now the Women of Reform Judaism ) from 1933 to 1976 .
Rudra Pratap Singh ( died 1531 ) was the founder and first raja of the kingdom that became the princely state of Orchha , India , during the British Raj era .
Jean Chamoux ( 1925 - -2007 ) was a French photographer who started his career during World War II in the Savoyard bush .
Írgalach mac Conaing Cuirre ( died 702 ) , also called Írgalach ua Conaing , was a King of Brega from the Uí Chonaing sept of Cnogba ( Knowth ) of the Síl nÁedo Sláine branch of the southern Ui Neill .
William Leader Maberly ( 1798 - -1885 ) spent most of his life as a British army officer and Whig politician .
Albert Worthy ( 1 November 1905 -- 1 February 1978 ) was an English professional footballer who made 332 appearances in the Football League playing for Chesterfield , Lincoln City , Southend United and Rochdale .
Andrew Pryce Jackman ( 1946 -- 16 August 2003 ) was a keyboard player and arranger .
Leslie Edgley ( 1912 - -2002 ) was a mystery fiction writer .
Louis H. Asbury ( 1877 - -1975 ) was an American architect , a leading architect of Charlotte , North Carolina .
Gérard Debreu ( French : ( dəbʁø ) ; 4 July 1921 -- 31 December 2004 ) was a French - born American economist and mathematician .
Zachary Hickes ( 1739 -- 25 May 1771 ) was a Royal Navy officer , second - in - command on Lieutenant James Cook 's first voyage to the Pacific and the first among Cook 's crew to sight mainland Australia .
Patrick Lafcadio Hearn ( /hɜːrn/ ; 27 June 1850 -- 26 September 1904 ) , known also by the Japanese name Koizumi Yakumo ( 小泉 八雲 ) , was an international writer , known best for his books about Japan , especially his collections of Japanese legends and ghost stories , such as Kwaidan :
Charles Cornwallis , 1st Earl Cornwallis PC ( 29 March 1700 -- 23 June 1762 ) , styled The Honourable Charles Cornwallis until 1722 and known as The Lord Cornwallis between 1722 and 1753 , was a British peer .
Jack Vinall ( 16 December 1910 -- 26 May 1997 ) was a footballer and a member of the Norwich City Hall of Fame .
John Lorenzo Christian ( 15 July 1895 - 28 June 1984 ) served as Chief Magistrate of the British Overseas Territory of Pitcairn Island , twice , in 1952 - 54 and 1961 - 66 .
Rabbi Moshe Shmuel Glasner ( 1856 - -1924 ) , a Hungarian Talmudic scholar and communal leader , served as chief rabbi of Klausenburg ( Kolozsvár in Humgarian , Cluj in Romanian ) from 1877 to 1923 .
Hong Shen ( Chinese : 洪深 ; Wade -- Giles : Hung Shen ; 31 December 1894 -- 29 August 1955 ) was a Chinese playwright , film director and screenwriter , film and drama theorist , and educator .
David Dietz ( October 6 , 1897 -- December 9 , 1984 ) was an American science journalist and author .
Pan Guangdan ( Chinese : 潘光旦 ; 1898 - -1967 ) known in English as Quentin Pan , was one of the most distinguished sociologists and eugenicists of China .
Cynthia Longfield ( 16 August 1896 -27 June 1991 ) was an expert on the dragonfly and an explorer .
Estelle Liebling ( April 21 , 1880 -- 1970 ) was a vocal coach who taught singing using the three - register method .
Giovanni Bernardino Nanino ( ca . 1560 -- 1623 ) was an Italian composer , teacher and singing master of the late Renaissance and early Baroque eras , and a leading member of the Roman School of composers .
Egidio De Maulo ( 4 September 1840 -- 1904 ) was an Italian painter mainly of landscapes and still lifes .
Christine Glanville ( 28 October 1924 -- 1 March 1999 ) was an English puppeteer who spent much of her professional life contributing to television series produced by Gerry Anderson .
Sir William Duff - Gordon , 2nd Baronet ( 8 April 1772 -- 8 March 1823 ) , known as William Gordon until 1815 , was a Scottish politician .
Reverend Sir Charles Clarke , 2nd Baronet was born 15 June 1812 and died 25 April 1899 .
Maud Sulter ( 19 September 1960 -- 27 February 2008 ) was a contemporary fine artist and writer of Ghanaian and Scottish heritage who lived and worked in Britain .
James Tuite ( 14 November 1849 -- 6 October 1916 ) was an Irish watchmaker and politician .
Ernest Duchesne ( 30 May 1874 -- 12 April 1912 ) was a French physician who noted that certain molds kill bacteria .
Willy Birgel ( 19 September 1891 -- 29 December 1973 ) , born Wilhelm Maria Birgel , was a German theatre and film actor .
Reginald Purdell ( 4 November 1895 -- 22 April 1953 ) was an English actor and screenwriter who appeared in over 40 films between 1930 and 1951 .
Johan Henrik Virkkunen ( 1917 - 1963 ) was a Finnish organizational theorist and Professor of Accounting at the Helsinki School of Economics , whose 1954 textbook Laskentatoimijohdon apuna ( Accounting as a Tool of Management ) influenced Finnish accountancy thinking for decades .
Heinrich Dernburg ( 3 March 1829 -- 25 November 1907 ) was a German jurist , professor , and politician .
Minnie Devereaux ( 1891 - -1984 ) was a Canadian silent film actress .
Augustus Volney Waller FRS ( 21 December 1816 -- 18 September 1870 ) was a British neurophysiologist .
Joel Munsell ( born Northfield , Massachusetts , 14 April 1808 ; died Albany , New York , 15 January 1880 ) was a United States printer , publisher and author .
Edward John Burrow ( 1785 -- 8 August 1861 ) was an English divine and miscellaneous writer .
Ahmed al - Gaddafi al - Qahsi ( died 26 July 2011 ) was the cousin of former Libyan leader Muammar Gaddafi .
Archibald Pitcairne or Pitcairn ( 25 December 1652 -- 20 October 1713 ) was a Scottish physician .
Abraham van den Blocke ( 1572 -- 31 January 1628 ) was an architect and sculptor .
John Till Allingham ( fl . 1799 - -1810 ) was an English dramatist .
Peire Raimon de Tolosa or Toloza ( fl . 1180 - -1220 ) was a troubadour from the merchant class of Toulouse .
Will J. Quinlan ( William James Quinlan , 3rd , 1877 - -1963 ) , artist , was born in Brooklyn on June 27 , 1877 .
Sir William Mather ( 15 July 1838 -- 18 September 1920 ) was a British industrialist and Liberal politician who sat in the House of Commons between 1885 and 1904 .
Kelly Bryant ( August 28 , 1908 - October 1975 ) served as the Democratic secretary of state of the U.S. state of Arkansas from 1963 until his death nearly thirteen years later .
Alexander Home , 3rd Lord Home ( died 1516 ) was a Scottish soldier and nobleman , Chamberlain of Scotland and March Warden .
Joseph Leary ( 1831 - -1881 ) , Australian politician , elected as a member of the New South Wales Legislative Assembly .
Anthony Champney ( c. 1569 in England -- c. 1643 in England ) was an English Roman Catholic priest and controversialist .
Ran Bosilek ( Bulgarian : Ран Босилек ) ( 26 September 1886 in Gabrovo -- 8 October 1958 in Sofia ) , born Gencho Stanchev Negentsov ( Bulgarian : Генчо Станчев Негенцов ) , was a Bulgarian author of children 's books .
Chris Pavlou ( 18 August 1939 -- 15 January 2012 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played for Carlton in the Victorian Football League between 1958 and 1961 .
Leonard Hugh Newman , ( 3 February 1909 - 23 January 1993 ) always known as L. Hugh Newman , was a British entomologist , author and broadcaster .
Jack Hanbury was a British film producer ( died Jan. 1968 ) .
Richard Paternoster ( 14 October 1802 - 21 July 1892 ) was an English civil servant in the East India Company , barrister and founder of the Alleged Lunatics ' Friend Society , an organisation that exposed abuses in lunatic asylums and campaigned for the reform of the lunacy laws .
Bartholomaeus of Neocastro ( c. 1240 -- after 1293 ) was an Italian jurist , and author of a chronicle called the Historia Sicula , which covers the years from 1250 to 1293 .
Dave Feickert ( 13 December 1946 -- 2 July 2014 ) was an international mines safety advisor .
David Chilton Phillips , Baron Phillips of Ellesmere , KBE , FRS ( 7 March 1924 -- 23 February 1999 ) was a pioneering structural biologist and an influential figure in science and government .
James Payn ( /peɪn/ ; 28 February 1830 -- 25 March 1898 ) , was an English novelist .
Li Xilie ( 李希烈 ) ( died May 9 , 786 ) was a general of the Chinese Tang Dynasty who , believing himself to be strong enough to claim imperial title , did so as the emperor of a new state of Chu .
Olaf Helset ( 28 July 1892 -- 21 August 1960 ) was a Norwegian military officer with the rank of Major General , and a sports administrator .
Patrick Stone ( 14 March 1854 -- 23 December 1926 ) was a Member of the Western Australian Legislative Assembly from 1901 to 1904 , and from 1905 to 1908 .
Louis Friant ( 18 September 1758 -- 24 June 1829 ) was born in the village of Morlancourt , 8 km south of Albert near the river Somme .
S. Kanapathipillai ( 27 June 1899 -- 13 March 1986 ) was a minority Sri Lankan Tamil literary figure and Hindu revivalist in the school of Arumuga Navalar .
Hannah Lamdan ( Hebrew : חנה למדן‎ , born Hannah Lerner on 5 January 1905 , died 10 April 1995 ) was an Israeli politician who served as a member of the Knesset for several left - wing parties between 1949 and 1965 .
Sir Berney Brograve , 1st Baronet ( 10 October 1726 - 23 February 1797 ) was the eldest son and heir of Thomas Brograve ( 1691 - -1753 ) of Great Baddow , Essex , and his wife Juliana Berney .
Marvin Mudrick ( 1921 -- 1986 ) taught at UC Santa Barbara from 1949 until his death in October 1986 .
Andreas de Escobar ( 1348 - 1448 ) was a Portuguese Benedictine theologian .
Sam Melberg ( 9 September 1912 -- 11 November 1998 ) was a Norwegian sports diver and sports instructor .
Predrag Radovanović ( Serbian Cyrillic : Предраг Радовановић ) ( 27 March 1911 -- 1 August 1964 ) was a Serbian footballer and coach .
Sergey Yustinovich Bagotsky ( Russian : Серге́й Юстинович Багоцкий ; 15 February 1879 - 15 March 1953 ) was a Russian Marxist revolutionary and Soviet medicine and Red Cross diplomat , Soviet head of the Red Cross representative mission to Geneva from 1918 to 1936 .
Joseph Deharbe ( 11 April 1800 at Strasbourg , Alsace -- 8 November 1871 at Maria - Laach ) was a French Jesuit theologian and catechist .
Fritz Arno Wagner ( 5 December 1889 -- 18 August 1958 ) is considered one of the most acclaimed German cinematographers from the 1920s to the 1950s .
Charles Brunsdon Fletcher ( 5 August 1859 -- 17 December 1946 ) was an English - born Australian surveyor and journalist who served as the editor of the Sydney Morning Herald for twenty years .
Robert Brandard ( Birmingham 1805 - -1862 ) was an English landscape engraver .
Marek Kubliński ( 27 September 1931 -- 4 October 1950 ) was a Polish boy scout and a Cracow high - school student whose fame rests on his activities as an anticommunist freedom fighter .
Indra Bania ( Assamese : ইন্দ্ৰ বনিয়া‎ ; 24 December 1942 -- 25 March 2015 ) was an Indian theatre actor , playwright , film actor and director from Assam .
Philippa of Luxembourg ( 1252 -- 6 April 1311 ) was the daughter of Count Henry V of Luxembourg and his wife , Marguerite of Bar .
Ewald Straesser ( Sträßer ) ( 27 June 1867 -- 4 April 1933 ) was a German composer of classical music .
