Justin Matthews ( 1876 - -1955 ) was an Arkansas road and bridge builder as well as real estate developer .
Henry Edgar ( 1698 - -1765 ) was a Scottish Episcopal minister who served as the Bishop of Fife from 1762 to 1765 .
Commander Harry Pursey ( 1891 -- 13 December 1980 ) was a British politician and naval officer , who began his career as a boy seaman and served as a Member of Parliament for twenty - five years .
Zenón Martínez García ( died 2010 ) was a Mexican potter from Tlaquepaque , Jalisco recognized for his figurines .
He may have been alive as late as 1690 , as author Caleb Johnson reports that in that year , he provided a note to Bradford 's History of Plymouth Plantation stating that `` Two persons living that came over in the first ship in 1620 , this present year 1690 : Resolved White and Mary Cushman . ''
Christian I , Prince of Anhalt - Bernburg , also known as Christian of Anhalt , ( 11 May 1568 -- 17 April 1630 ) was a German prince of the House of Ascania .
Sudha Shivpuri ( 14 July 1937 -- 20 May 2015 ) was an Indian actress who was most famous for her role as Baa in the Hindi TV serial Kyunki Saas Bhi Kabhi Bahu Thi ( 2000 - -2008 ) .
Octavio M. Salati ( 1914 - 2001 ) was Professor of Electrical Engineering at the University of Pennsylvania in the field of Electromagnetic Compatibility .
Menahem Shemuel Halevy ( 1884 - -1940 ) was a prominent Iranian Rabbi of the early 20th century .
Arvid Andersen ( 1909 -- 31 October 1970 ) was a Danish violinist , conductor , and composer .
William Henry Bateson ( 1812 , Liverpool , Lancashire -- 1881 Cambridge , Cambridgeshire ) was a British scholar and , from 1857 until 1881 , Master of St John 's College , Cambridge .
Max McGraw ( 1 February 1883 -- 26 October 1964 ) was an American entrepreneur who founded McGraw - Edison and Centel .
Robert Morton Nance ( 1873 - -1959 ) was a leading authority on the Cornish language , nautical archaeologist , and joint founder of the Old Cornwall Society .
Thomas Horace Fuller ( ca . 1816 -- August 24 , 1861 ) was a lawyer and political figure in Nova Scotia .
Abba bar Pappai was a Jewish Amora ( scholar ) , of the fourth century CE , who died in 375 .
Geoffrey Owen Whittaker , OBE , ( c. 1932 -- 24 February 2015 ) was a British civil servant .
Valentine Dencausse ( 20 May 1871 -- 16 February 1954 ) was probably the most famous chiromancer in Paris during the first half of the 20th century , under the name of `` Madame Fraya '' .
Sevas Hanum ( died May 1990 ) , was a Greek singer .
John Eddie Mullan ( 27 April 1923 -- 14 December 2008 ) was an Irish Gaelic footballer who played for Derry in the 1940s and 1950s .
Bal Gangadhar Tilak ( or Lokmanya Tilak , pronunciation ; 23 July 1856 -- 1 August 1920 ) , born as Keshav Gangadhar Tilak , was an Indian nationalist , teacher , social reformer , lawyer and an independence activist .
William Beresford Inglis ( died 1967 ) was a Scottish architect .
Olive Mudie - Cooke ( 1890 - 11 September 1925 ) was a British artist who is best known for the paintings she created during the First World War .
Gysbert Japiks or Japicx ( 1603 - -1666 ) was a Frisian writer , poet , schoolmaster , and cantor .
Reverend Francis Orpen Morris ( 25 March 1810 -- 10 February 1893 ) was an Irish clergyman , notable as `` parson - naturalist '' ( ornithologist and entomologist ) and as the author of many children 's books and books on natural history and heritage buildings .
José Joaquín Casimiro Olañeta y Güemes ( 1795 - 1860 ) was a nephew of Pedro Antonio Olañeta who , after working for him , turned against his uncle in favor of Bolivian independence .
Philip Morant ( 6 October 1700 in Jersey -- 25 November 1770 in Battersea ) was an English clergyman , author and historian .
Vilhelm Herman Oluf Madsen ( 11 April 1844 -- 14 June 1917 ) , was a Danish politician , minister , army officer , businessman and inventor .
Du Zhongyuan ( 1895 - -1943 ) was one of China 's best - known wartime journalists , having reported in great detail on the Japanese invasion and occupation of China during the Second Sino - Japanese War .
Hayır Bey ( sometimes spelled Kha'ir Bey ; died 1522 ) ruled Egypt in the name of the Ottoman Empire from 1517 until his death in 1522 .
Frank William Erickson ( 1 September 1923 Spokane -- 21 October 1996 ) was an American composer , conductor , arranger , writer , and trumpet player .
William Paullin ( born in Philadelphia , 3 April 1812 ; died there , 1 December 1871 ) was a United States balloonist ( or aeronaut as they were called then ) .
George Van Dyne ( 1933 - 1981 ) was a pioneer of systems ecology and served as the first director of the Natural Resource Ecology Laboratory in the USA .
Colonel John George Nathaniel Gibbes ( 30 March 1787 -- 5 July 1873 ) was a British army officer who emigrated to Australia in 1834 , becoming a Crown - appointed member of the New South Wales Legislative Council and the Collector of Customs for the Colony of New South Wales for a record term of 25 years .
The Reverend Moses Rintel , S.J.M. , ( 1823 -- 9 May 1880 ) was a Jewish Rabbi in colonial Victoria ( Australia ) who established the first Beth din ( rabbinical court ) in the British empire outside London .
Nathaniel St André ( c.1680 - -March 1776 ) was a Swiss physician who practised in England .
John Frescheville , 1st Baron Frescheville ( 4 December 1607 -- 31 March 1682 ) was an English soldier , landowner and politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1628 and 1665 when he was created a peer and then sat in the House of Lords .
Joshua Arthur Rodrigues Brandon ( 9 February 1822 , London -- 11 December 1847 , 11 Beaufort Buildings , Strand ) was an English architect and author .
William Berkeley , 4th Baron Berkeley of Stratton PC , PC ( I ) ( d. 24 March 1741 ) , was a British politician and judge , of the Bruton branch of the Berkeley family .
Ramon d'Abella ( fl . 1389 - -1401 ) was a Catalan military leader and royal councillor under John I and Martin of the Crown of Aragon .
Xi Zuochi ( after 316 - -384 ) , courtesy name Yanwei , was a Jin dynasty historian native to Xiangyang , Hubei .
Cornelius Smelt ( August 1748 -- 28 November 1832 ) was an administrator who served as Lieutenant Governor of the Isle of Man from 1805 until his death in 1832 .
Brother Fernando de la Fuente de la Fuente ( 16 December 1943 -- 31 October 1996 ) was a Spanish Marist Brother and missionary who was one of four Marist Brothers martyred at the Nyamirangwe refugee camp , Zaire .
Roy Rich ( 16 September 1911 - 24 March 1970 ) was a British broadcaster and film and theatre director .
Gangadhar Balkrushna Sardar ( Devanagari : गंगाधर बाळकृष्ण सरदार ) ( 1908 - -1988 ) was a Marathi writer from Maharashtra , India .
Pierre de Villiers Pienaar ( 1904 - -1978 ) was an South African Afrikaans academic and Professor at University of the Witwatersrand ( Wits ) and later at University of Pretoria , who pioneered Speech Language Therapy in South Africa and specialising in Audiology and Lexicography as well as being an Afrikaans author .
Blessed Francisca de Paula de Jesus , also known as Nhá Chica ( Aunt Francie , in Portuguese , 1810 - - 14 June 1895 ) , was born in Santo Antônio do Rio das Mortes Pequeno , neighborhood of the Brazilian city of São João del - Rei , where she was also baptized .
Sir George Herbert Duckworth CB FSA ( 5 March 1868 -- 27 April 1934 ) was an English public servant .
Joseph - Antoine - Charles Couderc ( 10 March 1810 -- 16 April 1875 ) was a French operatic tenor ( and later baritone ) prominent on the stages of the Opéra - Comique in Paris where he created numerous roles .
Sigurd Eldegard ( 10 July 1866 -- 30 January 1950 ) was a Norwegian actor , playwright and theatre director .
Sir Thomas McCall Anderson ( 1836 - -1908 ) was a professor of practice of medicine , at the University of Glasgow .
Edward Holton James ( 1873 - -1954 ) was an American socialist .
Henry Bryan Ziegler ( 1798 - -1874 ) was a British artist , known as a landscape and portrait painter .
Thomas Thornley ( 1 Apr 1781 -- 4 May 1862 ) was a British Liberal Party politician .
Harold Shapinsky ( May 21 , 1925 -- January 31 , 2004 ) was an American abstract expressionist painter , born in Brooklyn , New York .
Kostas Skarvelis ( 1880 -- 8 April 1942 ) was a Greek composer of popular music , οf the genre of rembetiko ( ρεμπέτικο ) in particular .
Gustave Léonard de Jonghe , Gustave Léonard De Jonghe or Gustave de Jonghe ( 4 February 1829 - 28 January 1893 ) was a Belgian painter known for his glamorous society portraits and genre scenes .
Eleonora Rossi Drago , born Palmira Omiccioli , ( 23 September 1925 -- 2 December 2007 ) was an Italian film actress .
Adolph Strasser ( 1843 - 1939 ) , born in the Austro - Hungarian empire , was an American trade union organizer .
Antonio Maria Haffner ( 1654 - -1704 ) was an Italian painter of quadratura and priest during the Baroque period , active mainly in Bologna .
John Hoesli ( 8 March 1919 -- March 1997 ) was a British art and set decorator .
John Christmas Beckwith ( 25 December 1750 , Norwich -- 3 June 1809 ) was an English organist and composer .
Richard Irvine Bentley ( 1 January 1854 -- 1909 ) was the superintendent to the British Columbia provincial Asylum for the Insane and medical officer to the New Westminster Gaol .
Dafydd ab Owain Gwynedd ( born c. 1145-died 1203 ) was Prince of Gwynedd from 1170 to 1195 .
The Reverend John Brodie Innes ( 26 December 1815 -- 19 October 1894 ) , John Innes before 1862 , was a clergyman who became a close friend of Charles Darwin at Downe in Kent , and remained a friendly correspondent for the rest of Darwin 's life .
Marco Antonio Andino Flores ( 25 April 1955 -- 9 August 2015 ) was a Honduran politician and lawyer .
Jan Willem van Otterloo ( 27 December 1907 -- 27 July 1978 ) was a Dutch conductor , cellist and composer .
Edward Flowerdew ( died 1586 ) , was an English judge and MP .
Li Quanzhong ( 李全忠 ) ( d. 886 ) was a warlord late in the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty , who controlled Lulong Circuit ( 盧龍 , headquartered in modern Beijing ) from 885 , when he overthrew the prior military governor ( Jiedushi ) Li Keju , to his death in 886 .
Hosea Hudson ( April 12 , 1898 -- 1988 ) was an African - American labor leader in the Southern United States .
Christopher Bethell ( 21 April 1773 -- 19 April 1859 ) was Bishop of Bangor .
Vavrinec Dunajský ( born 15 July 1784 in Ľubietová , died 15 February 1833 in Budapest ) was a Slovak sculptor .
Ulrika Melin ( 1767 - -1834 ) was a Swedish textile artist , and a member of the Royal Swedish Academy of Arts .

The East India Company built Willoughby Memorial Hall in 1924 in memory of Sir Robert William Douglas Willoughby , Deputy Commissioner of Kheri who was killed on 26 August 1920 .
Henry Tresham RA ( c.1751 -- 17 June 1814 ) was an Irish - born historical painter active in London , England , in the late 18th century .
Francisco Gavidia ( 1863 in San Miguel - 24 September 1955 in San Salvador ) was a Salvadoran writer , educator and journalist .
Andreas Faye ( 5 October 1802 -- 5 May 1869 ) was a Norwegian priest , folklorist and historian .
William Walter Merry ( 1835 - -1918 ) was an English classical scholar , clergyman , and educator .
Kidane - Mariam Teklehaimanot ( 10 September 1933 , Alitena - 2 June 2009 ) was a bishop of the Ethiopian Catholic Church .
Amadeus I of Geneva ( 1098 - -1178 ) was count of Geneva .
Roland Khoury ( Arabic : رولان خوري‎ ) ( 1930 - -1988 ) was a Syrian painter .
Louis A. Hill ( 1865 - -1933 ) was an official in the United States Department of the Treasury who was Director of the Bureau of Engraving and Printing from 1922 to 1924 .
Cor Blekemolen `` Blekie '' ( 7 February 1894 -- 28 November 1972 ) was a Dutch cyclist .
Maria Abdy , née Smith ( 25 February 1797 -- 19 July 1867 ) was an English poet .
Len Morrison ( 23 December 1872 -- 16 November 1922 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Sussex Camock or Sussex Cammock ( 1600 - -1659 ) was an English privateer who was involved in establishing the Providence Island colony , a Puritan colony on what is now Isla de Providencia in the western Caribbean .
Biraja Sankar Guha ( Bengali : বিরজাশঙ্কর গুহ ) ( 15 August 1894 -- 20 October 1961 ) was an Indian physical anthropologist , who classified Indian people into races around the early part of the 20th century .
Georges Corvington , Jr. ( died 3 April 2013 ) was a Haitian historian .
Adolf Šimperský ( 5 August 1909 in Břevnov -- 15 February 1964 ) is a former Czech football player who played mostly for SK Slavia Praha .
George Brettingham Sowerby III ( 1843 - -1921 ) was a British conchologist , publisher , and illustrator .
Clotilde Arias ( 1901 - -1959 ) was a Peruvian - American lyricist and composer .
Jeane Gardiner , d. 26 May 1651 in Saint George , Bermuda in the West Indies , was an alleged British witch .
Jules Langsner ( 1911 - -1967 ) was an American art critic and psychiatrist .
Ken Bousfield ( 2 October 1919 -- 25 May 2000 ) was one of the leading British golfers of the immediate post - World War II period .
Edmond Delphaut ( 1873 - -1943 ) was a French sculptor known for his work on World War I memorials , in particular that at Malo - les - Bains in the Nord department in Northern France .
Henry Schenck Tanner ( 1786 - -1858 ) , was an American cartographer , born in New York .
Bayan Qulï ( died 1358 ) was khan of the Chagatai Khanate from 1348 to 1358 and a grandson of Duwa .
Guy Mone ( Mohun ) ( died 1407 ) was an English royal administrator and bishop .
George W. Stocking Sr . ( 1892 - -1975 ) was an American economist who was one of the pioneers of industrial organization and an early writer on international cartels .
Enrique Kicho Díaz ( Buenos Aires , 21 January 1918 -- 5 October 1992 ) was an Argentine double bass tango musician who played in various ensembles including Aníbal Troilo 's orquesta típica , Astor Piazzolla 's first Quinteto and Conjunto 9 and finally Sexteto Major .
Harry Kuhl ( 7 March 1903 -- 11 January 1967 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with St Kilda in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Edward Oxford ( 19 April 1822 -- 23 April 1900 ) was the first of eight people who tried to assassinate Queen Victoria .
Gustav Alexander ( 1873 -- 12 April 1932 ) was an Austrian otolaryngologist remembered for describing Alexander 's law .
William Hirst ( 1873 -- 5 May 1946 ) was a British Labour Co - operative politician who was the Member of Parliament ( MP ) for Bradford South from 1924 to 1931 .
Solomon Bregman ( in Russian , Соломон Брегман ) ( 1895 , Zlynka -- 1953 ) was a prominent member of the Jewish Anti - Fascist Committee formed in the Soviet Union in April 1942 .
Zhou Longxiang ( Chinese : 周隆庠 ; pinyin : Zhōu Lóngxiáng ; Wade -- Giles : Chou Long - hsiang ) ( 1905 - -1969 ) was a politician in the Republic of China .
William Crowne ( 1617 - -1682 ) had a varied career as an officer of arms , a member of parliament , a colonel during the English civil war , and one of the early colonists of North America .
John Palsgrave ( c. 1485 -- 1554 ) was a priest of Henry VIII of England 's court .
Minosuke Hiroe ( ( Japanese ) 廣江美之助 ; 7 June 1914 -- 12 January 2000 ) was a Japanese botanist .
Sir William Morison ( died 15 May 1851 ) was a Scottish Liberal Party politician .
John Blaquiere , 1st Baron de Blaquiere KCB , PC ( 15 May 1732 -- 27 August 1812 ) , known as Sir John Blaquiere , Bt , from 1784 to 1800 , was a British soldier , diplomat and politician of French descent .
Father John B. DeValles ( 1879 - 1920 ) founded the first Portuguese parochial school at Espirito Santo Church in Fall River , Massachusetts .
Bhajan Lal ( 6 October 1930 -- 3 June 2011 ) was a politician and three - time chief minister from the northern Indian state of Haryana .
Hattie Bishop Speed ( 1858 - -1942 ) was a pianist , humanist , and philanthropist who championed music and the arts in Louisville , Kentucky .
George Edward Luckman Gauntlett ( born 4 December 1868 , Swansea , UK ; d. 29 July 1956 , Tokyo , Japan ) was a teacher of English and educator in Japan .
Jiang Fengzhi ( 蒋风之 , 1908 - -1986 ) was an erhu artist from Yixing , Jiangsu Province , China .
Allen Allensworth ( 7 April 1842 -- 14 September 1914 ) , born into slavery , escaped and became a Union soldier ; later he became a Baptist minister and educator , and was appointed as a chaplain in the United States Army .
John Manwood ( died 1610 ) was a barrister of Lincoln 's Inn , gamekeeper of Waltham Forest , and Justice in Eyre of the New Forest under Elizabeth I of England .
Pappus of Alexandria ( /ˈpæpəs/ ; Greek : Πάππος ὁ Ἀλεξανδρεύς ; c. 290 -- c. 350 AD ) was one of the last great Greek mathematicians of Antiquity , known for his Synagoge ( Συναγωγή ) or Collection ( c. 340 ) , and for Pappus 's hexagon theorem in projective geometry .
Rabbi Ya'akov - Michael Hasani ( Hebrew : יעקב - מיכאל חזני‎ , born Ya'akov Kantrovich on 27 June 1913 , died 2 July 1975 ) was an Israeli politician who served as Minister of Welfare during two spells in the early 1970s .
Bernhard Pollack ( 14 August 1865 -- 3 March 1928 in Berlin ) was a German neuroanatomist and ophthalmologist practicing in Berlin .
Captain Robert Cecil Beavan ( 1841 - 3 February 1870 ) , corresponding member of the Zoological Society of London , served in India with the Bengal Staff Corps for 10 years .
Richard FitzRalph ( also Fitz Ralph ; c. 1300 -- 16 December 1360 ) was an Irish Archbishop of Armagh during the 14th century .
Martin - Joseph Mengal ( 27 January 1784 - 4 July 1851 ) was a Belgian composer and instructor .
Toussaint - Antoine - Rodolphe Laflamme , PC ( 15 May 1827 -- 7 December 1893 ) , was a French - Canadian lawyer , professor of law and politician .
Ion Andreescu ( Romanian pronunciation : ( iˈon andreˈesku ) ; 15 February 1850 -- 22 October 1882 ) was a Romanian painter of great renown .
William Godwin the Younger ( 1803 - -8 September 1832 ) was an English reporter and author .
Wolfgang Langewiesche ( 1907 - -2002 ) aviator , author and journalist , is one of the most quoted authors in aviation writing .
Wilhelm Bogner ( 7 February 1909 -- 27 July 1977 ) , better known as Willy Bogner , Sr . , was a German Nordic skier who competed in the 1930s .
Solomon Jacobs ( 9 July 1861 -- 6 August 1920 ) was an English - born Canadian rabbi .
Guillaume Daniel Delprat CBE ( 1 September 1856 -- 15 March 1937 ) was a Dutch - Australian metallurgist , mining engineer , and businessman .
Zaharija Pribislavljević or Zaharija of Serbia ( Serbian : Захаријa Прибислављевић , Greek : Ζαχαρίας ; c. 890s -- 924 ) was Prince of the Serbs from 922 to 924 .
Tomás Óg de Burca , 5th Mac William Iochtar and lord of Lower ( North ) Connacht , died 1460 .
Heinrich Gottfried Philipp Gengler ( 25 July 1817 -- 28 November 1901 ) was a German historian of law , Geheimrat and academic lecturer .
Raffaele Conflenti ( 4 December 1889 -- 16 July 1946 ) was an Italian aeronautical engineer and aircraft designer .
Mihai Ioan Botez ( 29 June 1927 -- 2 June 1998 ) was a Romanian neurologist and academic who specialised in the field of neuropsychology .
Mgolombane Sandile ( 1820 - -1878 ) was a Chief of the Ngqika ( `` Gaikas '' ) and Paramount - Chief of the Rharhabe tribe - a sub - group of the Xhosa nation .
Cybi died on 8 November 555 and was buried in Eglwys y Bedd ( the Chapel of the Grave ) adjoining his monastery at Holyhead .
Jimmy Luff ( 9 May 1887 -- 5 October 1960 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Uisang ( 625 - -702 ) was one of the most eminent early Silla Korean scholar - monks , a close friend of Wonhyo ( 元曉 ) .
Victor de Bonald ( 1780 - -1871 ) , son of Louis Gabriel Ambroise de Bonald , followed his father in his exile .
Architect John Ariss ( sometimes spelled Ayres ) ( 1725 - -1799 ) was born in Westmoreland County , Virginia to a family long settled in the Old Dominion .
Walter Jobson ( by 1519 - -1605 ) , of London and Kingston upon Hull , Yorkshire , was an English politician .
Hubert de Cronin Hastings ( 18 July 1902 - 4 December 1986 ) , often referred to in contemporary works as H. de C. Hastings ( and known to friends as `` H. de C. '' ) , was chairman of the Architectural Press and editor of Architectural Review and Architects ' Journal .
Tol Hansse ( born Hans van Tol , 3 April 1940 - 29 April 2002 ) was a Dutch singer and musician .
Giuseppe Weidmann ( 1742 - -1810 ) was an Austrian drama actor .
Ahad Rajabli ( Azerbaijani : Əhəd Rəcəbli , 1962 -- 8 June 2013 , Sumgayit ) was a world champion in sambo and multiple sambo champion of Azerbaijan , as well as Judo Master of Sports .
Edward Cator Seaton ( 1815 -- 21 January 1880 ) was an English doctor who became the second Chief Medical Officer .
Kurt Hasse ( 7 February 1907 - 9 January 1944 on the Eastern Front of World War II in the Soviet Union ) is a German show jumping champion , and 1936 Olympic champion .
Ramu Kariat ( alternatively Ramu Karyat ) ( 1 February 1927 -- 10 February 1979 ) was a legendary Malayali Indian film director for almost three decades from the 1950s to the 1970s .
Claude de Saint - Étienne de la Tour ( c. 1570 -- d. after 1636 ) was born in the province of Champagne , France and came to Acadia in 1610 after suffering heavy losses as a ship 's captain .
Rikdag , also called Ricdag , Riddag , or Rihdag ( died 985 ) , was Margrave of Meissen from 979 until his death .
Peder Lauridsen Kylling ( c. 1640 - 1696 ) was a 17th - century Danish botanist .
Abu Ali Hasan ibn Ustadh - Hurmuz , commonly known after his father as Ibn Ustadh - Hurmuz ( died 1011 ) was a Dailamite military officer of the Buyids , and an important figure in the Buyid state during the late 10th century .
Alexandros Zaimis ( Greek : Αλέξανδρος Ζαΐμης ; 9 November 1855 -- 15 September 1936 ) was a Greek Prime Minister , Minister of the Interior , Minister of Justice , and High Commissioner of Crete .
Jes Bundsen ( 1766 - -1829 ) was a Danish architectural and landscape painter and etcher .
Lily Strickland ( 1884 -- 6 June 1958 ) was an American composer , painter and writer .
James Mott ( 20 June 1788 -- 26 January 1868 ) was a Quaker leader , teacher , and merchant as well as an anti - slavery activist .
Vladislav Achalov ( Russian : Владисла́в Алексе́евич Ача́лов ) ( 19 November 1945 -- 23 June 2011 ) was a Soviet general who at one time commanded the Soviet Airborne Forces .
Thomas Mompesson ( 1630 -- 1701 ) , of Mompesson House , The Close , Salisbury and St. Martin 's Lane , Westminster , was an English politician .
Sir Siddiq Abubakar III ( 1903 - -1988 ) was a Nigerian Muslim leader .
Thomas Kensett died 16 June 1829 at the age of 42 .
Sir Gerard Vanneck , 2nd Baronet ( c. 1743 - 23 May 1791 ) , was a British merchant and Member of Parliament .
Clarence Hatzfeld ( 1873 - -1943 ) was a prolific Chicago architect who designed residences , park field houses , Masonic temples , banks and other commercial buildings in the Craftsman , Prairie , and Revival styles .
Eddie Hinton ( 15 June 1944 -- 28 July 1995 ) was an American songwriter and session musician best known for his work with soul music and R&B singers .
Abraham Isaac Castello ( 1726 in Ancona , Italy -- August 1 , 1789 in Leghorn , Italy ) was a rabbi , preacher , and poet .
Nathaniel Chapman ( 28 May 1780 -- 1 July 1853 ) was a well - known early American physician .
Albert David Hager ( 1 November 1817 Chester , Vermont - 29 July 1888 Chicago , Illinois ) was a United States geologist , librarian and historian .
Joseph Henry Lynch ( 28 October 1911 -- 16 January 1989 ) was a British artist , better known under his signature J.H. Lynch .
Charles John Cornish ( 28 September 1858 -- 30 January 1906 ) was an English naturalist and author .
Polly Collins ( 1808 - 1884 ) was a Shaker artist who made gift drawings , which were depictions of spiritual messages during the Era of Manifestations in the mid-1800s .
Hjalmar Selander ( 2 July 1859 in Mölndal Municipality -- 10 August 1928 ) was a Swedish actor , stage director and theatre manager .
Sir George Yeardley ( 1587 - -1627 ) was a planter and three time colonial Governor of the British Colony of Virginia .
Ibrahim Mirza bin Ala - ud - Daulah ( died c. 1459 ) was a Timurid ruler of Herat in the fifteenth century .
Colin Clive ( 20 January 1900 -- 25 June 1937 ) was an English stage and screen actor best remembered for his portrayal of Dr. Frankenstein in James Whale 's two Universal Frankenstein films Frankenstein and Bride of Frankenstein .
Sir Francis Pile , 2nd Baronet ( c. 1617 -- 1649 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons between 1645 and 1649 .
Ernest Hickinbottom ( born 1865 - 2 September 1939 ) was an English footballer who played for Derby County .
Dame Caroline Arnott died on 28 December 1933 of unknown causes .
Lieutenant - Colonel Sir Hugh Daly KCSI KCIE ( 29 May 1860 -- 25 August 1939 ) was a British Indian Army officer and colonial administrator .
John Charles Templer ( 1814 - -1874 ) was a lawyer .
William Longstreet ( c.1760 New Jersey - 1814 Georgia ) was an inventor .
Henry Darnley Naylor MA Cantab ( 21 February 1872 -- 8 December 1945 ) , was a British born Australian academic who became Emeritus Professor of Classics in the University of Adelaide , South Australia .
Achille Compagnoni ( 26 September 1914 -- 13 May 2009 ) was an Italian mountaineer and skier .
Lilik Sudjio ( 14 May 1930 -- 9 December 2014 ) was an Indonesian actor turned film director who won the Citra Award for Best Director in 1955 for his film Tarmina .
Tony Holiday ( born Rolf Peter Knigge ; 24 February 1951 -- 14 February 1990 ) was a German pop singer and songwriter .
Edward Hugh Buggy ( 9 June 1896 -- 18 June 1974 ) was a leading journalist well known as an Australian rules football writer covering the Victorian Football League ( later renamed to Australian Football League ) .
Sir Thomas Malcolm Knox FRSE ( 28 November 1900 -- 6 April 1980 ) was an Anglo - Scottish philosopher who served as Principal of St Andrews University from 1953 - -66 and Vice - president of the Royal Society of Edinburgh from 1975 - 8 .
Ludwig Czaczkes ( 12 September 1898 -- 4 August 1992 ) was an Austrian composer , musicologist and pianist .
The Reverend Walter Whiter ( 30 October 1758 in Birmingham , England-- 23 July 1832 in Hardingham ) was an English philologist and literary critic .
Majida Boulila ( 12 November 1931 -- 4 September 1952 ) was a Tunisian militant .
Hilbrand Boschma ( 22 April 1893 , IJsbrechtum , Wymbritseradeel , Friesland -- 22 July 1976 , Leiden ) was a Dutch zoologist and director of the Rijksmuseum of Natural History in Leiden .
Sir Lionel Phillips , 1st Baronet ( 6 August 1855 -- 2 July 1936 ) was a South African mining magnate and politician .
Jiang Zhaohe or Chiang Chao - ho ( Chinese : 蒋兆和 ) ( 1904 -- 1986 ) was a Chinese artist who played a leading role in the reform process of Chinese figure painting .
William Fiennes , 1st Viscount Saye and Sele ( 28 June 1582 -- 14 April 1662 ) was an English nobleman and politician , known also for his involvement in several companies for setting up overseas colonies .
Kang Yanxiao ( 康延孝 ) ( died 926 ) , known as Li Shaochen ( 李紹琛 ) from 923 to 926 , was a general of the Chinese Five Dynasties and Ten Kingdoms period states Later Liang and Later Tang .
Dr. George G. Ritchie , M.D. ( 25 September 1923 -- 29 October 2007 ) held positions as president of the Richmond Academy of General Practice ; chairman of the Department of Psychiatry of Towers Hospital ; and founder and president of the Universal Youth Corps , Inc. for almost 20 years .
Anthony Chenevix - Trench ( 10 May 1919 -- 21 June 1979 ) was a British schoolteacher and Classics scholar .
Arthur Ernest Wilder - Smith , FRSC ( 22 December 1915 -- 14 September 1995 ) , more commonly known as A. E. Wilder - Smith , was a British organic chemist , and young Earth creationist .
Cosimo Boscaglia ( c. 1550 -- 1621 ) was a professor of philosophy at the University of Pisa in Italy .
George Stephănescu ( 13 December 1843 - 25 April 1925 ) was a Romanian composer , one of the main figures in Romanian national opera .
Safford Cape ( 28 June 1906 - 26 March 1973 ) was an American conductor , composer and musicologist .
Jadwiga Dziubińska , a Polish politician ( born 10 October 1874 in Warsaw , died 28 January 1937 ) .
William Goffe ( 1605?--1679 ? ) was an English Roundhead politician and soldier , perhaps best known for his role in the execution of King Charles I and later flight to America .
David Keith Duckworth ( 10 August 1933 -- 18 December 2005 ) was an English mechanical engineer .
Sattur A. G. Subramaniam , ( 1916 - -1977 ) was a vocalist in the carantic tradition .
James Charles Dowdall ( 1873 -- 28 June 1939 ) was an Irish politician and businessman .
Hanut Singh Rathore ( 6 July 1933 - 11 April 2015 ) , also referred as Hanut Singh ( not to be confused with Maharaja Hanut Singhji of Jodhpur ) was a former Lt . General of Indian army .
Elias Solomon ( 2 September 1839 -- 23 May 1909 ) was an Australian politician based in Fremantle .
Gísli Halldórsson ( 2 February 1927 -- 27 July 1998 ) was an Icelandic actor of theatre , radio , film and television , and one of the most popular Icelandic actors of the late twentieth century .
Ian Greer ( 5 June 1933 -- 4 November 2015 ) was a British political lobbyist , who had a very successful career , until the Cash - for - questions affair .
Yamyam ( born Abdulkadir Hersi Siyad , 1945 -- 18 September 2005 ) ( Somali : Cabdiqaadir Xirsi Siyaad ( Yamyam ) , Arabic : `` عبد قادر حرس سياد ' ' يميم‎ ) was a Somali poet and playwright .
John Systad ( 14 September 1912 -- 16 September 1998 ) was a Norwegian long - distance runner who specialized in the marathon race .
Nikolay Adamets ( Belarusian : Мiкалай Адамец ; Russian : Николай Адамец ; 18 October 1983 -- 7 September 2014 ) was a Belarusian footballer who last played for Volna Pinsk .
John Samuel Enys ( 21 September 1796 -- 29 May 1872 ) was a British mining engineer and scientist who wrote several important papers on the `` duty '' of steam engines and other types of power delivery , from water wheels to horses .
Henry Bernard Carpenter ( April 22 , 1840 in Dublin or near Enniskillen , Ireland of an ancient landed family -- July 17 , 1890 at Sorrento , Maine ) , was a noted Unitarian clergyman , orator , author , and poet .
Alexander Pearce ( 1790 -- 19 July 1824 ) was an Irish convict who was transported to Van Diemen 's Land for seven years for theft .
Joe McKelvey ( Irish : Seosamh Mac Giolla Bhuidhe ; died 8 December 1922 ) was an Irish Republican Army officer who was executed during the Irish Civil War .
Cesar Picton ( c. 1755 Senegal ? -- 1836 Thames Ditton , Surrey ) was presumably enslaved in Africa by the time he was about six years old .

Rowland Stephenson ( 1782 - -1856 ) was a British banker and politician who precipitated the collapse of a bank and took refuge in America .
Huang Yao ( Chinese : 黄尧 ; Pinyin : Huáng Yáo ; 1917 - -1987 ) was a Chinese artist .
Samuel Trevor Francis ( 19 November 1834 -- 28 December 1925 ) was an English lay preacher and hymn writer , with the Plymouth Brethren .
James Dodsley ( 1724 - -1797 ) was an English bookseller .
Macduff of Fife ( died 22 July 1298 ) played a small but significant role in the Wars of Scottish Independence .
Robert Bowne Minturn ( born New York , 16 November 1805 ; died New York , 9 January 1866 ) was one of the most prominent American merchants and shippers of the mid-19th century .
Catherine Obianuju Acholonu ( 26 October 1951 -- 18 March 2014 ) was a Nigerian writer , researcher and former lecturer on African Cultural and Gender Studies .
Count Friedrich Albrecht zu Eulenburg ( 29 June 1815 -- 2 June 1881 ) was a Prussian diplomat and politician .
Henry Roy Donovan ( 26 November 1903 -- 18 February 1972 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Hawthorn in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Harriet Auber ( Middlesex , 1773 -- Hoddesdon , Hertfordshire , 1862 ) was an English poet and hymnist .
Walter Melzer ( 7 October 1894 -- 23 June 1961 ) was a highly decorated General der Infanterie in the Wehrmacht during World War II who commanded the XXIII corps .
Burchard du Puiset ( died 1196 ; sometimes Bourchard du Puiset , or Bourchard of Le Puiset ) was a medieval Anglo - Norman clergyman and treasurer of the diocese of York .
Lieutenant - Colonel George Robert Harland Bowden ( 1873 - 10 October 1927 ) was a British mechanical engineer and Conservative Party politician .
Dorothea Krag ( 27 September 1675 -- 10 October 1754 ) was a Danish General Postmaster and noble .
Mohammed ibn Amr al - Ribati or Abu Abdallah Mohammed ibn Mohammed ibn Amr al - Ansari ( died 1 October 1827 ) was a Moroccan poet from Rabat .
Brigadier - General Alfred Douglas Miller , DSO ( 1864 − 5 December 1933 ) was a British army officer .
Louis Livingston Seaman , FRGS ( October 17 , 1851 -- 1932 ) was an American surgeon , born in Newburgh , New York .
David J. Hetland ( 1947 - 2006 ) was a nationally recognized artist from Fargo , ND , known particularly for his liturgical works in mosaic and stained glass .
Giulio Variboba ( Arbërisht : Jul Variboba ; 1725 -- 1788 ) was an Arbëresh poet that gave an important contribution to the literature in the Albanian language .
Jacotin or Jacob Godebrye ( died 24 March 1529 ) was a Franco - Flemish singer and composer .
Achsah Barlow Brewster ( 1878 - -1945 ) was an American painter and writer , and wife of artist Earl Brewster ( 1878 - -1957 ) .
Caroline Louisa Waring Atkinson ( best known as Louisa Atkinson ) ( 25 February 1834 -- 28 April 1872 ) was an early Australian writer , botanist and illustrator .
Mundia Sikatana ( 1938 -- 14 June 2012 ; Lusaka ) was a Zambian politician , diplomat and lawyer .
Thomas Buttersworth ( 5 May 1768 -- November 1842 ) was an English seaman of the Napoleonic wars period who became a marine painter .
John J. Burke ( 1875 - -1936 ) was a Paulist priest and editor of the Catholic World from 1903 to 1922 .
Johann Jakob Wirz ( 1778 in Basel -- 1858 ) was a Swiss silkweaver who became known a Theosophist prophet and started a group called the Nazarenes , or in German Nazarener .
Hillel Noah Maggid ( 1829 - 1903 ) ( also known as Hillel Steinschneider ) was a Russian - Jewish genealogist and historian .
Olimpia Ludovisi ( 1656 -- 27 November 1700 ) was the eldest daughter of Niccolò Ludovisi and his third wife Costanza Pamphili .
Voivode George Ducas ( Greek : Γεώργιος Δούκας , Romanian : Gheorghe Duca ) ( d. 1685 ) was three times Prince of Moldavia ( September 1665 -- May 1666 , November 1668 -- 20 August 1672 , November 1678 -- January 1684 ) and one time Prince of Wallachia ( 1673 -- 29 November 1678 ) .
Lawson Wood , sometimes Clarence Lawson Wood , ( 23 August 1878 -- 26 October 1957 ) , was an English painter , illustrator and designer known for humorous depictions of cavemen and dinosaurs , policemen , and animals , especially a chimpanzee called Gran'pop , whose annuals circulated around the world .
Francisco Urcuyo Maliaños ( 30 July 1915 -- 14 September 2001 ) was a Nicaraguan politician , who served as Vice President of Anastasio Somoza Debayle from May 1967 to May 1972 .
Benjamin Bramer ( 15 February 1588 -- 17 March 1652 ) was a German mathematician , architect , inventor , and adviser .
Nuala Níc Con Iomaire ( died 16 July 2010 ) was an Irish playwright , producer , translator , artist and poet .
Mas Penewu Surakso Hargo , better known as Mbah Maridjan ( `` Grandfather Maridjan '' ) ( 5 February 1927 ? -- 26 October 2010 ) was the spiritual guardian or `` gatekeeper '' of the Indonesian volcano Mount Merapi .
Orville Vogel ( 1907 - -1991 ) was an American scientist and wheat breeder whose research made possible the `` Green Revolution '' in world food production .

Andrew McIntyre ( 9 August 1855 -- 30 March 1941 ) was a Scottish footballer who played as a full back .
Gavino Gulia ( 1835 - -1889 ) was a Maltese botanist and author of books on flora of that island .
James Jezreel , real name James Rowland White ( cir 1851 -- 2 March 1885 ) , was a nineteenth - century soldier and self - proclaimed prophet .
Nordepert ( or Nodepert ) was briefly the Abbot of Farfa in 888 .
Rufus L. Porter ( February 20 , 1897 -- February 1979 ) was a well - regarded poet living in the Pikes Peak region near Cascade , Colorado during the 1950s until his death in 1979 .
Fanny Butcher ( September 13 , 1888 -- May 11 , 1987 ) was a long time writer and literary critic for the Chicago Tribune newspaper .
William Mukama ( 1951 - 2002 ) , was a Ugandan teacher and politician and founding member of the Ninth October Movement .
Michael Critobulus ( Greek : Μιχαήλ Κριτοβούλος , c. 1410 -- c. 1470 ) was a Greek politician , scholar and historian .
Heinrich Amersdorffer ( 10 December 1905 -- 2 December 1986 ) was a German painter , printmaker , war artist and art teacher .
Moir Tod Stormonth Darling , Lord Stormonth - Darling FRSE DL LLD ( 3 November 1844 -- 2 June 1912 ) was a Scottish Conservative Party politician and judge .
Liviu Constantinescu ( 26 November 1914 -- 29 November 1997 ) was a Romanian geophysicist , professor of geophysics , member of the Romanian Academy .
Emily Bliss Gould ( c. 1825 - 31 August 1875 Perugia , Italy ) founded a school for Italian children of limited means .
Lope de Hoces ( fl . 1619 -- 21 October 1639 ) was a Spanish admiral who was killed in action at the Battle of the Downs .
François Cautaerts ( 1810 in Brussels -- 1881 in Brussels ) was a Belgian art painter from the 19th century .
Maulana Azhar ( died 1475 ) was a Persian calligrapher .
Reginald Koettlitz ( 1860 - -1916 ) was a British physician and polar explorer .
Peter Gee ( 1932 - -2005 ) was a British - born artist and developer who spent most of his life living and working in New York City .
Moran Mar Baselios Mar Thoma Mathews I ( 27 March 1907 -- 8 November 1996 ) was the Supreme head of the Indian Orthodox Church , which is also known as Malankara Orthodox Syrian Church .
Iwao Horiuchi ( 堀内 岩雄 , 9 December 1941 -- 4 March 2015 ) was a Japanese lightweight freestyle wrestler .
Nicholas Mills Sr . ( 23 November 1781 -- 13 September 1862 ) was a prominent businessman in Richmond , Virginia .
Henry Trengove or Nance ( by 1521 - 1561 ) , of Nance in Illogan , Cornwall , was an Cornish politician .
Muhammad Abdul Wahab Siddiqi ( 1942 - -1994 ) was a Sunni Muslim religious scholar and Sufi master .
An - Nasir ibn Alnas ( died 1088 ) was the fifth ruler of the Hammadids in Algeria , from 1062 until his death .
Charles L. Walker ( 1832 - -1904 ) was a Latter - day Saint hymnwriter , most noted for having written the words to the hymn `` Dearest Children , God is Near You '' .
Robert Quirk Short ( 1759 -- 31 January 1827 ) was a Church of England clergyman who emigrated to Canada in 1796 .
Fletcher Christian ( 25 September 1764 -- 20 September 1793 ) was master 's mate on board HMS Bounty during William Bligh 's voyage to Tahiti for breadfruit plants .
Frederick Wheeler ( 1853 - -1931 ) ( FRIBA ) was a British architect , born in Brixton , Surrey , in October 1853 .
Jules Chapon ( 1914 - -2007 ) , was a Dutch artist who moved to France in 1973 .
Eudald Pradell ( 1721 - -1788 ) was a typographer .
Krishna Nath Sarmah ( 1887 - 1947 ) was a renowned nationalist and social reformer from Assam .
Vincenzo Galli ( 1798 -- 1858 ) was an Italian opera singer and impresario .
Sir Arthur Vicars , KCVO ( 27 July 1862 -- 14 April 1921 ) was an English - born genealogist and heraldic expert who spent his adult life in Ireland .
José María García Lahiguera ( 9 March 1903 -- 14 July 1989 ) was a Spanish Roman Catholic who served as the Archbishop of Valencia from 1969 until his resignation came into effect in 1978 .
Mohammed Awzal ( Berber : Mḥemmed U - Ɛli U - Brahim Akʷbil Awzal / n Yinduzal ; 1680 - -1749 ) is the most important author in the literary tradition of the Berber Shilha language .

Hans Peter Edvind Johannesen ( born 3 September 1846 in Frederikshald , died 29 November 1909 ) was a Norwegian barrister and civil servant .
Guman Mal Lodha ( 1926 -- 22 March 2009 ) was the chief justice of Gauhati High Court and former member of Lok Sabha .
Mother Lettice Mary Tredway , C.R.L. , ( 1595 -- October 1677 ) , courtesy title Lady Tredway , was an English canoness regular and abbess who founded a monastery for the English members of her Order in 17th - century Europe .
John Manners , 4th Earl of Rutland ( c. 1559 -- 24 February 1588 ) was the son of Henry Manners , 2nd Earl of Rutland , and Lady Margaret Neville , daughter of Ralph Neville , 4th Earl of Westmorland .
Herman Schlom ( 1904 - -1983 ) was a film producer who first received film credit as an assistant director for Dracula in 1931 .
Norman Feather FRS FRSE PRSE ( 16 November 1904 , Pecket Well , Yorkshire -- 14 August 1978 , Christie Hospital , Manchester ) , was an English nuclear physicist .

Morris Lurie ( 30 October 1938 -- 8 October 2014 ) was an Australian writer of comic novels , short stories , essays , plays , and children 's books .
Josip Boljkovac ( Croatian pronunciation : ( jǒsip bǒʎkovat͡s ) , 12 November 1920 -- 10 November 2014 ) was a Croatian politician who served as the first Minister of Internal Affairs in the Croatian Government .

Charles Ashpitel Denton ( 24 October 1852 -- 28 September 1932 ) was an English amateur footballer who twice won the FA Cup with Wanderers .
Pat Booth , Lady Lowe ( 24 April 1943 -- 11 May 2009 ) was an English model , photographer and author of romantic fiction .
Cui Youfu ( 崔祐甫 ) ( 721 -- July 7 , 780 ) , courtesy name Yisun ( 貽孫 ) , was an official of the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty , serving as a chancellor briefly early during the reign of Emperor Dezong .

Willy Schmidt - Gentner ( 6 April 1894 -- 12 February 1964 ) was one of the most successful German composers of film music in the history of German - language cinema .
Felix Huston ( 1800 - -1857 ) was a lawyer , soldier , military opportunist and the first commanding general of the Army of the Republic of Texas under the Constitution of 1836 .

Dr John William Ballantyne FRSE FRCPE ( 4 June 1861 -- 23 January 1923 ) was a Scottish physician and obstetrician .
Franciszek Duszeńko ( 6 April 1925 -- 11 April 2008 ) was a Polish sculptor , professor of the Academy of Fine Arts in Gdańsk and its Rector in the years 1981 - -87 .
Cyril Gwynn ( 1897 - -1988 ) was a British poet , from Gower , in the City and County of Swansea .

Henry Villiers - Stuart , 1st Baron Stuart de Decies PC ( 8 June 1803 -- 23 January 1874 ) , was a British Tory politician .
Robert le Poer ( died 1344 ) was an Irish judge and Crown official who held the offices of Lord High Treasurer of Ireland and Chief Baron of the Irish Exchequer .
Andrea Pozzi ( 1778 - -1833 ) was an Italian painter , active mainly in his native Rome , as a painter of religious and mythologic histories .
Ilija Birčanin ( Serbian Cyrillic : Илија Бирчанин ; 12 August 1764 - 4 January 1804 ) was a Serbian knez ( Duke ) who was killed during the Slaughter of the Dukes , the incident that sparked the First Serbian Uprising of the Serbian Revolution , ultimately leading to Serbia 's liberation from the Ottoman Empire .
Elena Cantacuzino ( 1611 - -1687 ) was a Wallachian noble .
Lillian Cotton ( 1892 - -1962 ) was an American artist known for her portraits , especially of high - society figures and well - known actors , writers , and artists of her day .
Claudio Gabriele de Launay ( 6 October 1786 -- 21 February 1850 ) was prime minister of the Kingdom of Sardinia from 27 March to 7 May 1849 .
Edmund Schlink ( 3 March 1903 -- 20 May 1984 ) was a leading German Lutheran theologian in the modern ecumenical movement , especially in the World Council of Churches .
Welland Lathrop ( 1905 - -1981 ) was a dancer , teacher , painter , and choreographer and a leader of the west coast modern and avant - garde dance movement .
Béni Grosschmid ( 6 November 1852 -- 7 September 1938 ) , also known as Beno Zsögöd , was a Hungarian jurist .
Philip Falle ( 1656 - -1742 ) was a clergyman and historian of Jersey .
Walter Scott of Harden ( before 1563 -- 1629 ) , also known as Auld Wat , was a notorious Border Reiver .
Johann Georg Danninger ( died 1848 ) was an Austrian bronzesmith , known for making many of the bronze items that decorated the Viennese court of the Austrian Empire in the 19th century .
Prince Hans Ulrich von Eggenberg ( 1568 -- 18 October 1634 ) was an Austrian statesman , a son of Seyfried von Eggenberg , Lord of Erbersdorf ( 1526 - 1594 ) , and great - grandson of Balthasar Eggenberger ( died 1493 ) .
Joli Jászai ( 21 May 1907 -- 26 September 2008 ) was a Hungarian actress and entertainer .
Rt . Rev. Joseph Sakunoshin Motoda D.D. ( 22 February 1862 -- 16 April 1928 , 元田 作之進 ) was the first Japanese born Bishop of Tokyo in the Nippon Sei Ko Kai , the Anglican Church in Japan .
He Changling ( simplified Chinese : 贺长龄 ; traditional Chinese : 賀長齡 ; pinyin : Hè Chánglíng ; Wade -- Giles : He Ch'angling ) , ( March 18 , 1785 - -July 6 , 1848 ) , courtesy name Ougen ( 耦耕 ) , was a Chinese scholar and official of the Qing dynasty from Changsha , Hunan .
Roger II Trencavel ( died March 1194 ) was the Viscount of Carcassonne , Béziers , Razès , and Albi from 1167 or 1171 until his death .
Elizabeth Allan ( 9 April 1910 -- 27 July 1990 ) was an English actress who worked in both Britain and Hollywood , making about 50 films over more than a quarter century .
Elaine Kowalsky ( September 24 , 1948 -- September 17 , 2005 ) was a Canadian printmaker and artists ' rights campaigner who lived and worked in the United Kingdom for over 30 years .
Sam Donahue ( 18 March 1918 -- 22 March 1974 ) was an American swing music jazz tenor saxophonist , trumpeter and musical arranger .
Vladimir Potapov ( January 24 , 1914 -- December 21 , 1980 ) was a renowned Ukrainian mathematician .
Lady Anne Beauchamp , 16th Countess of Warwick ( 13 July 1426 -- 20 September 1492 ) was the daughter of Richard Beauchamp , 13th Earl of Warwick , and his second wife Isabel le Despenser , a daughter of Thomas le Despenser ( 22 September 1373 -- 13 January 1399/1400 ) and Constance of York .
Gregory Fiennes , 10th Baron Dacre ( 25 June 1539 , Hurstmonceaux , Sussex -- 25 December 1594 , Chelsea , Middlesex , England ) was an English courtier .
Cornwallis Maude , 1st Viscount Hawarden ( 19 September 1729 - 23 August 1803 ) was an Anglo - Irish peer and politician .
Sir John Stepney , 8th Baronet ( 1743 - 1811 ) , of Llanelli , Carmarthenshire , was a politician .
Dinis Gregório de Melo Castro e Mendonça ( Lisbon , 11 April 1735 -- Angra , 3 December 1793 ) was a member of high nobility , military and Portuguese colonial administrator , who exercised the role as the Captain - General of the Azores ( 1771 - 1793 ) .
Domenico Brescia ( 1866 - -1939 ) was an Italian composer who taught in Chile and Ecuador , then became known in the United States for writing chamber music as well as musical accompaniment for dramatic performances .
Hugh William Peel ( 14 September 1887 -- 4 March 1975 ) , better known as Gillie Potter , was an English comedian and broadcaster .
Rudolf Ernest Langer ( 8 March 1894 -- 11 March 1968 ) was an American mathematician , known for the Langer correction and as a president of the Mathematical Association of America .
John Hamrick ( 1875 - -1956 ) was an American entrepreneur in the theater business .
John Mylles ( c. 1604 -- March 1676 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons in 1659 and 1660 .
Bjørn Bjørnson ( 15 November 1859 -- 14 May 1942 ) was a Norwegian stage actor and theatre director .
Blind Harry ( c. 1440 -- 1492 ) , also known as Harry , Hary or Henry the Minstrel , is renowned as the author of The Actes and Deidis of the Illustre and Vallyeant Campioun Schir William Wallace , more commonly known as The Wallace .
Otto Max Koegel ( 16 October 1895 -- 27 June 1946 ) was a Nazi officer who served as a commander at Lichtenburg , Ravensbrück , Majdanek and Flossenbürg concentration camps .
John Watney ( 27 January 1834 -- 25 March 1923 ) was Honorary Secretary of the City and Guilds of London Institute for the Advancement of Technical Education .
Sree Padmanabhadasa Sree Uthradom Thirunal Marthanda Varma ( 22 March 1922 -- 16 December 2013 ) was the titular Maharaja of Travancore .
Carl Agardh Westerlund ( 12 January 1831 in Berga , near Kalmar -- 28 February 1908 in Ronneby ) was a Swedish malacologist .
Bohdan Skaradziński ( pen names Jan Brzoza , Kazimierz Podlaski ; 5 January 1931 -- 4 May 2014 ) was a Polish writer and social activist .
Henry Jacob ( 1563 - -1624 ) was an English clergyman of Calvinist views , who founded a separatist congregation associated with the Brownists .
Tom Peake ( c.1720 - -1767 ) was a noted English cricketer of the mid-18th century .
Nectarius of Jerusalem , born Nektarios Pelopidis ( Greek : Νεκτάριος Πελοπίδης , 1602 - -1676 ) was the Greek Orthodox Patriarch of Jerusalem from 1661 to 1669 .
Yosef Navon ( 1858 - -1934 ) was a Jerusalem businessman and the man principally responsible for the construction of the Jaffa--
Henry Odera Oruka ( 1 June 1944 , Nyanza Province -- 9 December 1995 , Nairobi ) was a Kenyan philosopher who is best known for `` Sage Philosophy , '' a project started in the 1970s in an attempt to preserve the knowledge of the indigenous thinkers in traditional African communities .
Johann Jacob Zimmermann ( November 25 , 1642 -- 1693 ) was a German nonconformist theologian , millenarian , mathematician , and astronomer .
Siegfried Taub ( 1876 , Telč , Margraviate of Moravia -- 1946 ) was a Sudeten German Jewish politician from Czechoslovakia .
Count Lajos Tisza de Borosjenő et Szeged ( 12 September 1832 - 26 January 1898 ) was a Hungarian politician , who served as Minister besides the King between 1892 and 1894 .
Bindon Blood Stoney FRS ( 13 June 1828 , Oakley Park , County Offaly -- 5 May 1909 , Dublin ) was an Irish engineer .
Solomon kaDinuzulu ( 1891 - -1933 ) was the king of the Zulu nation from 1913 until his death on 4 March 1933 at Kambi .
Sophia Armitt ( 1847 -- 12 June 1908 ) was a British teacher , writer , and naturalist .
Daniël van Vlierden ( 1651 , Hasselt -- 1716 , Hasselt ) was a Flemish sculptor who is mainly known for his Baroque sculpture in churches in the Prince - Bishopric of Liège .
Jelena Balšić ( Serbian Cyrillic : Јелена Балшић ; 1365/1366 -- 1443 ) , also known as Jelena Lazarević , was a medieval Serbian noblewoman and a member of the Lazarević dynasty .
Emilio Brambilla ( 26 June 1882 -- 17 October 1938 ) was an Italian athlete
Rueben Berry ( died March 1998 ) was a Canadian Football League coach who served as the head coach of the Saskatchewan Roughriders from 1983 to 1984 .
Henry MacManus ( MRHA ) ( c. 1810 -- 22 March 1878 ) was an Irish artist and teacher .
After Nymphidius ' death , Sporus would , in the year 69 , become involved with Otho , who was also killed by his enemies .
Benjamin Morrell ( July 5 , 1795 -- 1838 or 1839 ? ) was an American sea captain , explorer and trader who made a number of voyages , mainly to the Atlantic , the Southern Ocean and the Pacific Islands .
Frederik Vilhelm August Meinert ( 1833 , in Copenhagen -- 1912 ) , was a Danish entomologist and editor of the first series of Entomologiske Meddelelser .
Arnold Wathen Robinson RWA , FMGP ( 1888 - -1955 ) was an English stained - glass artist .
Jacqueline Briskin , née Orgell ( 18 December 1927 -- 24 December 2014 ) was a British - born American writer specializing in historical fiction from 1970 to 1995 .
Brian Lemon ( 11 February 1937 -- 11 October 2014 ) was a British jazz pianist and arranger .
Willie Horne ( 23 January 1922 -- 25 March 2001 ) was an English rugby league footballer .
Henry Cavendish , 2nd Duke of Newcastle - upon - Tyne , KG , PC ( 24 June 1630 -- 26 July 1691 ) , styled Viscount Mansfield until 1676 , was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1660 to 1676 , and then inherited the dukedom .
John Carnegie , 1st Earl of Northesk ( 1611 - -1667 ) , was a Scottish noble who supported the Royalist cause during the Wars of the Three Kingdoms .
Robert Brook Aspland ( 19 January 1805 - 21 June 1869 ) was an English Unitarian minister and editor .
Ron Hovey OAM ( 25 August 1932 -- 6 January 2015 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Geelong in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Evgen Sajovic ( 25 November 1913 - 1986 ) was a Slovene painter , also known for his frescos and sgraffito as well as book illustrations .
Giacomo Giuseppe Federico Delpino ( 27 December 1833 -- 14 May 1905 ) was an Italian botanist who made very important observations on the pollination of flowers by insects .
Christian Lupus ( 23 July 1612 -- 10 July 1681 ) was a historian .
Karol Hiller ( 6 December 1891 in Łódź - December 1939 ) was a Polish painter .
Aron Elias Seligmann ( 26 April 1747 -- 11 January 1824 ) was a German Jewish financier .
George Trewick ( 15 November 1933 -- 2003 ) was an English footballer who played as a Wing half .
Barry Mather ( 20 February 1909 -- 30 March 1982 ) was a Canadian journalist , columnist , and politician .
John Seden ( 1840 - -1921 ) was a hybridist and horticulturist best known for the hybrids he created while in the employment of Veitch Nurseries .
Nicholas Eymerich ( Catalan : Nicolau Aymerich ) ( c. 1316 -- 4 January 1399 ) was a Roman Catholic theologian and Inquisitor General of the Inquisition of the Crown of Aragon in the later half of the 14th century .
Marko Lerinski ( Bulgarian : Марко Лерински , `` Marko of Florina '' ; 20 June 1862 - -13 June 1902 ) was the nickname of Georgi Ivanov Gyurov ( Георги Иванов Гюров ) , also known as Georgi Geroyski or Marko Voyvoda , a Bulgarian military man and revolutionary .
John William Nicholson , FRS ( 1 November 1881 -- 3 October 1955 ) was an English mathematician .
Nuño Álvarez de Carazo ( floruit 1028 - -1054 ) was a Castilian nobleman , diplomat , and warrior .
Kay Daniels ( 17 June 1941 -- 17 July 2001 ) was a historian and a public servant , who made a significant contribution to knowledge on women in Australia , as well as Australian social and colonial history .
General Walther Buhle ( 26 October 1894 -- 28 December 1959 ) was an infantry General in the German army who was the Chief of the Army Staff of the Oberkommando der Wehrmacht from 1942 and chief of armaments for the army in 1945 .
Dick Hingston ( 16 December 1915 -- 3 December 1999 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played for Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Pieter Bast ( ca 1550 -- 17 March 1605 ) was a Dutch cartographer , engraver and draftsman .
Frank Abney Hastings ( Greek : Φραγκίσκος Άστιγξ ) ( 14 February 1794 -- 1 June 1828 ) was a British naval officer and Philhellene .
Earl Anthony Robinson ( 8 December 1955 -- 1980 ) , better known as General Echo , aka Ranking Slackness , was one of the first reggae deejays to move away from ' cultural ' lyrics towards ' slackness ' ( risqué or sexually explicit lyrics ) .
Harry L. Hansen ( 21 October 1911 , New York City - 3 August 1992 , Cambridge Massachusetts ) was a pioneer of management education .
Edward Garth - Turnour , 1st Earl Winterton FRS ( 1734 -- 10 August 1788 ) was a British politician .
Nikolaos Trikoupis ( Greek : Νικόλαος Τρικούπης ; 1868 - -1956 ) was a Greek general and politician , most notable for his service in the Greco - Turkish War of 1919 - -1922 , where he was taken as a prisoner of war .
Alonso Meléndez de Guzmán ( b. ? - d. 1342 ) was a Spanish noble from León of the House of Guzmán .
Erwin Chargaff ( 11 August 1905 -- 20 June 2002 ) was an Austro - Hungarian biochemist who immigrated to the United States during the Nazi era and was a professor of biochemistry at Columbia University medical school .
Kuai Xiang ( Chinese : 蒯祥 ; pinyin : Kuǎi Xiáng ; 1398 - -1481 ) was a Chinese architect and engineer widely known as designer of the Forbidden City and originator of the Xiangshan Carpenters .
Ignác Frank ( 1788 - -1850 ) was a Hungarian jurist and one of the most renowned private law scholars of his time .
Henry Clay Whitney ( 23 February 1831 -- 1905 ) was a United States lawyer who was a close friend of President Abraham Lincoln , and later a biographer of the president .
Shaheed ( Martyr ) Corporal Hussain Adam , was a Maldivian soldier who died while defending the Maldives National Defence Force headquarters , during the 1988 Maldives coup d'état on 3 November 1988 .
Sir Daniel Cooper , 1st Baronet GCMG ( 1 July 1821 -- 5 June 1902 ) was the first speaker of the Legislative Assembly of New South Wales and a noted philatelist .
François - Marie Treyve ( 1847 - -1906 ) was a French landscape gardener .
John W. Slayton ( 1863 - -1935 ) was an American socialist lecturer and politician .
Joseph Coleman Smith ( 17 May 1934 -- 5 September 1998 ) , who performed and recorded under the name Sonny Knight , was an African - American singer , songwriter and author .
Pomponio Allegri ( 1521 -- fl . 1593 ) was an Italian painter , the son of Correggio .
Lavemai Kitione Takitau ( 16 April 1934 -- 2 June 2006 ) , who fought under the name Kitione Lave , was a Tongan heavyweight boxer .
Peter Mews ( 25 March 1619 -- 9 November 1706 ) was an English Royalist theologian and bishop .
Allan Roberts ( 28 October 1943 -- 21 March 1990 ) was a British politician who was the Labour Member of Parliament for Bootle from 1979 until his death .
Burton Wadsworth Jones ( 1 October 1902 , Redwood Falls , Minnesota -- 8 December 1983 , Wellesley , Massachusetts ) was an American mathematician , known for his work on quadratic forms .
Nyan Shein gives Ba Zaw 's date of death as 1943 , but Amar claims that her husband found Ba Zaw 's obituary in the newspaper and that he died on 11 December 1942 .
Fred Backway ( 2 October 1913 -- 28 March 1995 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with South Melbourne , Melbourne and Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Irene Lieblich ( 20 April 1923 -- 28 December 2008 ) was a Polish - born artist and Holocaust survivor noted for illustrating the books of Nobel laureate Isaac Bashevis Singer and for her paintings highlighting Jewish life and culture .
Sir Mountstuart Elphinstone Grant Duff GCSI CIE PC FRS ( 21 February 1829 -- 12 January 1906 ) , known as M. E. Grant Duff before 1887 and as Sir Mountstuart Grant Duff thereafter , was a Scottish politician , administrator and author .
Ha Po - gyong ( Hangul : 하보경 ; born 1906 - died 1996 ) was a Korean dancer who was designated an Important Intangible Cultural Asset .
Ronald Acott Hall CBE ( 24 May 1892 -- 21 March 1966 ) , was a British diplomat , writer and Liberal Party politician .
Jaime Valencia ( 1916 in Quito -- 2010 ) was an Ecuadorian painter and sculptor .
Gloria Fonda ( 1896 - January 20 , 1978 ) was a U.S. actress of the silent film era .
George H. Kendall ( c.1854 - -1924 ) was the president of the New York Bank Note Company , that printed stock certificates .
Solomon Adler ( August 6 , 1909 -- August 4 , 1994 ) was an economist in the U.S. Treasury Department who served as Treasury representative in China during World War II . He was identified by Whittaker Chambers and Elizabeth Bentley as a Soviet intelligence source and resigned from the Treasury Department in 1950 .
Luigi Vannucchi ( 25 November 1930 -- 30 August 1978 ) was an Italian film , stage and television actor .
Bruno Metsu ( French pronunciation : ​(bʁyno mɛtsy ) ; 28 January 1954 -- 14 October 2013 ) was a French footballer and football manager .
Doina Badea ( 6 January 1940 , Craiova - 4 March 1977 , Bucharest ) was a Romanian singer of popular music .
Duchess Charlotte Frederica of Mecklenburg - Schwerin ( 4 December 1784 -- 13 July 1840 ) , was the first wife of King Christian VIII from 1806 until 1810 , before he became King of Denmark .
Wynne Ellis ( 1790 - -1875 ) was a wealthy British haberdasher , politician and art collector .
Rice Price ( born 3 January 1807 at Wroughton , Wiltshire ; died 30 November 1845 at Oxford ) was an English cricketer with amateur status .
John Chester Buttre ( 10 June 1821 Auburn , New York -- 2 December 1893 Ridgewood , New Jersey ) , was an American steel - plate engraver and lithographer , responsible for some 3 000 engraved portraits of American political , naval and military personalities .
Rafał Górski ( 22 September 1973 -- 4 July 2010 ) was a Polish historian , writer , anarchist , trade union and housing activist .
Thomas Tomkis ( or Tomkys ) ( c. 1580 -- 1634 ) was an English playwright of the late Elizabethan and the Jacobean eras , and arguably one of the more cryptic figures of English Renaissance drama .
Dinos Dimopoulos ( Greek : Ντίνος Δημόπουλος ; 22 August 1921 -- 28 February 2003 ) was a Greek actor , film director , screenwriter and theatre director .
William Patrick Ryan ( 1867 -- 1942 ) , was an Irish author and journalist .
Gotthardt Kuehl ( 28 November 1850 -- 9 January 1915 ) was a German painter and a representative of early German Impressionism .
Pope Gregory XIII ( Latin : Gregorius XIII ; 7 January 1502 -- 10 April 1585 ) , born Ugo Boncompagni , was Pope of the Catholic Church from 13 May 1572 to his death in 1585 .
George Alexander Hamilton ( 29 August 1802 -- 17 September 1871 ) was a minor British Conservative Party politician and later a prominent civil servant .
Richard Vicary ( 1918 - 2006 ) was a British artist and printmaker .
Emperor Gaozu of Tang ( 566 -- 25 June 635 ) , born Li Yuan , courtesy name Shude , was the founder of the Tang Dynasty of China , and the first emperor of this dynasty from 618 to 626 .
Makhdum Muhammad Ajmal ( 7 September 1919 , Ludhiana , India -- 1994 ) was an academic psychologist who established the first university psychology department in Pakistan .
Joseph Francis Joy ( September 13 , 1883 - February 1957 ) was born in the small mining town of Cumberland , Maryland .

Princess Joséphine Caroline of Belgium ( 18 October 1872 -- 6 January 1958 ) .
Carlo Randanini ( Rome -Turin , 1884 ) was an Italian painter , in oil and watercolor , mainly of genre subjects , including costume genre .

Pablo Vicente de Solá , ( 1761 - -1826 ) , was a Basque , and the twelfth and last Spanish colonial governor of Alta California , 1815 - 1822 .
Cyril Pearce ( 28 January 1908 -- 1990 ) was an English footballer who played in the Football League for Charlton Athletic , Newport County and Swansea Town .
Edward Stafford , 2nd Earl of Wiltshire ( 7 April 1470 -- 24 March 1499 ) was an English nobleman .
Charles Dundas Lawrie ( 8 February 1923 -- 31 August 1976 ) was a Scottish International golfer , administrator , and golf course architect ; described as one of the best golfers of his era and as one of golf architecture 's finest representatives .
Andrew Picken ( 1788 -- 23 November 1833 ) was a novelist born in Paisley , Scotland .
Nicolas Geffrard ( 1871 - -1930 ) was a Haitian musician best known for composing La Dessalinienne , the Haitian national anthem .

Laurie Thompson ( 26 February 1938 -- 8 June 2015 ) was a British academic and translator , noted for his translations of Swedish literature into English .

Gerardo Emilio San Clemente Zárate ( 1818 Remedios , Antioquia - 1880 Barcelona ) was a photographer and painter from Colombia .
Theobald Stapleton , alias Teabóid Gallduf or Gallduff ( 1589 -- 13 September 1647 ) , was an Irish Roman Catholic priest born in County Tipperary , Ireland .
Ezekiel Abraham Ezekiel ( 1757 - -1806 ) was an English engraver .
Frank Lewis Dowling ( 18 October 1823 -- 10 October 1867 , in Norfolk Street , Strand , London ) was a British newspaper editor .
Perez ben Elijah of Corbeil ( died 1295 ) was a French tosafist , son of the Talmudist Elijah of Tours .
Onni Aukusti Mäenpää ( 5 January 1891 , Soini - 1933 , Petrozavodsk ) was a Finnish shoemaker and politician .
Arthur Lawley , 6th Baron Wenlock , GCSI GCIE KCMG ( 12 November 1860 -- 14 June 1932 ) , was a British colonial administrator who served variously as Administrator of Matabeleland , Governor of Western Australia , Lieutenant - Governor of the Transvaal , and Governor of Madras .
George Sullivan Dodge ( 3 August 1838 - 24 August 1881 ) was an American military officer and merchant .
Prince Peter of Greece and Denmark ( Greek : Πρίγκιψ Πέτρος της Ελλάδος ; 3 December 1908 -- 15 October 1980 ) was a Greek soldier and anthropologist specialising in Tibetan culture and polyandry .
John Bernard Lee ( 10 January 1908 -- 16 January 1981 ) , known as Bernard Lee , was an English actor best known for his role as M in the first eleven Eon - produced James Bond films .
George Layman was born at Wonnerup House in 1838 and resided there until his death on 26 March 1922 .
Henry de Cobham , 1st Baron Cobham ( of Kent ) ( c. 1260 -- 25 August 1339 ) was an English Peer .

Nadezhda Chaikova ( Чайкова Надежда ) ( 1963 - -1996 ) was a correspondent for the Russian weekly Obshchaya Gazeta .
Thomas Brown Clark ( 1895 - -1983 ) was a Scottish painter who worked in oils , pastels and watercolours .
Giacomo Tebaldi ( died 1465 ) ( called the Cardinal of Montefeltro or the Cardinal of Sant'Anastasia ) was an Italian Roman Catholic bishop and cardinal .
Godas ( died 533 ) was a Gothic nobleman of the Vandal kingdom in North Africa .
