Thomas Mukarobgwa ( 1924 - -1999 ) was a Zimbabwean painter and sculptor who worked as a gallery attendant for much of his career .
Armand Vetulani ( 16 December 1909 -- 3 April 1994 ) was a Polish art historian and educator , first director of the Central Bureau for Art Exhibitions .
Gaspare Diziani ( 1689 -- 17 August 1767 ) was an Italian painter of the late - Baroque or Roccoco period , active mainly in the Veneto but also in Dresden and Munich .
Joseph Vollmer ( 1871 - -1955 ) was a German automobile designer and engineer and a pioneering tank designer .
Leonard Carey ( 25 February 1887 -- 11 September 1977 ) was an English - born character actor who very often played butlers in Hollywood films of the 1930s , ' 40s , and ' 50s .
Alan Squire ( 9 February 1927 -- 12 June 2003 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with St Kilda in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Rowland Dawkins ( died 1691 ) was a Welsh military colonel and politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1654 and 1656 .
Archibald Mosman ( 15 October 1799 -- 29 January 1863 ) was a Scottish - born merchant , grazier and whaler in New South Wales , Australia .
Karl Emil Ståhlberg ( 30 November 1862 -- 27 June 1919 ) was a Finnish photographer and engineer .
Lucy Godiva Woodcock ( 23 February 1889 -- 29 February 1968 ) was an Australian pacifist , schoolteacher , trade union official and women 's activist .
Richard Wooddeson ( 1745 - -1822 ) was an English jurist , Vinerian Professor of English Law from 1777 .
Sidsel Ulfstand ( died 1575 ) , was a Danish ( Scanian ) landholder and county administrator .
Jakob Sande ( 1 December 1906 -- 16 March 1967 ) was a Norwegian writer , poet and folk singer from Dale in Sunnfjord .
David Gaunson ( 3 September 1879 -- 7 March 1946 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with St Kilda in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Anwar Pasha ( Bengali : আনোয়ার পাশা ; 1928 - -1971 ) was a Bangladeshi author and novelist .
Ida Lupino ( 4 February 1918 -- 3 August 1995 ) was an Anglo - American film actress , singer , director and producer , a pioneer among women filmmakers .
Charles Roka ( Róka Károly , 1912 - -1999 ) was a Hungarian painter living in Norway whose name became synonymous with an excess of artistic kitsch .
Mollie Harris ( born Mollie Woodley , 23 June 1913 -- 2 October 1995 ) was an English actress and author , known for her appearances as village shopkeeper Martha Woodford in the BBC Radio soap opera The Archers .
José Datrino , known as prophet Gentileza ( 11 April 1917 -- 28 May 1996 ) was a Brazilian urban personality , kind of a preacher , which became known from 1980 by making quirky inscriptions under an overpass in Rio de Janeiro , where he walked in a white robe and long beard .
Leo Drabent ( 15 June 1899 -- 20 November 1944 ) was a German peace campaigner and Communist activist .
Hermann Wesel ( died June 1563 ) was a German ecclesiastic in Livonia , and the last Roman Catholic Bishop of Dorpat ( Tartu ) .
Sir Richard Grosvenor , 2nd Baronet ( c. 1604 -- 31 January 1665 ) was an ancestor of the modern day Dukes of Westminster .
Alta M. Hulett ( born near Rockford , Illinois , 4 June 1854 ; died in California , 27 March 1877 ) was a United States lawyer .
Ray Wartman ( 29 January 1915 -- 20 April 2008 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the VFL .
Marko Penov ( 2 October 1922 -- 24 March 1998 ) was a well known Serbian artistic woodcarver and restorer of artifacts .
Francesco Comi , also known as il Muto da Verona or il Fornaretto , ( Bologna , 1682 - 1 January 1769 ) was an Italian painter of the Baroque Period .
Bahadur Singh Dhakad ( died 19 September 2007 ) was an Indian politician .
John Kingsmill ( 1 September 1920 - 6 August 2013 ) was an Australian author , actor and public speaker , and amateur social historian .
Fritz Tarnow ( April 13 , 1880 , Bad Oeynhausen , Province of Westphalia - October 23 , 1951 ) was an important Social Democrat trade unionists and Reichstag deputy during the Weimar Republic .
Roy Selwyn - Smith ( 22 September 1923 in Walton - on - Thames -- 16 June 2006 ) , was well known as a sculptor of English plastic figures and toy soldiers .
Shah Hussain ( 1538 - -1599 ) was a Punjabi Sufi poet who is regarded as a Sufi saint .
Edward Henry Carson , Baron Carson , PC , PC ( Ire ) , KC ( 9 February 1854 -- 22 October 1935 ) , from 1900 to 1921 known as Sir Edward Carson , was an Irish unionist politician , barrister and judge .
Mrs Gardner or Sarah Cheney ( fl . 1763 - -1795 ) was a British comedic actress and playwright .
René Fülöp - Miller , born Philip Müller ( 17 February 1891 -- 17 May 1963 ) was an Austrian cultural historian and writer .
Bakhtiyar ( Persian : بختیار , died 978 ) , better known by his laqab of ʿIzz al - Dawla ( Arabic : عز الدولة، , `` Glory of the Dynasty '' ) , was the Buyid amir of Iraq ( 967 - -978 ) .
Stephen Perse ( 1548 -- 30 September 1615 ) was an English academic and philanthropist .
Hughie Hay ( died 23 October 2012 ) was a Scottish professional footballer who played as an inside forward .
Frederick Wicks ( 23 February 1840 -- 30 March 1910 ) was an English author and inventor , whose book The British Constitution and Government was first published in 1871 and ran to several editions .
García Gómez ( died after 1017 ) was a Leonese count , at least from 971 .
Patrick Duigenan , KC , BA , MA , LLB , LLD , FTCD ( 1735 - -11 April 1816 ) , Irish lawyer and politician , was the son of a Leitrim Catholic farmer surnamed Ó Duibhgeannáin .
Thomas Bevan ( 1796 ? - 31 January 1819 ) was , with fellow Welshman David Jones , the first Christian missionary to Madagascar , sent by the London Missionary Society .
Vikramaditya I ( Kannada : ವಿಕ್ರಮಾದಿತ್ಯ ೧ ) ( 655 - -680 CE ) was the third son and followed his father , Pulakeshin II on to the Chalukya throne .
Qutlugh Nigar Khanum ( also spelled Kutlak Nigar Khanum ; d. 1505 ) was the first wife and chief consort of Umar Shaikh Mirza II , the King of Ferghana Valley .
John Smart ( c. 1740 - -1811 ) , was an English painter of portrait miniatures .
Emma Eleonora Kendrick ( c. 1788 - -1871 ) was a British miniature - painter who was prominent during the reigns of Kings George IV and William IV .
Joseph Godfrey ( January 1894 - January 1977 ) , commonly known as Joby Godfrey , was an English professional footballer who played in the Football League for Birmingham , Coventry City , Manchester City and Merthyr Town .
Ernest Choquette ( 18 November 1862 -- 29 March 1941 ) was a Canadian physician , novelist , and politician .
John Edmund Sharrock Moore ARCS ( 10 May 1870 -- 15 January 1947 ) was an English biologist , best known for leading two expeditions to Tanganyika .
Tlacaelel I ( 1397 -- 1487 ) was the principal architect of the Aztec Triple Alliance and hence the Mexica ( Aztec ) empire .
Robert Jewell ( 20 January 1920 * -- 10 May 1998 ) was an Australian actor who mostly worked as a Dalek or other robot operator on Doctor Who in the late 1960s , also playing a cameo as Bing Crosby in the serial The Daleks ' Master Plan .
Henry Ogg Forbes ( 30 January 1851 -- 27 October 1932 ) was a Scottish explorer , ornithologist , and botanist .
Adelsteen Normann ( 1 May 1848 - 26 December 1918 ) was a Norwegian painter who worked in Berlin .
( Dudley ) Geoffrey Stewart - Smith ( 29 December 1933 -- 13 March 2004 ) was a British politician .
Benjamin Akzin ( Hebrew : בנימין אקצין‎ ) ( 1904 - -1985 ) was an early Zionist activist and , later , an Israeli professor of law .
Alexander Leslie - Melville , 7th Earl of Leven ( 7 November 1749 -- 22 February 1820 ) was a Scottish Whig politician and peer .
Frans Hendrik Karel Zaalberg ( 26 November 1873 -- 13 February 1928 ) was an Indo ( Eurasian ) journalist and politician in the Dutch East Indies .
Frederick Ringer ( 1838 - -1907 ) was a British merchant who took over Thomas Glover 's role as leader in the Nagasaki foreign settlement .
Ahmad Zaidi Adruce served three terms before passing on peacefully on 5 December 2000 , leaving behind a lasting legacy as a true nationalist and as his people 's first scholar .
Norman McKinnel ( 10 February 1870 -- 29 March 1932 ) was a Scottish stage and film actor and playwright , active from the 1890s until his death .
Hassen Belkhodja , also known as Hassan Belkhodja , born March 10 , 1916 in Ras Jebel , died November 29 , 1981 , was a Tunisian politician and businessman .
Djamaluddin Adinegoro ( 14 August 1904 -- 8 January 1967 ) was an Indonesian press pioneer .
Major General Sir ( Henry ) Cecil Lowther KCMG CB CVO DSO FRGS ( 1 January 1869 -- 1 November 1940 ) was a British general and Conservative politician , the fourth son of William Lowther .
Fiachnae mac Ainbítha ( died 886 ) or Fiachna mac Ainfítha was a Dál Fiatach king of Ulaid , which is now Ulster , Ireland .
Mesa Kincaid ( born Cheryl Holm ; 23 September 1956 - 6 September 2009 ) was a talk radio host in the Minneapolis - St . Paul broadcast area .
Ngụy Văn Thà ( 16 January 1943 - 19 January 1974 ) was a Republic of Vietnam ( South Vietnam ) naval officer .
Reg Spencer ( 1 December 1908 -- 16 March 1981 ) was an English footballer who played as a left half for Tranmere Rovers .
Henning Carlsen ( 4 June 1927 -- 30 May 2014 ) was a Danish film director , screenwriter , and producer most noted for his documentaries and his contributions to the style of cinéma vérité .
Anthony Bedingfield ( died 1651 ) was an English merchant and politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1640 to 1648 .
Joshua David Stone ( 7 December 1953 -- August 2005 ) was an American author and teacher in the Ascended Master Teachings ( sometimes called the Ascension Movement ) , a group of religions based on Theosophy .
Arthur Charles Fox - Davies ( 28 February 1871 -- 19 May 1928 ) was a British author on heraldry .
Maria Lidka ( May 27 , 1914 - -12 December 2013 ) was a German - born classical violinist .
Folgóre da San Gimignano ( folˈɡoːre da ˈsan dʒimiɲˈɲaːno ) , pseudonym of Giacomo di Michele or Jacopo di Michele ( c. 1270 -- c. 1332 ) was an Italian poet .
Alan Frank Guttmacher , MD ( 1898 - -1974 ) was an American obstetrician / gynecologist .
Tom Kromer ( 1906 - -1969 ) was an American writer known for his one novel , Waiting for Nothing , an account of vagrant or hobo life during the nineteen - thirties .
Surajit Chandra Sinha ( 1926 - -27 February , 2002 ) was born in Durgapur Upazila , of Netrokona District , in Mymensingh Division , then in Bengal and now in Bangladesh .
İhsan Sabancı ( 1931 - -1979 ) , a second - generation member of the renowned Sabancı family , was a Turkish businessman .
Emperor Xiaowu of Liu Song ( 劉宋孝武帝 ) ( 430 - -464 ) , personal name Liu Jun ( 劉駿 ) , courtesy name Xiulong ( 休龍 ) , nickname Daomin ( 道民 ) , was an emperor of the Chinese dynasty Liu Song .
Fred Whibley ( Fredrick George Whibley , 1855 - 1919 ) abandoned a career as clerk in a London bank to escape from the constraints and social expectations of respectability in the Victorian era .
Frank Bokas ( 13 May 1914 -- 1996 ) was a Scottish footballer .
George Hawking ( 22 March 1902 -- 25 November 1968 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Prince Whipple ( 1750 - 1796 ) was an African - American slave and later freedman who accompanied his former owner , General William Whipple of the New Hampshire militia , during the American Revolutionary War.hi
Thomas Savage , 1st Viscount Savage ( circa 1586 -- 20 November 1635 ) , known as Sir Thomas Savage , 2nd Baronet from 1615 to 1626 , was an English peer and courtier in the court of Charles I. Savage was the son and heir of Sir John Savage , 1st Baronet and his wife Mary Alington .
Thomas Hookham ( ca.1739 - 1819 ) was a bookseller and publisher in London in the 18th-19th centuries .
Edmond Thieffry ( 28 September 1892 -- 11 April 1929 ) was a Belgian First World War air ace and aviation pioneer .
Baron François Narmon ( 26 January 1934 -- 14 March 2013 ) was a Belgian businessman and president of Dexia Group and the Belgian Olympic Committee .
Gilles Lauzon ( Lauson ) ( 1631 - -1687 ) was a talented French coppersmith and a member of `` le grande recrue '' , a group of roughly 100 Frenchman recruited to populate the colony of New France .
Sir Robert Moray ( alternative spellings : Murrey , Murray ) ( 1608 or 1609 -- 4 July 1673 ) was a Scottish soldier , statesman , diplomat , judge , spy , freemason and natural philosopher .
Thomas McNulty ( born 30 December 1929 in Salford , Greater Manchester ; Died April 1979 ) was an English football player .
The World War and Its Consequences ( 1919 ) An Explorer - Scientist 's Pilgrimage : the Autobiography of William Herbert Hobbs ( 1952 ) .
Venkatraman Radhakrishnan ( 18 May 1929 -- 3 March 2011 ) was a space scientist and member of the Royal Swedish Academy of Sciences .
Lucas Franchoys the Elder or Lucas Francois ( 1574 - -1643 ) was a Flemish painter of history paintings and portraits .
Gustavo Petricioli Iturbide ( 19 August 1928 -- 9 October 1998 ) was a Mexican economist who served as Secretary of Finance ( 1986 - -1988 ) in the last cabinet of Miguel de la Madrid and as Mexican ambassador to the United States ( January 1989 - -1993 ) .
William Niven ( 2 October 1850 -- 2 June 1937 ) was a mineralogist and archeologist noted for his discovery of the minerals yttrialite , thorogummite , aguilarite and nivenite ( named after him ) , as well as a set of controversial tablets .
John FitzPatrick , 2nd Earl of Upper Ossory FRS DL ( 2 May 1745 -- 13 February 1818 ) , styled ' Lord Gowran ' from 1751 to 1758 , was an Irish peer and member of parliament .
Friedrich Hartmann Graf ( 23 August 1727 -- 19 August 1795 ) was a German flautist and composer .
Zoubeir Turki ( 1924 -- 23 October 2009 ) was a Tunisian painter and sculptor of Turkish origin .

Sidney Siegel ( 4 January 1916 in New York -- 29 November 1961 ) was an American psychologist who became especially well known for his work in popularising non - parametric statistics for use in the behavioural sciences .
Mateus Fernandes ( died 10 April 1515 ) , also called Mateus Fernandes the Elder , was a Portuguese architect .
Brikt Jensen ( 15 September 1928 -- 14 November 2011 ) was a Norwegian publisher , writer , journal editor , professor who also hosted a popular TV program about literature .
Nathaniel Ndazana Nakasa ( 12 May 1937 -- 14 July 1965 ) better known as Nat Nakasa was a South African journalist and short story writer .
Marie Cuttoli ( née Myriam Bordes ; 1879 -- 1973 ) was an Algerian - born French entrepreneur and patron of modernist tapestry .
Alexander Constantine Ionides ( Greek : Κωνσταντίνος Ιωνίδης or Κωνσταντίνος Ιωάννου Ioannou or Κωνσταντίνος Ιπλιξής Ipliksis ; 1 September 1810 -- 10 November 1890 ) was a British art patron and collector , of Greek ancestry .
Charles Chabot ( baptised 19 March 1815 - 15 October 1882 ) was an English graphologist who , as part of the firm of Netherclift , Chabot and Matheson , was an early practitioner of questioned document examination .
Bartolomeu Dias ( Portuguese pronunciation : ( baɾtuluˈmew ˈdi.ɐʃ ) ; Anglicized : Bartholomew Diaz ; c. 1451 -- 29 May 1500 ) , a nobleman of the Portuguese royal household , was a Portuguese explorer .
Robert Jocelyn , 3rd Earl of Roden KP , PC PC ( I ) ( 27 October 1788 -- 20 March 1870 ) , styled Viscount Jocelyn between 1797 and 1820 , was an Irish Tory politician and supporter of Protestant causes .
Francis Needham , 1st Earl of Kilmorey ( 5 April 1748 -- 21 November 1832 ) , known as Francis Needham until 1818 and as The Viscount Kilmorey from 1818 to 1822 , was an Anglo - Irish soldier and Member of Parliament .
Treat Baldwin Johnson ( 1875 - 1947 ) was an American chemist , born at Bethany , Connecticut .
Joe Darion , ( 30 January 1917 - 6 June 2001 ) was an American musical theatre lyricist , most famous for Man of La Mancha .
Paul Healion ( 3 June 1978 - 16 August 2009 ) was an Irish racing cyclist from Dunboyne , Co. Meath .
Bart Van den Bossche ( 17 April 1964 -- 6 January 2013 ) was a Flemish singer , actor and radio / TV presenter .
John Crawte ( December 1763 at Frensham , Surrey -- 7 October 1836 at Bexley , Kent ) was an English cricketer who played mainly for Kent .
B. Vithalacharya or B. Vittalacharya ( 18 January 1920 -- 28 May 1999 ) was an Indian film director and producer known for his works in Telugu cinema , and Kannada cinema .
Princess Vera Constantinovna of Russia , also Vera Konstantinovna ( Russian : Вера Константиновна Романова ; 24 April 1906 -- 11 January 2001 ) , was the youngest child of Grand Duke Konstantine Konstantinovich of Russia and his wife , Grand Duchess Elizabeth Mavrikievna .
Tra Hoa Bo Dê was a king of Champa from 1342 to 1360 .
William Ernest Cooke ( 25 July 1863 -- 7 November 1947 ) , generally referred to as `` W. Ernest Cooke '' or informally `` Ernest Cooke '' , was an Australian astronomer , credited with a number of important scientific breakthroughs and improved methodologies in astronomical observations and star cataloguing .
Etbin Kristan ( 15 April 1867 -- 22 November 1953 ) was a Slovenian labour leader and Social Democratic politician and writer during the late - Austrian - Hungarian and the Yugoslav monarchy .
Perry Broad , also Pery Broad ( 25 April 1921 -- 28 November 1993 ) was a Brazilian Non - commissioned officer SS - Unterscharführer , active at Auschwitz from April 1942 - 1945 as a translator and stenographer at the Auschwitz headquarters .
At the time of his death in May 1875 , Jeremiah Hamilton was said by obituaries to be the richest black man in the United States .
Carter W. Clarke ( died 1987 at age 90 ) was a U.S. Army intelligence officer and brigadier general .
Elvia Carrillo Puerto ( 1878 -- 1967 ) was a Mexican socialist politician and feminist activist .
Herman Wildenvey ( 20 July 1885 -- 27 September 1959 ) , born Herman Theodor Portaas , was one of the most prominent Norwegian poets of the twentieth century .
Vladislav Titelbah ( Serbian Cyrillic : Владислав Тителбах ; 1847 - -1925 ) was a Czech - born Serbian painter .
Derick Heathcoat - Amory , 1st Viscount Amory ( /ˈeɪmərɪ/ AY - mər - ee ; 26 December 1899 -- 20 January 1981 ) was a British Conservative politician and member of the House of Lords .
Tony Allan ( 22 September 1949 -- 9 July 2004 ) was a British broadcaster and voice over artist .
Guillaume Guiart ( or Guiard ) ( died c. 1316 ) was a French chronicler and poet .
Sir Robert Dillington , 2nd Baronet ( ca . 1634 -- 25 April 1687 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1659 and 1685 .
Lady Sophia Burrell ( 1753 - -1802 ) was an English poet and dramatist .
Domingo Gribeo y Martin ( 1558 - 1649 ) was a Spanish Military , Mayordomo of Hospital , and Regidor of Buenos Aires during the Viceroyalty of Peru .
Morits Skaugen , Sr . ( 27 June 1920 -- 17 January 2005 ) was a Norwegian yacht racer and businessperson .
Brigadier General Sławomir Petelicki ( 13 September 1946 -- 16 June 2012 ) was the first commander of the Polish special forces unit GROM from July 13 , 1990 , until December 19 , 1995 .
Hermann Matthias Werrecore ( village of Warcoing , Pecq , ca . 1500 -- after 1574 ) was a Flemish composer in Italy .
Charles Whitworth , 1st Baron Whitworth ( 14 October 1675 -- 23 October 1725 ) was a British diplomat .
James Jeffrey Roche ( 31 May 1847 , Mountmellick , Queen 's County , Ireland -- 3 April 1908 , Berne , Switzerland ) was an Irish - American poet , journalist and diplomat .
Kanzen Teruya ( 1920 - -2004 ) was a physician who contributed much to the Okinawan medical world in postwar days .
Saint Michael of Chernigov or Mikhail Vsevolodovich ( c. 1185 -- Saray , 20 September 1246 ) was a Rus ' prince ( a member of the Rurik dynasty ) .
Sir John Anderson , 1st Baronet ( 8 May 1878 -- 11 April 1963 ) was a Scottish businessman , writer and lecturer .
Johann Albrecht Widmannstetter ( 1506 in Nellingen / Blaubeuren near Ulm -- March 28 , 1557 in Regensburg ) , was a German humanist , orientalist , philologist , and theologian .
Chen Cuifen ( 1873 - -1960 ) was born in Hong Kong as a fourth child .
Sir Thomas Gorges ( 1536 -- 30 March 1610 ) was an Elizabethan courtier and Groom of the Chamber to Queen Elizabeth I. By his great - grandmother , Lady Anne Howard , daughter of John Howard , 1st Duke of Norfolk , he was a second cousin of queen consorts Anne Boleyn and Catherine Howard .
Joseph Cooper Walker ( c.1762 - -1810 ) was an Irish antiquarian and writer .
George Stradling ( 1620 or 1621 -- 19 April 1688 ) was Dean of Chichester Cathedral from 1672 until his death .
Robert Dudley , 1st Earl of Leicester , KG ( 24 June 1532 or 1533 -- 4 September 1588 ) was an English nobleman and the favourite and close friend of Elizabeth I from her first year on the throne until his death .
Leon Festinger ( 8 May 1919 -- 11 February 1989 ) was an American social psychologist , perhaps best known for cognitive dissonance and social comparison theory .
Smohalla ( Dreamer ) ( c. 1815 - 1895 ) Wanapum nineteenth - century dreamer - prophet associated with the Dreamers movement among Native American people in the Pacific Northwest 's Columbia Plateau region .
Alf Frotjold ( 1929 -- 28 March 2001 ) was a Norwegian trade unionist and leader of the Arbeidernes Opplysningsforbund .
John Miley ( 1813 - -1895 ) was an American Christian theologian in the Methodist tradition who was one of the major Methodist theological voices of the 19th century .
Emmanouil Dadaoglou ( Greek : Εμμανουήλ Δαδάογλου ) ( died 1870 ) was a Greek anarchist and a central figure in the early era of Greek anarchism .
Jesús Silva Herzog ( 14 November 1892 -- 13 March 1985 ) was a Mexican economist and historian specialized in the Mexican Revolution and a member of The National College .
Warwick Buckland ( 1863 - -1945 ) was a British stage actor .
Robert Foster Kennedy ( 1884 - 1952 ) was an Irish - American neurologist .
Clive McCorkell ( 20 May 1910 -- 6 May 1962 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Capt . Nathaniel Morton ( 1616 christened -- 29 June 1685 ) was a Separatist settler of Plymouth Colony in Massachusetts , where he served for most of his life as Plymouth 's secretary under his uncle , Governor William Bradford .
Wesley Crawford ( 1901 Indianapolis , Indiana -- 9 January 1961 ) was an American racecar driver .
Paul Nazaroff ( Pavel Stepanovich Nazarov ) ( died 1942 ) was a Russian geologist and writer who was caught up in the Russian Revolution , and became the leader of a plot to overthrow Bolshevik rule in Central Asia .
Franz Schmidt ( 22 December 1874 -- 11 February 1939 ) was an Austrian composer , cellist and pianist .
Elsie Maud Wakefield , OBE ( 3 July 1886 - 17 June 1972 ) was an English mycologist and plant pathologist .
James H. Carson ( 1821 -- 1853 ) , a Second Sergeant in the US Army , boarded the U.S. Lexington with his regiment and set sail for California in 1846 .
Najim Abd - Jasem ( died March 2007 ) was an Iraqi trade unionist who was murdered .
Willem Wissing , known in England as William Wissing ( 1656 -- 10 September 1687 ) , was a Dutch portrait artist who worked in England .
Carl Haeberlin ( 15 December 1870 - -12 November 1954 ) , sometimes also spelled Häberlin , was a German physician and natural historian .
Abraham Booth ( 1734 - -1806 ) was an English dissenting minister and author , known as a Baptist apologetical writer .
Henry Paget , 4th Marquess of Anglesey Bt , PC , ( 25 December 1835 -- 13 October 1898 ) , styled Lord Paget until 1880 and Earl of Uxbridge between 1880 and 1898 , was a British peer .
Gaston Chevrolet ( 4 October 1892 -- 25 November 1920 ) was a French - born American racecar champion driver and automobile manufacturer .
Tankeu Noé ( died 3 January 1964 ) was a member of the Union of the Peoples of Cameroon ( UPC ) guerrilla forces in Cameroon fighting first against French colonial government and then against the government of Ahmadou Ahidjo in the Douala region .
Paul Lukather ( 1926 - 9 October 2014 ) was an actor and voice - over artist who was mostly known as giving voice - overs for many video games including Legacy of Kain series where he voiced Vorador .
Jochem Pietersen Kuyter ( died 1654 ) was an early colonist to New Netherland , and one of the first settlers of what would become Harlem on the island of Manhattan .
Ntare V of Burundi ( born Charles Ndizeye , 2 December 1947 -- 29 April 1972 ) was the last king of Burundi from June to November 1966 .
Mireille Marokvia ( 1908 -- 19 October 2008 ) was a French writer best known for her two books about her ordeals during World War II in Nazi Germany .
Sir Guy Stephenson CB ( 1862 -- 17 October 1930 ) was a British barrister , Assistant Treasury Solicitor and Assistant Director of Public Prosecutions .
Raymond of Poitiers ( c. 1115 -- 29 June 1149 ) was Prince of Antioch from 1136 to 1149 .
Thomas Herne ( died 1722 ) was an English academic and lay participant in religious controversy .
Willis Hardy ( 3 March 1897 -- 7 April 1972 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Antonio Comellas y Cluet ( born in Berga , in Catalonia , 16 Jan. , 1832 ; died there , 3 June 1884 ) was a philosopher .
Herbert Mackworth ( 7 September 1687 -- 20 August 1765 ) was a Welsh landowner , coal owner and MP .
Sam de Brito ( 30 January 1969 -- 12 October 2015 ) was a Sydney - born author and writer for The Sydney Morning Herald and The Age who wrote the blog All Men Are Liars .
Héctor David Delgado Santiago ( 23 December 1975 -- 15 January 2013 ) , commonly referred to by his alias El Metro 4 , was an alleged drug trafficker and high - ranking leader of the Mexican criminal organization known as the Gulf Cartel .
Ja'far Kashfi , Iranian Muslim philosopher , was born at Darabgard in Fars in 1775 or 1776 , lived all his life at Borujerd and died in 1850 - 1851 .
Sobey Martin ( 27 June 1909 -- 27 July 1978 ) was an American director of television and short films , mainly in the 1950s and 1960s .
Drita Pelingu ( 3 December 1926 -- 2 October 2013 ) was an Albanian film and stage actress , academic and director .
Bartholomeus van der Helst ( 1613 -- buried 16 December 1670 ) was a Dutch Golden Age portrait painter .
Stefano Sertorelli ( 24 December 1911 -- 17 December 1994 ) was an Italian soldier and skier .

John Lafayette Camp ( February 20 , 1828 -- 1891 ) was an American lawyer and planter from Texas who served in the Texas state Senate and as a district court judge .
Aquila Emil ( died 4 February 2011 ) was a Papua New Guinean rugby league player who represented his country .
Bo Eriksson ( 30 March 1922 -- 15 December 1982 ) was a Swedish fencer .
Adrien - Gabriel Morice ( 1859 - -1938 ) was a missionary priest belonging to the Oblates of Mary Immaculate .

Aharon Efrat ( Hebrew : אהרון אפרת‎ , born 20 March 1911 , died 16 May 1989 ) was an Israeli politician who served as a member of the Knesset for the Alignment and Mapam between 1974 and 1977 .
Charles Michael , Duke of Mecklenburg ( German : Carl Michael Herzog zu Mecklenburg ; 17 June ( O.S. 5 June ) 1863 -- 6 December 1934 ) was an officer in the Imperial Russian Army , heir presumptive to the throne of Mecklenburg - Strelitz and from 1918 head of the Grand Ducal House .
Hywel ap Ieuaf ( died 985 ) was a King of Gwynedd in north - west Wales from 979 to 985 .
Henry Edward King ( 9 June 1832 -- 5 February 1910 ) was a politician in colonial Queensland , Speaker of the Legislative Assembly of Queensland 1876 to 1883 .
Beli Ram , Sri Swami Swarupanand ji Maharaj ( 1 February 1884 -- 9 April 1936 ) , was an Indian guru of the Advait Mat lineage .

Jakob Wilhelm Hüber ( 1787 in Düsseldorf -- 1871 in Zurich ) was a German landscape painter of the 19th century .
Woodbury Kane ( 8 February 1859 -- 5 December 1905 ) was a noted yachtsman and bon vivant , and member of Theodore Roosevelt 's Rough Riders .
Karl Felix Wolff ( Italian : Carlo Felice Wolff ; 21 May 1879 -- 25 November 1966 ) was a journalist , poet , author and self - taught folklorist of the South Tyrol who collected and published Ladinian legends .
John Okemos ( Chief Okemos ) ( ca . 1775 - 1858 ) was a Michigan Ojibwe ( Chippewa ) chief .
Irving Sayles ( 1872 -- 8 February 1914 ) was an African American vaudeville entertainer .
Edward Manning Bigelow ( 1850 - -1916 ) , known as the `` father of Pittsburgh 's parks '' , was an American City Engineer and later Director of Public Works in Pittsburgh , Pennsylvania .
Herman Georges Berger ( 1 August 1875 -- 13 January 1924 ) was a French fencer and Olympic champion in épée competition .
Otto Šling ( 24 August 1912 - 3 December 1952 ) was born in Nová Cerekev , a village in south Bohemia , then part of the Austrian Empire .
Sir John Austen , 2nd Baronet ( c. 1640 -- 1699 ) was an English landowner and politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1667 and 1699 .
Alice Lucy or Lady Alice Lucy ( c.1594 -- August 1648 ) , born Alice Spencer , was a British puritan gentlewoman who was known for her charity and piety .
Şehzade Ömer ( 20 October 1621 - January 1622 ) was an Ottoman prince ( Turkish : şehzade ) , son of Sultan Osman II .
Frederick John Howard ( 1 March 1814 -- 28 February 1897 ) , was a British Member of Parliament .
Mu'izz al - Dawla Thimal ( died 1062 ) was the Mirdasid emir of Aleppo from 1042 until 1057 , and again from 1061 until his death .
Antonio Fernández Santillana ( 7 February 1876 - 6 December 1909 ) was an early pioneer in aviation .
George Winter Park ( 1834 - 1901 ) was an American politician who served as a member of the Cambridge , Massachusetts Board of Aldermen , in 1869 and 1870 and in the Massachusetts House of Representatives .
Henry Lee II ( 1730 - -1787 ) of Alexandria , Westmoreland , Virginia Colony was the father of Henry `` Light - Horse Harry '' Lee III and grandfather of Robert E. Lee .
Bourchier Cleeve ( died 1760 ) was an English pewterer and writer of pamphlets .
Pietro Valpreda ( 22 June 1933 -- 6 July 2002 ) was an Italian anarchist , dancer and novelist .
Mustafa Hilmi Pasha ( 1840 - 1922 ) was a general of the Ottoman Army .
John Trehenban ( pronounced TREM - on ) ( 1650 - -1671 ) , of St Columb Major in Cornwall , United Kingdom , was a murderer sentenced to imprisonment in a cage on Castle An Dinas downs and starved to death .
Johann Melchior Roos ( December 27 , 1663 , Heidelberg -- 1731 , Braunschweig ) , was a German Baroque painter .
Marcellus de Niveriis , O.F.M. , also known as Marcellus of Skálholt ( d. 1460 or 1462 , at sea , near the coast of Sweden ) , was a German Franciscan and an adventurer who was the 26th Bishop of Skálholt from 1448 until his death but he never came to Iceland .
Janina Hosiasson - Lindenbaum ( 1899 - -1942 ) was a Polish logician and philosopher .
Giuseppe Natoli Gongora di Scaliti ( 9 June 1815 -- 25 September 1867 ) was an Italian lawyer and politician from the Mediterranean island of Sicily .
Savaş Buldan ( 1964 , Hakkâri-4 June 1994 , Bolu ) was a Turkish citizen of Kurdish descent involved in the Susurluk scandal .
Oliver St John , 1st Earl of Bolingbroke ( 1580?--1646 ) , known from 1618 until 1624 as 4th Baron St John of Bletso , was an English nobleman and politician .
Saint Sabinian of Troyes ( died 275 ) was a pagan who converted to Christianity ( tradition states that he was converted by Patroclus of Troyes ) , and became a martyr under Marcus Aurelius .
Mervyn Pinfield ( 28 February 1912 - 20 May 1966 ) was a British television producer and director working for the BBC during the 1950s and 1960s .
Reverend Edward Adey ( 1799 - 1876 ) was a Baptist minister and abolitionist .
Peter Benjamin Graham ( 4 June 1925 -- 15 April 1987 ) , was an Australian visual artist , printer , and art theorist .
Chancey Whiting , Sr . ( 19 August 1819 - 7 June 1902 ) was a Latter Day Saint leader who served as the second president of The Church of Jesus Christ ( Cutlerite ) from 1864 to 1902 , following the death of Cutlerite founder Alpheus Cutler .
Robert Snoden or Snowden ( Mansfield , unknown date -- London , 1621 ) was an English bishop .
Christopher Blackett ( 1751 -- 25 January 1829 ) owned the Northumberland colliery at Wylam that built Puffing Billy , the first commercial adhesion steam locomotive .
Sir William Twysden , 1st Baronet ( 1566 - -1628 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1593 and 1628 .
Kevin Greening ( 30 December 1962 -- 29 December 2007 ) was a British radio presenter , who co - hosted The Radio 1 Breakfast Show on BBC Radio 1 with Zoë Ball from 1997 to 1998 .
Philippa Pullar ( 12 February 1935 , in London -- 7 September 1997 in London ) was a British author and jet set personality best remembered for her exhaustively - researched 1975 biography of Irish - American author Frank Harris .
Alf Milner ( 6 February 1919 -- 2002 ) was an English footballer who made 35 appearances in the Football League playing as an outside right or wing half for Aldershot and Darlington in the 1940s .
Félix Faustino Outes ( July 29 , 1878 -- 1939 ) was an Argentine anthropologist , archeologist and linguist .
Brother Melchior Polowy CSC ( 1911 - -1997 ) was a Catholic member of the Congregation of Holy Cross .
Mawlawi Muhammad Hussain a.k.a . Jamil al - Rahman ( 1939 - -1991 ) was the leader of a Salafist state located in Afghanistans Kunar province .
William Kelly Wallace ( 1883 - -1969 ) was an Irish railway engineer who joined the Northern Counties Committee and later became Chief Civil Engineer of the London Midland and Scottish Railway ( LMS ) .
Eşref Bitlis ( 1933 -- 17 February 1993 ) was a general in the Turkish Gendarmerie , who died in a controversial plane crash .
Seka Gadiyev ( Ossetian : Гæдиаты Секъа ) ( 1855/57 - August 3 , 1915 ) was an Ossetian writer .
Marta Traba ( 25 January 1930 -- 27 November 1983 ) was an art critic and writer known for her contributions to Latin American art and literature .
Richard Boyle , 2nd Earl of Shannon KP , PC ( Ire ) ( 30 January 1727 -- 20 May 1807 ) was an Irish peer and Member of Parliament .
Clifton Brady ( 16 October 1894 -- 9 June 1963 ) was a Seattle architect and one of the founders of the architectural firm NBBJ .
James Arderne , D.D. ( 1636 - 1691 ) , was the dean of Chester .
Lü Zhengcao ( simplified Chinese : 吕正操 ; traditional Chinese : 呂正操 ; pinyin : Lǚ Zhèngcāo ) ( 4 January 1905 -- 13 October 2009 ) was a Chinese military officer .
Albert Frank Mockridge ( 21 October 1903 -- 27 March 1990 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Geelong in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Cungagnaq ( date of birth unknown - d. 1815 ) is venerated as a martyr and saint ( as Peter the Aleut ) by some jurisdictions of the Eastern Orthodox Church .
Thorkil Vanggaard ( 1910 - -1998 ) was a Danish psychiatrist and doctor .
Lieutenant - General Henry Wray CMG ( 1 January 1826 -- 6 April 1900 ) was a Royal Engineers officer who arrived in Fremantle on 12 December 1851 and was responsible for carrying out the construction plans for Fremantle Prison for Edmund Henderson .
Arthur Cole , 1st Baron Ranelagh ( c. 1669 -- 5 October 1754 ) , known as Sir Arthur Cole , Bt , between c. 1691 and 1715 , was an Irish politician .
Rev Joseph Dacre Carlyle FRSE ( 4 June 1759 -- 18 April 1804 ) was an English orientalist .
Sir James South ( October 1785 -- 19 October 1867 ) was a British astronomer .
Whiteley Turner ( born 1866 at Higgin Chamber , Yorkshire , England ; died 20 February 1921 ) was a mill worker , shopkeeper and author .
Joseph Nicholds ( ca.1785 - -1860 ) was a player of the keyed bugle and a composer of sacred music , today known as West gallery music .
Johannes Bernardus van Bree ( 29 January 1801 -- 14 February 1857 ) was a Dutch composer , violinist and conductor .
Eftimios Youakim , BS ( born on 15 June 1886 in Qaytuleh - died on 19 May 1972 ) was an Archbishop of the Melkite Greek Catholic Archeparchy of Zahle and Forzol in Lebanon .
Sir Thomas Peter Anderson Stuart ( 20 June 1856 -- 29 February 1920 ) was a Scottish - born professor of physiology , founder of the medical school at the University of Sydney .
Willem Pieterszoon Buytewech ( 1591/1592 -- September 23 , 1624 ) was a Dutch Golden Age painter , draughtsman and etcher .
Giocangga ( Manchu : ; Chinese : 覺昌安 ; pinyin : Juéchāng'ān ) ( died 1582 ) was the grandfather of Nurhaci , the man who was to unify the Jurchen peoples and begin building what later became the Manchu state .
Dick Mullaly ( 19 June 1892 -- 11 June 1971 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with South Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Dmitry Avaliani ( Georgian : დიმიტრი ევგენის-ძე ავალიანი ; Russian : Дми́трий Евге́ньевич Авалиа́ни ; IPA : ( ˈdmʲitrʲɪj jɪvˈɡʲenʲjɪvʲɪtɕ ɐvəlʲɪˈanʲɪ ) ; 6 August 1938 -- 19 December 2003 ) was a Russian poet and palindromist , who made important contributions to Russian visual poetry .
Alfonso Silva Placeres ( 19 March 1926 -- 16 February 2007 ) was a football player considered one of the best in the history of Canary Islands ' football .
Ralph Truman ( 7 May 1900 -- 15 October 1977 ) was an English actor , usually cast as either a villain or an authority figure .
Charles Kerremans ( 1847- 10 October 1915 , Brussels ) was a Belgian entomologist who specialised in Coleoptera , especially Buprestidae and Cicindelidae .
Pabitra Kumar Deka ( 29 January 1940 -- 5 January 2010 ) is a novelist , humor writer , publisher and editor of a monthly magazine , film critic and script writer living in Assam in India .
John Cliff ( 7 March 1883 - -18 October 1977 ) was the first Assistant General Secretary of the Transport and General Workers ' Union and later a prominent London Transport board member .
Justice Sardar Ali Khan ( 5 May 1930 -- 8 November 2012 ) was former Chief Justice of Andhra Pradesh .
Federico Molero Giménez ( 11 January 1908 , Almería -- 1969 , Madrid ) was a Spanish physicist and inventor , who made pioneering studies of the potential of solar energy for human use .
Kheri is a place of some antiquity , and contains a tine tomb built over the remains of Saiyid Khurd , who died in 1563 .
Vidya Jyothi Osmund Jayaratne ( 2 October 1924 - -September 2006 ) was Sri Lankan academic and politician .
John Michael Hayes ( 11 May 1919 -- 19 November 2008 ) was an American screenwriter , who scripted several of Alfred Hitchcock 's films in the 1950s .
Samuel C. Brightman ( 1911 - -1992 ) was a journalist , war correspondent , freelance writer and adult educator .
Marie Stritt ( 1855 - -1928 ) was a German feminist and a leading force in the German women suffrage movement .
Xue Ji ( Chinese : 薛稷 ; 649 -- July 29 , 713 ) , courtesy name Sitong ( 嗣通 ) , was an official of the Chinese Tang dynasty , briefly serving as chancellor during the reign of Emperor Ruizong .
William Agutter ( 1758 -- 26 March 1835 ) was an English sermon writer and preacher .
Elizabeth Poston ( 24 October 1905 -- 18 March 1987 ) was an English composer , pianist , and writer .
Alexander Innes Shand ( 1832 - -1907 ) was a Scottish barrister and author , known as a journalist , critic , biographer , novelist and travel writer .
Balthazar Martinot ( 1636 - -1714 ) was a French clockmaker , and valet de chambre of the queen and of the King .
Robin Midgley ( 10 November 1934 -- 19 May 2007 ) was a director in theatre , television and radio and responsible for some of the earliest episodes of Z - Cars and for the television version of the Royal Shakespeare Company 's Wars of the Roses .
Sydney Horler ( 18 July 1888 -- 27 October 1954 ) was a prolific British novelist specialising in thrillers .
William Appleton Potter ( December 10 , 1842 -- February 19 , 1909 ) was an American architect who designed numerous buildings for Princeton University , as well as municipal offices and churches .
Hans Granfelt ( 26 October 1897 -- 5 September 1963 ) was a Swedish fencer and discus thrower .
Julius Vuylsteke ( Ghent , 10 November 1836 -- Ghent , 16 January 1903 ) was a Belgian liberal politician and writer .
Jakub Krčín ( June 18 , 1535 -- 1604 ) was a prominent Czech Renaissance architect and engineer .
Ramses Younan ( رمسيس يونان ; Minya , 1913 - Cairo , 1966 ) , was an Egyptian painter and writer .
Anna Sundström , born as Anna Christina Persdotter , ( 26 February 1785 in Kymlinge , Spånga -- 1871 ) , was a Swedish chemist .
Cynthia Payne ( 24 December 1932 -- 15 November 2015 ) was an English brothel keeper and party hostess who made the headlines in the 1970s and 1980s , when she was acquitted of running a brothel at 32 Ambleside Avenue , in Streatham , a southwestern suburb of London .
Aristides Paradissis ( 1923 - 2006 ) was an Australian poet and professor .
Jabir al - Kaabi ( 178~ - 1881 ) ( Arabic : الشيخ جابر الكعبي‎ ) was the leader of the Bani Kaab Arab tribe and the Sheikh of Khorramshahr ( `` Mohammerah '' ) during the 19th century .
Edward Ingersoll ( 2 April 1817 , Philadelphia - 19 February 1893 Germantown , Philadelphia , Pennsylvania ) was a United States author .
Zhang Song ( died 213 ) was an advisor to the warlord Liu Zhang during the late Han Dynasty period of Chinese history .
Robert Scott Troup CMG CIE FRS ( 13 December 1874 -- 1 October 1939 ) was a British forestry expert .
Robert Bayard ( 1788 -- 4 June 1868 ) was a doctor and writer from New Brunswick , Canada .
Giulio Viotti ( Casale Monferrato , Alessandria , 1845-Turin , 1877 ) was an Italian painter , mainly of orientalist and historic subjects .
Mihály Csutorás ( 7 March 1912 - 7 April 1956 ) is a Hungarian international football player .
Tarek Ben Halim died on 11 December 2009 aged 54 after being diagnosed with brain cancer 14 months earlier .
Stephen Woolls ( 1729 - 1799 ) was an English and early American actor and singer , and member of the American and Old American Company .
Battistina Vernazza ( secular name Tommasina Vernazza ) ( born at Genoa , 1497 ; died there , 1587 ) was an Italian canoness regular and mystical writer .
Ellsworth Hunt Augustus ( November 23 , 1897 -- May 16 , 1964 ) was an American businessman from Cleveland , Ohio who served as the tenth National president of the Boy Scouts of America .
Noxolo Nogwaza ( 1987 -- 24 April 2011 ) was a South African lesbian LGBT rights activist and member of the Ekurhuleni Pride Organising Committee .
Ludwik Narbutt ( 26 August 1832 - 5 May 1863 ) was a Polish noble and a notable military commander during the January Uprising .
Ethel McClellan Plummer ( 1888 - -1936 ) was an American artist who resided primarily in New York .
On 16 June 1933 , just two days after his return from negotiations in Germany , Haim Arlosoroff was murdered .
Rosella Rice ( 11 August 1827 - 6 June 1888 ) was an American author , born in Perrysville , Ashland County , Ohio .
George Godsalf ( died 1592 ) , of the diocese of Bath , was an English Roman Catholic priest who had been converted to Catholicism by John Payne .
Sir Arthur Frederick Peterson KC ( 1859 - -1922 ) was a leading barrister and an English High Court judge in the Chancery Division from 1915 to 1922 .
Yi Sang - ryong ( November 24 , 1859 - June 15 , 1932 ) was a Korean Liberation activist , serving as the third president of the Provisional Government of the Republic of Korea from 1925 to 1926 .
Alexander John Forsyth ( 28 December 1769 -- 11 June 1843 ) was a Scottish Presbyterian clergyman who invented the percussion ignition .
Marie Bosse , also known as La Bosse ( died 8 May 1679 ) , was a French poisoner , fortune teller and alleged witch .
Lazar Krestin ( 1868 - -1938 ) was an artist famous in the German art world for Judaic genre scenes and his many sober portraits of Eastern European Jews .
Jill Kitson ( 1938/39 -- 13 May 2013 ) was an Australian radio broadcaster and literary journalist .
Marco D'Arienzo ( Naples , 24 April 1811 -- 24 April 1877 ) was an Italian opera librettist .
Yelü Lihu ( 耶律李胡 ) ( 911 - 960 ) , also named Honggu ( 洪古 ) , courtesy name Xiyin ( 奚隱 ) , formally Emperor Zhangsu ( 章肅皇帝 ) , was an imperial prince of the Khitan Liao state .
N. E. Cameron ( 26 January 1903 -- May 1983 ) is a writer from Guyana who wrote on almost every topic from history and mathematics to politics .
Antisa Khvichava ( Georgian : ანტისა ხვიჩავა ; 8 July 1880 ( purportedly ) -- 30 September 2012 ) was a Georgian woman who claimed to have been born in 1880 .
John Henry Rasor ( 22 November 1849 - 5 November 1925 ) was a Plano , Texas , United States cotton farmer .
Jakob Seisenegger ( 1505 - -1567 ) was an Austrian painter used by Charles V. He won international fame for his use of full - length poses in his portraits , creating a model used by future artists , such as François Clouet .
Abd al - Malik Abd al - Wahid ( died 1339 ) ( also known as Abomelique or Abu Malik ) was a son of the Marinid sultan of Morocco , Abu al - Hasan Ali ibn Othman .
James Anthony Stodart , Baron Stodart of Leaston PC ( 6 June 1916 -- 31 May 2003 ) was a Scottish Tory politician .
Colin Whitaker ( 14 July 1932 -- 1 May 2015 ) was an English footballer who played as a left winger in the Football League .
Lieutenant - Colonel Thomas Howard , 3rd Earl of Effingham PC ( 13 . January 1746 -- 19 November 1791 ) , styled Lord Howard until 1763 , was a British nobleman and Army officer , the son of Thomas Howard , 2nd Earl of Effingham .
Howard E. Ross ( 8 March 1921 in Drumheller , Alberta -- 4 June 2010 in Calgary , Alberta ) was a pioneering land developer and builder in Canada .
Máel Mórda mac Murchada ( died 23 April 1014 ) was King of Leinster .
Yoav Yehoshua Weingarten ( 1845 - 1923 ) was a prominent rabbi and author of Torah commentaries .
David Rindos ( 1947 -- 9 December 1996 ) , was an archaeologist .
Henry Scrimgeour or Scrymgeour ( c. 1505 -- 23 September 1572 ) was a diplomat and book collector .
Gavin Lambert ( 23 July 1924 -- 17 July 2005 ) was a British - born screenwriter , novelist and biographer who lived for part of his life in Hollywood .
Richard Thomas Parker ( 1834 - 10 August 1864 ) was an English murderer who was the last person to be publicly executed in Nottingham .
Horace Gifford ( 1932 -- 1992 ) was a celebrated beach house architect of the Sixties , Seventies and early Eighties .
Jia Qiyun ( Chinese : 贾启允 ) ( 1914 - -2004 ) was a People 's Republic of China politician .
Alexander Ivanovich Galich ( Russian : Александр Иванович Галич ; 1783 -- 1848 ) was a Russian teacher , philosopher , and writer .
Frédéric Cailliaud ( 9 June 1787 -- 1 May 1869 ) was a French naturalist , mineralogist and conchologist .
Marko Orešković ( 3 April 1895 -- 20 October 1941 ) was a Croatian ( and Yugoslav ) Partisan commander .
Waheed Murad ( Urdu : وحید مراد‎ ; 2 October 1938 -- 23 November 1983 ) was a Pakistani film actor , producer and script writer , famous for his charming expressions , attractive personality , tender voice and unusual talent for acting .
Sir David Ferrier FRS ( 13 January 1843 -- 19 March 1928 ) was a pioneering Scottish neurologist and psychologist .
Henry Beaufoy ( November 1750 -- 17 May 1795 ) was a British MP .
Hugh Lunghi ( 3 August 1920 -- 14 March 2014 ) was a British military interpreter and veteran of World War II . He served as an interpreter for Prime Minister Winston Churchill during the war , often accompanying Churchill to summits with other world leaders .
Ronald Richardson Potter MA ARCO ( 12 July 1879 - 4 May 1911 ) was a Scottish organist and composer based in England .
Miha Krek ( 28 September 1897 -- 18 November 1969 ) was a Slovenian lawyer and conservative politician .
Stephen St. Croix ( born Stephen Curtis Marshall ) ( 1948 - -2006 ) was a multifaceted American artist , audio engineer , producer , equipment designer and inventor .
Ferdinand Havlík ( 17 June 1928 -- 28 October 2013 ) was a Czech composer , film composer and clarinet player .
Henry Radclyffe , 2nd Earl of Sussex , KG ( also spelled `` Radcliffe '' ) ( 1507 -- 17 February 1557 ) was a son of Robert Radclyffe , 1st Earl of Sussex and his wife Elizabeth Stafford , Countess of Sussex .
Hwanjile ( r. 1740 - -1774 ) was a high priest and kpojito ( `` reign mate '' ) of the African kingdom of Dahomey , in what is now Benin .
Per Helmer ( 16 July 1897 -- 9 June 1966 ) was a Norwegian businessperson .
Alexander Cowan ( 17 June 1775 -- 13 February 1859 ) was a Scottish papermaker and philanthropist .
S. M. Subbaiah Naidu ( SMS ) ( Telugu : సుబ్బయ్య నాయుడు ) ( 15 March 1914 -- 26 May 1979 ) was a South Indian composer , conductor , and orchestrator .
Mary Flagler Cary ( 1901 - 1967 ) was heir to part of the Standard Oil fortune and became a notable philanthropist , mainly through the charitable trust established at her death .
Geng Jingzhong ( Chinese : 耿精忠 ; pinyin : Gěng Jīngzhōng ; Wade -- Giles : Keng Ching - chung ; died 1682 ) was a powerful military commander of the early Qing dynasty .
Franz Macoun ( 1881 -- 1951 ) was a German Social Democratic trade unionist and politician from the Czech Lands .
Claud Butler ( 14 July 1903 -- 2 November 1978 ) was a London - based bicycle dealer and frame - builder , who from 1928 created a chain of bicycle - retail shops in London and the Midlands .
Jakob Rosanes ( also Jacob ; August 16 , 1842 -- January 6 , 1922 ) was a German mathematician who worked on algebraic geometry and invariant theory .
Sonam Topgyal ( 1941 -- 30 December 2012 ) was Prime Minister ( officially Kalön Tripa ) of the Central Tibetan Administration ( Tibetan government - in - exile ) .
Mow Pang Tzu ( Chinese : 毛邦初 ; also transcribed as Mow Pang Tsu , Mow Pong Tsu , Mow Pang Chu or Mao Bangchu ; March 5 , 1904 -- June 22 , 1987 ) was a high - ranking military officer in the Chinese Chiang Kai - shek government .
Narathihapate ( Burmese : နရသီဟပတေ့ , pronounced : ( nəɹa̰ θìha̰pətḛ ) ; also Sithu IV of Pagan ; 23 April 1238 -- 1 July 1287 ) was the last king of the Pagan Empire who reigned from 1256 to 1287 .
Herbert Fryer ( 21 May 1877 -- 7 February 1957 ) was an English pianist , teacher and composer .
Qara Osman ( Azerbaijani : Qara Yuluq Osman Bəy , Turkish : Kara Yülük Osman Bey ) ( reigned 1378 - -1435 ) was a late 14th and early 15th - century leader of the Turkmen tribal federation of Aq Qoyunlu in what is now eastern Turkey , Iran , Azerbaijan and Iraq .
Arthur Treadwell Walden ( 10 May 1871 -- 26 March 1947 ) was a Klondike Gold Rush adventurer , dog driver and participant in the first Byrd Antarctic Expedition .
Madhira Subbanna Deekshitulu ( 1868 - 1928 ) is the creator of the famous Kasi Majilee Kathalu , series of short stories in Telugu language , known for their wit and humor .
Gene Miller ( 1928 - -2005 ) was a longtime investigative reporter at The Miami Herald who won two Pulitzer Prizes for reporting that helped save innocent men on Florida 's Death Row from execution .
Dorothea of Saxe - Altenburg ( 26 June 1601 in Torgau -- 10 April 1675 in Altenburg ) , was a princess from the House of Wettin by birth and by marriage Duchess of Saxe - Eisenach .
Dattatraya Ganesh Godse ( Devanagari : दत्तात्रय गणेश गोडसे , द. ग. गोडसे ) ( 3 July 1914 -- 5 January 1992 ) was an Indian historian , playwright , art critic , art director , theatre and costume designer , and illustrator .
Louis Wernwag ( b. Alteburg , Württemberg , Germany , 4 December 1769 -- d. Harpers Ferry , Virginia , 12 August 1843 ) was a prominent bridge builder in the United States in the early 19th century .
Harry Peckham ( 1740 -- 10 January 1787 ) was a King 's Counsel , judge and sportsman who toured Europe and wrote a series of letters which are still being published over 200 years later .
Arthur Lukyn Williams ( 1853 - 1943 ) was an English New Testament scholar at Jesus College , Cambridge .
Gerald Griffin ( 12 December 1803 -- 12 June 1840 ) was an Irish novelist , poet and playwright .
Emma Eliza Coe ( 26 September 1850 , in Apia -- 1913 , in Europe ) , known also as `` Queen Emma of New Guinea '' , Emma Forsayth , Emma Farrell and Emma Kolbe was a business woman and plantation owner of mixed American / Samoan descent .
Udaykumar ( 5 March 1933 -- 26 December 1985 ) was an Indian film actor and producer in Kannada cinema , who is renowned for his quality films .
Oskar Heinroth ( 1 March 1871 -- 31 May 1945 ) was a German biologist who was one of the first to apply the methods of comparative morphology to animal behaviour , and was thus one of the founders of ethology .
John Bovingdon ( 1890 - -1973 ) was a modern dancer - turned - economic analyst who performed regularly at the Kings Road House of architect R.M. Schindler in Los Angeles in the 1920s .
Nils Trygg ( 1914 - -1951 ) was one of the recognized masters of twentieth century woodcarving , most famous for the Scandinavian flat - plane style of woodcarving .
Alexander Bernstein , Baron Bernstein of Craigweil ( 15 March 1936 -- 13 April 2010 ) was a British television executive and a Labour member of the House of Lords .
Novica Radović ( Serbian : Новица Радовић ; born in Martinići in 1890 - died in Cetinje in 1945 ) was a Montenegrin politician .
Giovanni Paolo Foscarini ( fl . 1600 -- 1647 ) was an Italian guitarist , lutenist , theorist and composer .
George Gwilt ( 1746 - -1807 ) , also sometimes known as George Gwilt the Elder , was an English architect of the late 18th and early 19th century , particularly associated with buildings in and around London .
Tiberius Claudius Severus Proculus ( about 163-by 218 ) was a Roman Senator .
Robert D. Bailey , Sr . ( July 26 , 1883 -- 1963 ) , better known as R.D. Bailey or `` Judge Bailey , '' was a Democratic politician in West Virginia .
Albert Tschautsch ( 20 December 1843 -- 18 January 1922 ) was a German genre painter .
Fred Esmelton ( 22 June 1872 -- 23 October 1933 ) , was an Australian - born American film actor .
Jan Chiapusso ( 2 February 1890 -- 21 August 1969 ) was a Dutch , later American , classical pianist and teacher .
Giovanni Pierluigi da Palestrina ( c. 1525 -- 2 February 1594 ) was an Italian Renaissance composer of sacred music and the best - known 16th - century representative of the Roman School of musical composition .
Saint Germanus of Man ( Manx : Carmane ) ( c. 410 , Brittany - c. 474 , Normandy ) , also known as Saint Germanus of Peel , was the first Bishop of the Isle of Man .
Frank Schubert ( 1915 - -2003 ) was the last civilian lighthouse keeper in the United States .
Christopher Wittich or Christophorus Wittichius ( 1625 , Brieg -- 1687 , Leiden ) was a German - born Dutch theologian .
Norman Dodd ( June 29 , 1899 -- January 1987 ) born in New Jersey , was a banker / bank manager , worked as a financial advisor and served as chief investigator in 1953 for U.S. Congressman B. Carroll Reece Special Committee on Tax Exempt Foundations ( commonly referred to as the Reece Committee ) .
Boodgur Ramakrishnaiah Panthulu ( 26 July 1910 -- 8 October 1974 ) , better known as B. R. Panthulu , was an Indian film director , producer , and actor .
Alexandre Lagoya ( 21 June 1929 -- 24 August 1999 ) was a classical guitarist and composer .
Martin Snape ( 31 December 1852 , Gosport -- 24 November 1930 ) was an English painter who worked in a variety of media ( oils , watercolours , engraving , etc . ) .
Elizabeth Vesey ( 1715 in Ossory , Ireland -- 1791 in Chelsea , London ) was a wealthy Irish intellectual who is credited with fostering the Bluestockings , a society of women which hosted informal literary and political discussions of which she was an important member .
Havaldar Lalak Jan Shaheed ( Urdu : لالک جان ; 1967 -- 7 July 1999 ) is the last and most recent recipient of Nishan - e - Haider .
Isabel de Bolebec , Countess of Oxford ( c. 1164 -- died 2 February/3 February 1245 ) , was the eldest daughter and co - heiress of Hugh de Bolebec II , Lord of Whitchurch , Buckinghamshire , and his wife , Margaret de Montfichet .

Hymie Barsel ( 11 September 1920 -- 13 March 1987 ) was a South African activist .
Eric Littler ( 14 April 1929 -- 2009 ) is an English former footballer who played in the Football League for Crewe Alexandra , Leicester City , Lincoln City and Wrexham .
George Rayner Hoff ( 27 November 1894 -- 19 November 1937 ) was a sculptor who worked in Australia .
Samaraweera Mudalige Don Premakeerthi de Alwis ( 3 June 1947 -- 31 July 1989 ; commonly known as Premakeerthi de Alwis ) was a Sri Lankan radio and television broadcaster and lyricist .
August Lösch ( 15 October 1906 -- 30 May 1945 ) was a German economist , known for his seminal contributions to regional science and urban economics .
Felix Robertson ( 1781 - -1865 ) was an American pioneer , physician and Jeffersonian Republican politician .
Géza Wertheim ( 3 July 1910 -- 10 August 1979 ) was a Luxembourgian tennis player and bobsledder .
Friedrich Ludwig Abresch ( 29 December 1699 , Homburg - 1782 ) was a Dutch philologist of German origins .
Henry Stauffer was born in Ibersheim , Germany on 1724 and died November 27 , 1777 .
Ryszard Nawrocki ( 7 March 1940 -- 25 April 2011 ) was a Polish film and stage actor , known espacially for his voice skills and work in the dubbing industry .
Charles Vincent Fox , DSO ( 1877 - 1928 ? ) was a British army officer and rower who won the Diamond Challenge Sculls at Henley Royal Regatta in 1900 and the Wingfield Sculls in 1901 .
Strange Jørgenssøn ( 7 April 1539 -- 5 February 1610 ) was a Danish / Norwegian businessman and bailiff .
Irene Astor , Baroness Astor of Hever ( 7 October 1919 -- 12 August 2001 ) was an English philanthropist and member of the Astor family .
Tadevos Hakobyan ( Armenian : Թադևոս Հակոբյան ; 15 June 1917 -- 15 October 1989 ) was a Soviet Armenian historian and geographer .
Christopher Henry Muwanga Barlow ( 1 May 1929 -- 20 August 2006 ) was a Ugandan poet , notable for his poem `` Building the Nation '' .
Josif Rajačić ( 20 July 1785 -- 1 December 1861 ; Serbian Cyrillic : Јосиф Рајачић , also known as Josif Rajačić - Brinski ) was a metropolitan of Sremski Karlovci , Serbian Patriarch , administrator of Serbian Vojvodina and baron .
Dmitry Sakunenko ( Russian : Дмитрий Сакуненко ; 7 January 1930 -- 13 September 2014 ) was a Russian Soviet speed skater .
Alfredo Ovando Candía ( 6 April 1918 -- 24 January 1982 ) was a Bolivian president and dictator ( 1964 - -66 and 1969 - -70 ) , general and political figure .
Captain Frederick Libby ( 15 July 1891 -- 9 January 1970 ) became the first American flying ace , while serving as an observer in the Royal Flying Corps during World War I. Libby transferred to the United States Army Air Service on 15 September 1917 .
Giovanni Maria Falconetto ( c. 1468 - -1535 ) was an Italian architect and artist .
James Ranalph Jackson ( 1882 - 1975 ) was an Australian painter , perhaps best known for painting views of Sydney harbour .
Kim Hwa - jip ( Hangul : 김화집 , Hanja : 金和集 ; 26 May 1905 -- 8 July 2006 ) was a South Korean football player and manager .
Charles Walter Stetson ( 1858 - -1911 ) was an American artist often described as a `` colorist '' for his rich use of color .
Jean - Pierre Étienne ( Rochefort , 9 October 1754 -- French ship Amsterdam ( 1810 ) , off Texel , 31 December 1812 ) was a French Navy officer .
Selma Kronold ( 18 August 1861 , Kraków -- 9 October 1920 , New York ) was a Jewish - born Polish operatic soprano and pianist .
María Magdalena Guzmán Garza ( 16 May 1931 -- 12 March 2015 ) , better known as Magda Guzmán , was a Mexican film and television actress .
Veli Mehmed Pasha was executed on the orders of sultan Ahmed III in June or July 1716 .
Andrew Ray ( 31 May 1939 -- 20 August 2003 ) was an English actor , who was best known as a child star .
Margaret Meen , née Coleman ( died 1824 ) was an English watercolour painter .
Nancy Whiskey ( born Anne Alexandra Young `` Nancy '' Wilson , 4 March 1935 -- 1 February 2003 ) was a Scottish folk singer , best known for the 1957 hit song , `` Freight Train '' .
Thomas Barger ( 1909 -- 1986 ) was an American geologist , explorer , miner , businessman and former CEO of the Arabian American Oil Company ( formerly Aramco now Saudi Aramco ) .

Abdul Qadir Al Rassam,عبد القادر الرسام ) , 1952 - 1882 ) , was born in Baghdad , Iraq .
Johan Georg Raeder ( 1889 - -1959 ) was a Norwegian ophthalmologist known for his studies on glaucoma .

Frank Delos Wolfe ( 1863 - 1926 ) was an architect for clients across northern California .
Maria of Antioch - Armenia ( 1215 - -1257 ) was lady of Toron from 1229 to her death .
Victor Hubinon ( 26 April 1924 -- 8 January 1979 ) was a Belgian comic - book artist , best known for the series Buck Danny and Redbeard .
Robert MacGimsey ( Pineville , Louisiana 1898 - Phoenix , Arizona 1979 ) was an American composer .
William Palfrey ( 1741 -- 1780 ) was an American Patriot .
Erwin Raisz ( 1 March 1893 , Lőcse , Hungary -- 1 December 1968 , Bangkok , Thailand ) was a Hungarian - born American cartographer , best known for his physiographic maps of landforms .
Abdul Wahid Khan ( born 1872-died 1949 ) was an Indian classical singer , from the Kirana gharana .
Max Lacroix ( 9 February 1913 -- 6 January 2009 ) was a distinguished French actuary best known as a founder of the Groupe Consultatif Actuariel Europeen .
Ragnar Vold ( 22 November 1906 -- 16 June 1967 ) was a Norwegian journalist , non - fiction writer and novelist .
Isaac Nordheimer ( born in Memmelsdorf , Germany , in 1809 ; died in New York City , 3 November 1842 ) was a Hebrew scholar and educator who worked in the United States .
Dietrich Hogemann ( 1852 - -1917 ) was Commodore of the Norddeutscher Lloyd fleet of ocean liners .
Li Ezi ( Chinese : 李娥姿 ; 536 - -588 ) , later Buddhist nun name Changbei ( 常悲 ) , was an empress dowager of the Chinese / Xianbei dynasty Northern Zhou .
Gatluak Gai ( died 23 July 2011 ) was a member of the Sudan People 's Liberation Army ( SPLA ) who rebelled after the April 2010 elections and led a renegade militia in the volatile Unity state of South Sudan .
Gerald FitzGerald , 15th Earl of Desmond ( c. 1533 -- 11 November 1583 ) was an Irish nobleman and leader of the Desmond Rebellions of 1579 .
Gianni Ferrio ( 15 November 1924 -- 21 October 2013 ) was an Italian composer , conductor and music arranger .
Richard Elmhirst ( born 18 September 1803 at Ouslethwaite Hall , Worsborough , Yorkshire ; died 18 November 1859 in Lincoln ) was an English first - class cricketer associated with Cambridge University who was active in the 1820s .
Kurt von Gehlen ( * 9 February 1927 in Kiel / Germany - 17 May 1995 in Königstein i m Taunus ) was a German mineralogist and professor .
Frederic Hervey Foster Quin ( 12 February 1799 -- 24 November 1878 ) was the first homeopathic physician in England .
Mathias Wieman ( Carl Heinrich Franz Mathias Wieman ) ( 23 June 1902 -- 3 December 1969 ) was a German stage - performer , silent - and - sound motion picture actor .
J. Fred Metcalf ( 27 July 1899 -- 10 May 1975 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with North Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Edmund FitzAlan , 9th Earl of Arundel ( 1 May 1285 -- 17 November 1326 ) was an English nobleman prominent in the conflict between Edward II and his barons .
Robert Recorde ( ca . 1512 - -1558 ) was a Welsh physician and mathematician .
Heinrich Becker ( 1770 - -1822 ) was a German actor whose real name was Blumenthal .
George Combe ( 21 October 1788 -- 14 August 1858 ) was the leader of -- and the spokesman for -- the phrenological movement for more than twenty years .
Bartolomeo Triachini or Bartolomeo Tassi ( 1516 - 1587 ) was a Bolognese architect .
Hendrick van Streeck ( baptized 11 April 1659 - buried 19 November 1720 ) , was a Dutch Golden Age painter of church interiors .
Zhang Zhifang ( 張直方 ) ( died January 23 , 881 ? ) was a general of the Chinese dynasty .
Gus Pixley ( 1864 -- 2 June 1923 ) was an American actor of the silent era .
Daniel Thurston ( March 1 , 1719 Bradford , Essex Co. , Massachusetts - July 14 , 1805 Bradford , Essex Co , MA ) , was an Officer during the American Revolution , Member of the Committee of Safety , and a member of the Committee drafting the Massachusetts State Constitution .
Thomas Lauder ( or Thomas de Lawedre ) ( 1395 -- 4 November 1481 ) was a 15th - century Scottish churchman .
Henry Ley , 2nd Earl of Marlborough ( 3 December 1595 -- 1 April 1638 ) was an English peer and Member of Parliament .
Andrew Stuart Hibberd MBE ( 5 September 1893 -- 1 November 1983 ) was a British radio personality for 40 years .
James Winstone ( 9 February 1863 - -27 July 1921 ) was a British trade unionist Born in Risca , Winstone worked from the age of eight , first at a local brickworks , then at Risca United Colliery .
Prof James Pillans ( 1778 - -1864 ) LLD FRSE was a Scottish classical scholar and educational reformer .
George Kestell - Cornish was the third Anglican Bishop of Madagascar from 1919 until his death in 1925 .
Lewis D. Collins , often known as Lew Collins or Cullen Lewis ( 12 January 1899 - -24 August 1954 ) , was an American film director .
Don Juan de Santo Domingo de Mendoza Tlacaeleltzin Chichimeca teuctli ( died 1563 ) was the tlatoani ( ruler ) of Itztlacozauhcan in Amaquemecan , Chalco from 1548 to 1563 .
Daniel Stuart ( 1766 - -1846 ) was a Scottish journalist , and associate of Samuel Taylor Coleridge .
Jean - Pierre Latz ( c. 1691 -- Paris , 4 August 1754 ) was one of the handful of truly outstanding cabinetmakers ( ébénistes ) working in Paris in the mid-18th century .
Pramod Chakravorty ( 15 August 1929 -- 12 December 2004 ) was an Indian director and film producer .
Hasan Nazih ( 1921 - September 2012 ) was a leading Iranian civil rights lawyer , opposition leader and a former bureuacrat .
Lieutenant Colonel Charles Hercules Green DSO ( 26 December 1919 -- 1 November 1950 ) was a senior officer in the Australian Army .
Frances Laughlin Wadsworth ( 1909 - 1978 ) was an American sculptor active in Hartford , Connecticut .
Fritz Lüddecke ( 23 February 1920 - 10 August 1944 ) was a Luftwaffe ( German air force ) fighter ace during the Second World war .
Otto VI , Margrave of Brandenburg - Salzwedel , nicknamed Otto the Short ( c. 1255 -- 1303 in Lehnin ) was a member of the House of Ascania and co - ruler of Brandenburg .
Charles Royle , Baron Royle JP ( 23 January 1896 -- 30 September 1975 ) was a British businessman and Labour politician .
Horace Francis ( 1821 - 1894 ) was a British architect , who often worked with his elder brother , fellow architect Frederick John Francis ( 1818 - 1896 )
Basil B. Bruno ( 1887 - 1955 ) was an American Republican Party politician , who served in the New Jersey General Assembly representing Monmouth County in 1924 and 1925 , and again in 1936 .
Dionysius Andreas Freher ( 1649 - -1728 ) was a Christian mystic , most famous for his extensive commentaries on Jacob Boehme .
Alex Sevanian ( November 3 , 1946 -- February 17 , 2005 ) was an American pharmacologist .
Laurent Dailliez ( died 1991 ) was a French history doctor who graduated from Ecole pratique des hautes études .
Georg von Kopp ( 25 July 1837 -- 4 March 1914 ) was a German Cardinal of the Roman Catholic Church who served as Bishop of Fulda ( 1881 - -87 ) and Prince - Bishop of Breslau ( 1881 - -1914 ) .
Duke Philip Sigismund of Brunswick - Wolfenbüttel ( July 1 , 1568 in Hessen am Fallstein -- 19 March 1623 in Iburg ) was a Lutheran administrator of the Prince - Bishopric of Verden and Osnabrück ( 1591 - -1623 ) son of Julius , Duke of Brunswick and Lunenburg , Prince of Wolfenbüttel and Hedwig of Brandenburg .
Vane Featherston ( 1864 - -1948 ) was an English theatre actress .
Justin Meyer ( born Raymond Meyer , 11 November 1938 -- 6 August 2002 ) was an American vintner , enologist , and monk of the Christian Brothers .
Samuel Bleichröder ( 15 July 1779 -- 30 December 1855 ) was German Jewish banker and financier .
Ben Winkler ( 1902 - 1979 ) was a sound engineer and recordist in the U.S. film industry having some 135 credits to his name .
William Guy Wall ( 1792 -- 1864 ) was an American painter of Irish birth .
Balthasar Guersye , M.D. ( died 1557 ) , was an Italian physician who rose to high favour at the court of Henry VIII . On 7 November 1519 ' Thomas Roos of London , surgeon , was bound over in 100l .
Paul Sievert ( born 12 March 1895 , died 18 December 1988 ) was a German racewalker , best known for his achievements in the 50 kilometres race walk .
Sir Charles Lyell , 1st Baronet , FRS ( 14 November 1797 -- 22 February 1875 ) was a British lawyer and the foremost geologist of his day .
John Baptist Smith ( 1843 - -1923 ) is believed by some to have provided the most lasting contribution made by either side during the American Civil War .
Roger Toothaker ( November 27 , 1634 , England -- June 1692 , Province of Massachusetts Bay ) was a farmer and folk - healer who came to Massachusetts from England shortly after he was born .
Lesley Duncan ( married name Lesley Cox ; 12 August 1943 -- 12 March 2010 ) was an English singer - songwriter , best known for her work during the 1970s .
Horace Harvey ( October 1 , 1863 -- September 9 , 1949 ) was a lawyer , jurist , and a Chief Justice of Alberta , Canada .
Goparaju Ramachandra Lavanam ( 10 October 1930 -- 14 August 2015 ) , known popularly as G. Lavanam or Lavanam , was an Indian social reformer and Gandhian .
Kristian Prestrud ( 22 October 1881 -- 11 November 1927 ) was a Norwegian naval officer and polar explorer who participated in the Amundsen Antarctic Expedition between 1910 and 1912 .
Marjorie Kendig Gates ( 1892 - -1981 ) , best known as M .
William Henry Warren ( 2 February 1852 -- 9 January 1926 ) was an Australian engineer and twice president of the Royal Society of New South Wales .
Sarah Cobcroft ( 1772 -- 1857 ) was a midwife and farmer who emigrated from England to Australia .
Gopal Singh Nepali ( Standard Nepali : गोपाल सिँह नेपाली ) ( 1902 - -1963 ) was an eminent Nepalese poet of Hindi literature and a famous lyricist of Bollywood .
Vannozza dei Cattanei ( née : Giovanna dei Cattanei , but nicknamed `` Vannozza '' ; 13 July 1442 - -24 November 1518 ) was an Italian woman who was one of the many mistresses of Cardinal Rodrigo Borgia , later to become Pope Alexander VI .
Hoàng Thị Loan ( 1868 - -1901 ) was the mother of Nguyen Sinh Cung , later known as Ho Chi Minh , former President of North Vietnam .
Major Victor Marra Newland , MC , DCM ( 2 November 1876 -- 12 January 1953 ) was an Australian army officer and politician .
John Sartorius ( 1700 ? -- 1780 ? ) was an Anglo - German animal painter , the first of four generations of the celebrated Sartorius family of artists .
Cyriacus of Jerusalem was a bishop of Jerusalem who died during a riot in 133 AD .
Dr. Leon Geršković ( 2 February 1910 -- 1 April 1992 ) was Croatian Jewish lawyer , legal scholar and politician .
Andrew Pringle , Lord Alemoor ( died 1776 ) was a Scottish judge .
Louis - Zéphirin Joncas ( 26 July 1846 -- 28 March 1903 ) was a Canadian civil servant , journalist and politician .
Henry Evans ( c. 1832 -- 17 June 1905 ) was a conjurer , ventriloquist and humorist , born in Kennington , South London , who used the stage name Evanion .
Levi ben Abisha ben Phinhas ben Yitzhaq ; ( 1920 - -May 23 , 2001 ) , served as the Samaritan High Priest from 1998 until his death .
Atinolfo was the Bishop of Fiesole ( 1038 - -1057 ) and an opponent of Papal reform .
Federico Tedeschini ( 12 October 1873 -- 2 November 1959 ) was an Italian Cardinal of the Holy Roman Church who served as Papal Datary in the Roman Curia from 1938 until his death , and was elevated to the cardinalate in 1935 by Pope Pius XI .
William Sawrey Gilpin ( 4 October 1762 ( source ? ) -- 4 April 1843 ) was an English artist , drawing master and , in later life , landscape designer .
Baron Carl Fredrik Pechlin ( 8 August 1720 -- 29 May 1796 ) was a Swedish politician and demagogue , son of the Holstein minister at Stockholm , Johan Pechlin , and brother of Johanna Lohm .
Jean Dun , also known as Jean Dun `` père '' , ( ? -- 1735 ) was a French opera singer active at the Paris Opéra where he created many bass roles during the late 17th and early 18th centuries .
Wayman Crow ( 1808 - -1885 ) was one of the founders of Washington University , a St. Louis businessmen , as well as a politician .
Bridget Chaworth ( c. 1542 -- 18 April 1621 ) , later Bridget Carr , was a gentlewoman of the Privy Chamber to Elizabeth I and Queen Anne .
Yasui Sanchi ( 安井算知 , 1617 - 1703 ) was a Japanese professional go player , and second head of the Yasui house .
John Shank ( also spelled Shanke or Shanks ) ( died January 1636 ) was an actor in English Renaissance theatre , a leading comedian in the King 's Men during the 1620s and 1630s .
Edward White Clark ( January 20 , 1828 -- 1904 ) was the head of E. W. Clark & Company , a prominent financial firm in Philadelphia , Pennsylvania .
Ranulph or Ralph de Mortimer ( before 1198 to before 6 August 1246 ) was the second son of Roger de Mortimer and Isabel de Ferrers of Wigmore Castle in Herefordshire .
Fred Paul Hedges ( March 27 , 1921 -- June 19 , 1999 ) was a master guitar builder and guitar teacher from Nashville , Tennessee .
John Cordier ( Oudenburg , 1 September 1941-Bonheiden , 22 January 2002 ) was a Belgian businessman .
Lambert Visscher ( 1633 , Haarlem -- after 1690 , Italy ) , was a Dutch Golden Age printmaker .
Francis Sheed Anderson CB ( 1897 -- 12 September 1966 ) , was a Scottish businessman , civil servant and Liberal Party politician .
Vice Admiral Glen Syndercombe SSA SD SOE SM MMM SAN ( Rtd ) ( 17 November 1931 -- 18 July 2005 ) was a former Chief of the South African Navy .
Leonidas Hubbard Jr. ( 1872 - -1903 ) was an American journalist and adventurer .
Sushila Sundari ( 1879 - 1924 ) was the first Indian woman to perform in a circus .
Shlomo Lavi ( Hebrew : שלמה לביא‎ , born Shlomo Levkovich in 1882 , died 23 July 1963 ) was a Zionist activist and politician .
Arthur Dick Pougher ( 19 April 1865 , Humberstone , Leicester , England -- 20 May 1926 , Aylestone Park , Leicester , England ) was a cricketer who played for Leicestershire County Cricket Club between 1894 and 1901 .
Dimitrie Paciurea ( Romanian pronunciation : ( diˈmitri.e paˈt͡ʃjure̯a ) ; 2 November ( 1873 or 1875 ) -- 14 July 1932 ) was a Romanian sculptor .
Tatiana Gritsi - Milliex ( 1920 -- 14 February 2005 ) was a Greek novelist and journalist .

Antti Yrjö Hammarberg ( 14 September 1943 -- 14 January 1991 ) , professionally known as Irwin Goodman , was a popular Finnish rock and folk singer .
Ogier of Savoy ( c.1333 - -1373 ) was the second and illegitimate son of Aymon , Count of Savoy , and half - brother of Amadeus VI .
Michael Cacoyannis ( Greek : Μιχάλης Κακογιάννης , Michalis Kakogiannis ; 11 June 1921 -- 25 July 2011 ) was a Greek Cypriot filmmaker , best known for his 1964 film Zorba the Greek .
James Craigie Robertson ( 1813 - -9 July 1882 ) was a Scottish Anglican churchman , canon of Canterbury Cathedral , and author of a History of the Christian Church .
James William Barclay ( 1832 -- 26 February 1907 ) was a Scottish businessman , farmer and politician .
Rahul Dasgupta or Rahul Da ( 14 January 1943 -- 19 November 2012 ) was an independent Indian film director .
Maerten de Vos , Maerten de Vos the Elder or Marten de Vos ( 1532 -- 4 December 1603 ) was a Flemish painter mainly of history paintings and portraits .
Lauritz Galtung ( c. 1615 - 1661 ) was a Norwegian nobleman of the Galtung - family who was educated in the military , and became Admiral of the Dano - Norwegian joint fleet .
Benjamin Paul Blood ( November 21 , 1832 -- January 15 , 1919 ) was an American philosopher and poet .
William Duncan Silkworth , M.D. , ( 1873 - 1951 ) was an American medical doctor and specialist in the treatment of alcoholism .
Sir John Bamford Slack ( 11 July 1857 - 11 February 1909 ) was a British politician , member of the Liberal Party and Methodist lay preacher .
Aliqoli Mirza Qajar ( 1819 - 1880 ) , given the honorary title of Etezado - ol - Saltaneh , was a prince of the Qajar dynasty .
Robert Sayer ( 1725 - -1794 ) was a leading publisher and seller of prints , maps and maritime charts in Georgian Britain .
Field Marshal Richard Molesworth , 3rd Viscount Molesworth , PC ( 1680 -- 12 October 1758 ) , styled The Honourable Richard Molesworth from 1716 to 1726 , was an Anglo - Irish military officer , politician and nobleman .
Benjamin Pye LL.D. ( 1726 - 1808 ) was Archdeacon of Durham from 1791 to 1808 .
Stephen Cabarrus ( 1754 - -1808 ) held the office of the Speaker of the House of Representatives in North Carolina from 1789 to 1793 and from 1800 to 1805 .
Vicente Lusitano ( died after 1561 ) was a Portuguese music composer and theorist of the late Renaissance .
Frank Meechan ( 27 October 1929 -- 20 August 1976 ) was a Scottish footballer , who played for Petershill , Celtic and Stirling Albion .
Washington Lloréns Lloréns ( 28 November 1899 -- 21 June 1989 ) was a Puerto Rican writer , linguist , lexicographer , and journalist .
Kapitan Laut Buisan ( reigned : 1597 - -1619 ) , also known as Datu Katchil or Sultan Laut Buisan , was the sixth Sultan of Maguindanao in the Philippines .
Antonio Sciortino ( Ħaż - Żebbuġ , 25 January 1879 - 10 August 1947 ) was a Maltese sculptor whose work reflects several artistic movements , including Realism and Futurism , as well as the influence of Auguste Rodin .
Sidney Bradford ( 30 May 1906 -- 2 August 1960 ) went blind at 10 months of age , but regained sight on both eyes after a cornea transplant at the age of 52 .
Gustav Johann Georg Hellmann or Georg Gustav Hellmann ( 3 July 1854 -- 21 February 1939 ) was a German meteorologist .
Hurtle Rice ( 7 July 1884 -- 25 May 1960 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Thomas Lilburne ( died 25 March 1665 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons in 1656 and 1659 .
Moses Blackman FRS ( 6 December 1908 -- 3 June 1983 ) was a South African - born British crystallographer .

Robert Alanson ( by 1472 - 1540 ) of Lincoln , was an English politician .

Nimrod Jarrett Smith ( 1837 - -1893 ) , or Tsaladihi , was the fourth Principal Chief of the Eastern Band of Cherokee Indians .

Brigadier Sir Joseph Frederick Laycock KCMG DSO TD ( 12 June 1867 -- 10 January 1952 ) was a British soldier , and Olympic sailor .

Fritz Steinbach ( 17 June 1855 - 13 Aug 1916 ) was a German conductor and composer who was particularly associated with the works of Johannes Brahms .
